INSERT INTO `page_content_models` VALUES (16,17,'Chemotherapy Operational Considerations','<h3><strong>1.1 Service Norms</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>a. The National Guidelines for Cancer Management shall form the basis for clinical management at the facility.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. The centre or unit must have NCI-K approved protocols for diagnosis and treatment of all malignancies they manage founded on sound scientific principles and evidence-based medicine which must be accessible to the prescribers, pharmacists and nurses at the centre at all times.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. The protocols must be updated as appropriate and be readily available for inspection when needed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. The centre or unit shall also commit to quality improvement, supporting cancer research and improving the training and mentoring of health care e. The centre or unit shall have infrastructure in place to be able to carry out cancer registration and reporting to the National Cancer Registry and DHIS.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.2 Service Delivery Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Service Delivery Considerations Every cancer centre shall:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Formulate and prominently display a service charter that details the roles and responsibilities of both the patient and the centre.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Provide integrated and multidisciplinary care&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Prioritize coordination and planning for professionals to help facilitate access to care at other levels of care, including awareness creation, screening/early detection, case management and appropriate downward referrals.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Have a reasonable time frame &ndash; definitive/tissue diagnosis should be done preferably within 2 weeks and the initiation of appropriate treatment within a month of diagnosis.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Follow evidence-based protocols and guidelines.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Have informed consent obtained prior to all procedures including treatments. In case of a minor, a parent/guardian shall give consent. The information prior to consenting shall be provided in a manner easily understandable by the patient. The rights of the child should be prioritized.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Establish clear navigation systems to enable patients&rsquo; access to services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;h. Design patient-tracking systems for patient follow-up throughout the continuum of care. i. Develop standard operating procedures for every service being provided</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.3 Clinical considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Provide cancer management that is holistic and patient-centred for best care outcomes</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Before initiation of treatment, clearly define and communicate the goals of care to the patient in accordance with a patient care plan</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Provide the patient the right to detailed information on his/her condition, treatment options including clinical trials, side effects, expected outcome and prognosis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Allow the patient the right to seek a second or additional opinion before consenting to initiation of treatment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Have all aspects of carefully documented, stored and easily retrievable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Allow access of patients to their records as well as laboratory samples when needed</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Comprehensively document patient history</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.4 Multi-disciplinary Tumor Boards</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Definition; the multidisciplinary expert team that should manage cancer patients in a consultative approach</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Establish multidisciplinary teams (MDTs)/tumor boards which shall guide and direct cancer management</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have MDTs meet regularly and have participation from all relevant disciplines depending on the cancer case and the level of care</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Have all complex cases discussed by a multidisciplinary team</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Have an MDT coordinator who will organize for meetings, keep records of discussions and provide reports on cancer patient management</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Utilize technology to convene virtual MDT discussions with proper documentation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It consists of different experts including &ndash; medical oncologist, radiation/clinical oncologist, surgeon, pathologist, palliative physician and specialists, oncology pharmacist, oncology nurse, radiologist, interventional radiologist, haematologist, medical physicist, radiation therapist/therapy radiographer, medical laboratory technologists specialized in different laboratory disciplines.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.5 Diagnostic imaging</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Incorporate clinical findings in conducting diagnostic imaging modalities&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Consider image-guided diagnostics where applicable</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use a standard protocol for conducting imaging procedures or an MOU with a facility with that has standard protocol for conducting imaging procedures.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use internationally and locally recognized standards and guidelines for the safe installation, operation and use of imaging equipment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use a standard imaging diagnostic reporting protocol&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Outsource/provide access to an accredited imaging diagnostic facility</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.6 Nursing Considerations&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:-</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide oncology and palliative nursing care for the entire continuum of care (Prevention, Awareness, screening, early detection, diagnosis, treatment, survivorship and end of life care, bereavement).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Support the coordinating role of oncology and palliative care nurses in the care team and community linkage for cancer patients</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.7 Chemotherapy Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Definition of Chemotherapy</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Have only appropriately qualified oncologists initiate cancer patients on chemotherapy and biotherapies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;b. Have chemotherapy medications prepared by a pharmacist or pharmaceutical technologist in a bio-safety cabinet class 2B2 vented to the outside.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Provide personal protective equipment to all members of the health care team who prepare, mix, administer and transport hazardous chemotherapy drugs.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Have a program that monitors exposure to hazardous chemotherapy drugs for all health workers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Ensure pregnant and lactating health workers are not assigned to an area where chemotherapy drugs are present/being administered</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Provide education and training for safe handling of these drugs to health workers exposed to hazardous chemotherapy drugs prior to their being assigned to an area where chemotherapy agents are present. Training must be done for all staff in the facility, annually, with the educational content being specific to the activities for which the health worker is responsible.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Prior to administration of chemotherapy ensure there is a system in place to confirm that the correct medication and dosage is administered to the correct patient.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>h. Chemotherapy medicines especially vesicants like vinca alkaloids shall be whenever possible be administered via a central line e.g. using chemoports. Chemotherapy shall be administered through infusion pumps for accuracy and safety.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Have the facility ensure provision for management of extravasations and spills.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>j. Provide patients and caregivers involved in the delivery of chemotherapy at home receive some basic education and training on the principles of safe handling, dealing with spills, waste disposal and patients&rsquo; excreta. Written instructions shall be given to the patient and/or caregiver, including information on the use of oral chemotherapeutic agents.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>k. Document the process for handling hazardous drugs waste generated during compounding and administration or during spills, as well as waste (bulk) products for chemotherapy.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>l. Store chemotherapy medicines separately from other medicines &ndash; both storage area and refrigerator&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>m. Transport of chemotherapy medicines should maintain the integrity of the drug to avoid breakage or leakage that leads to spillages, contamination and exposure to the hazardous drug&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>n. Ensure labelling of chemotherapeutic agents includes storage, handling and disposal instructions&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>o. Develop facility SOPs for &ndash; designation of HD areas; receipt of HDs; storage of HDs; compounding of HDs; use and maintenance of proper engineering controls; hand hygiene and use of PPEs; deactivation, decontamination, cleaning &amp; disinfection; dispensing of HDs; transport of HDs; administering HDs, environmental monitoring; disposal of HDs; spill control and medical surveillance.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.8 Health Information and Records &amp; Cancer Registry Office Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Designate an office for Cancer registry- the office should be lockable, with lockable cabinets and a computer with internet access.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Establish a health records department that will maintain all patient records in a system that is secure, confidential and easy to retrieve.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Capture data for all cancer cases comprehensively.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Notify the National Cancer Registry all new cancer cases using the cancer&nbsp;abstract form <a href=\"about:blank\">National Cancer Notification Form_FINAL copy.pdf</a>(NACARE) as provided for by the Cancer Control Act 2012.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Ensure that the health records department sends reports to the National&nbsp;Cancer Registry and MoH-KHIS monthly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Permanently archive cancer patient records.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Respect patients&rsquo; rights to access their records at any point in their lifetime.<strong> </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.9 Palliative Care and Survivorship Considerations&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Provide palliative care from the point of cancer diagnosis and at all times throughout the course of illness.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Integrate palliative care with other health services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Prioritize and provide effective relief of pain and other distressing symptoms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Provide timely rehabilitative and supportive services.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Facilitate formation of patient support groups.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Establish survivorship programs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Adhere to the National Palliative Care Policy and the National Palliative Care&nbsp;Guideline.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.10 Equipment Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Have all the facilities and equipment registered and licensed for safe and effective conduct of its services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have access to a qualified biomedical engineer, who is ultimately responsible for ensuring that all equipment are in proper working condition and that the necessary safety devices are fitted and in working order.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Maintain service contracts and schedules of service with the contracted service providers to ensure regular servicing as per the manufacturer&rsquo;s instructions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Ensure equipment compliance with relevant regulations according to the appropriate governing regulatory body. Equipment more than 7 years old should not be acquired for cancer treatment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Ensure safe disposal of obsolete or unserviceable equipment as guided by the relevant regulatory body.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.11 Referral Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Develop patient referral SOPs (<a href=\"about:blank\">ministry-of-health-referral-guidelines-37-40.pdf</a> ) which conform to the national referral guidelines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Properly document referrals to and away from the facility.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Promote upward, downward and horizontal referral where appropriate.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Facilitate referrals for specialized services that are unavailable at the centre to facilities that are accessible and are accredited by the relevant regulatory body.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Assess patients for fitness to travel and provide necessary supportive&nbsp;mechanisms (ambulance, nurse, oxygen supply) before referral.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Provide proper patient counseling on cancer, tests to be done, costs implications and expected treatment before referral.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Refer a patient to the right specialist for further management if a service outside oncology services is required</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.12 Quality Assurance</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Establish a Quality Assurance Programme (QAP) that is adequately supervised and provides reports to NCI Kenya as required.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have risk assessment measures in place with objectives and systematic monitoring and evaluation so as to identify problems and system failures and guide the necessary action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Have regular morbidity and mortality meetings to identify specific clinical performance indicators.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.13 Infection Prevention and Control</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oncology patients are at increased infection risk due to immunosuppression and frequent exposure to healthcare settings.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Have a hospital&rsquo;s infection prevention and control program must be in accordance with the WHO Practical Guidelines for Infection Control<a href=\"about:blank\">.File571.pdf</a>.</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Have hand-washing facilities for staff readily available. Hand sanitizers should be provided at every work station.</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have eyewash facilities for staff in Chemo mixing and administration areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide a designated sluicing area for linen generated in the chemo area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have isolation rooms and practice barrier nursing by ensuring PPEs are&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>available and easily accessible.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.14 Occupational health and safety</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Implement the Occupational, Health &amp; Safety (OSH) Act in the workplace.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Provide safety and health training at least once every 3 years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Be subject to annual inspection by the local regulatory body and adhere to the basic safety standards as set by the regulatory body.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Disclose labeling laws for identification and classification of chemicals by types of hazards, including medication labels and safety data sheets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Establish a system for identification and surveillance of exposure: estimating the number of workers who come into contact with substances and are employed in occupations with increased carcinogenic risk, and reducing to minimum the number of workers exposed, the duration of exposure and the degree of exposure, and establishing an appropriate system of records.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Ensure medical surveillance applies to all healthcare workers handling hazardous drugs and includes assessment and documentation of symptom complaints, physical findings &amp; laboratory values</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Provide personal protective equipment i.e N95 masks, powder-free Nitrile gloves, shoe covers, head net, goggles, non-absorbent gown, face shield for health workers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>h. Establish/develop guidelines and recommendations for proper use and handling of carcinogenic chemicals and training packages for healthcare workers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>i. Have a system for incidents monitoring and management at the workplace.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>j. Empower workers by providing them with access to information about their exposures and risks.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>k. Have programs to monitor and support employee performance, mental health, work-life balance and put in place debriefing programs.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.15 Waste Management</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Dispose cytotoxic waste produced in the process of the diagnosis and treatment of cancer in accordance to international and relevant local guidelines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have written policies and SOPs for hazardous waste describing requirements for the segregation, packaging, labeling, collection, transportation storage and on site treatment of waste within the facility.<a href=\"about:blank\">National-Guidelines-for-Safe-management-of-health-care-waste-Final1.pdf</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Provide waste disposal amenities and commodities.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Conduct regular capacity building on waste disposal for all healthcare providers including support staff.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Provide appropriate PPEs for handling hazardous waste.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Incinerate hazardous waste using special incinerators that can combust at 1200&deg;Centigrade and maintain documentation on the same.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Minimize the risk of contaminating the local water supply and/or soil with hazardous drugs. Hazardous drug waste shall never be discarded into waste water (sink or toilet) or into a landfill.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.16 Emergency Medical Care&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Have facilities and human resources to handle oncologic and palliative care emergencies.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Ensure medical staffs are trained in BLS/ACLS.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Stabilize the patient and expeditiously refer for emergency management where applicable.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Be well equipped with resuscitation commodities and equipment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.17 Adverse Events</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Any adverse event that occurs as a result of cancer diagnosis or treatment must be documented, discussed internally and reported to the relevant regulatory bodies such as the Pharmacy and Poisons Board, relevant regulatory body and the NCI-K.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.18 Death of a Patient</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Document all deaths occurring whilst patients are undergoing treatment appropriately.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Offer bereavement support to the family.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Have periodic mortality meetings where cancer deaths are discussed by a multidisciplinary team</p>','2022-07-18 09:32:39','2022-07-18 09:33:45'),(17,18,'Chemotherapy Human Resource','<p>The human resource requirements for the chemotherapy centre are as follows with core staff and supportive staff</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oncologist (Medical, Clinical)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oncology Nurse</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical Pharmacist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Cancer Registrar</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical Counsellor&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nutritionist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical social worker</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Infection Prevention and Control Expert&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Quality Assurance Expert</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient navigators</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Core Human Resource</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Minimum Qualifications&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Required staff establishment (number)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation oncologist/ Medical oncologist/clinical&nbsp;Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED/Fellowship in&nbsp;radiation oncology/Clinical oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;as an oncologist by&nbsp;KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; in charge of radiotherapy treatment;&nbsp;assessment, initiation, review of patients cancer&nbsp;treatment and patient follow up; treatment&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>planning; chair MDTs meetings; participate in clinical research in oncology; participates in&nbsp;equipment procurement&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse - Specialized oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or BSc&nbsp;Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Specialized oncology nursing training&nbsp;at Higher Diploma,&nbsp;MSc Nursing or an&nbsp;accredited oncology program&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provide nursing care to cancer patients in&nbsp;collaboration with other members of the MDT;&nbsp;health education; screening activities; comprehensive patient assessments; symptom&nbsp;management; management of treatment side&nbsp;effects; patient navigation activities; clinical research in oncology; advocacy; mentorship and&nbsp;teaching; policy formulation and implementation; screening activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer registrars</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Degree/diploma&nbsp;holder in Health Records &amp; information.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in cancer&nbsp;registration from&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>African Cancer Registry Network (AFCRN)&nbsp;approved provider</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer data abstraction, maintenance of cancer&nbsp;patients records and participation in cancer&nbsp;research</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical pharmacist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Masters in clinical&nbsp;pharmacy or equivalent&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to Practice&nbsp;by PPB.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;- Training and certification in chemotherapy&nbsp;handling and administration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Head of pharmaceutical oncology services; allocation of duties; supervision; member of MDT;&nbsp;research; in charge of supply chain of oncology&nbsp;commodities; in-charge of preparation of chemotherapy medications</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical counselors&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma/degree in&nbsp;Psychological counseling.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- License to practice&nbsp;from relevant body</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Counseling of patients and their caregivers/families on cancer; patient navigation; research;&nbsp;member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Housekeeping&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Staff</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Relevant training in&nbsp;housekeeping</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training in safe handling of hazardous&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Products</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Handling of waste and cleaning</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical social&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Worker</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma or bachelors&nbsp;in social Sciences</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Assessment of socio-economic background of&nbsp;patients; Contact tracing; patient navigation;&nbsp;research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse - General&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(adult care and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>pediatric care)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Certification in chemotherapy handling and&nbsp;administration (those&nbsp;working in chemotherapy units)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Undergone an appropriate preceptorship/mentorship program in cancer management for at least 3 or 6&nbsp; months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Providing nursing care to cancer patients in&nbsp;collaboration with other members of the MDT,&nbsp;in all areas of cancer treatment; health education; screening activities; participate in clinical&nbsp;research in oncology; screening activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nutritionists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or degree in&nbsp;Nutrition or Masters</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- License to practice&nbsp;from Nutritionists &amp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Dieticians Council</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provision of nutritional counseling and support&nbsp;to patients and their families/caregivers; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Porters/patient navigators</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training in customer&nbsp;service&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- First aid Training&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Ferrying of patients between service points&nbsp;within the facility</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Quality Assurance&nbsp;Officer/ Safety&nbsp;health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>A designated Quality&nbsp;Assurance Officer/&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Safety health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Liaise with all departments to ensure safety &amp;&nbsp;quality assurance is embedded in their processes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Infection Prevention and Control</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and Certification in IPC</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>-Monitor the rate of infections</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure proper waste management</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure proper use of PPE</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure hand hygiene compliance</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Supportive Human Resource</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Human resource category&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Minimum Qualifications&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Required staff establishment (number)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical Officers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MBCHB</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by KMPDB - Training&nbsp;and certification in&nbsp;chemotherapy handling and administration</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Health education; screening activities; assess,&nbsp;prescribe, administer subsequent cancer treatment under supervision of an oncologist; participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical Officers in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Higher National&nbsp;Diploma in Clinical&nbsp;Medicine Oncology.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by the Clinical Officers&nbsp;Council</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Health education; screening activities; assess,prescribe and administer subsequent cancer&nbsp;treatment under supervision of an oncologist;&nbsp;participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurses - Palliative&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>care</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Specialized Palliative&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>care nursing - Higher&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Diploma, MSc Nursing&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>or an accredited Palliative program&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of K</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the palliative&nbsp;care services in the facility; nursing care to cancer patients in the MDT; comprehensive patient&nbsp;assessments; Pain and Symptom management;&nbsp;Management of treatment side effects; Patient&nbsp;navigation activities; initiating , organizing and&nbsp;facilitating family conferences and advance care&nbsp;planning; end of life and bereavement care;&nbsp;clinical research in palliative care; advocacy;&nbsp;mentorship and teaching; policy formulation&nbsp;and implementation</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Pharmaceutical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>technologists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma/Higher&nbsp;National diploma in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Pharmacy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Enrolled to Practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by PPB&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and certification in chemotherapy handling and administration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Preparation of chemotherapy medications&nbsp;under supervision of a clinical pharmacist; research; supply chain management of oncology&nbsp;commodities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Pharmacists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Degree in pharmacy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to Practice&nbsp;by PPB&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and certification in chemotherapy&nbsp;handling and administration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Preparation of chemotherapy medications under supervision of a clinical pharmacist; member of MDT; research; supply chain management&nbsp;of oncology commodities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>','2022-07-18 09:42:57','2022-07-18 09:43:40'),(18,19,'Chemotherapy Equipment','<p>Equipment must have service contracts and appropriate measures for plans for preventive maintenance purposes and provide service stickers showing dates for last service and next service due dates. Elements that are important for the life of the equipment and for safety shall be addressed early in the planning stage and should be included in contractual forms, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Compliance with quality and safety standards</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Acceptance tests and conditions to correct deficiencies revealed during acceptance</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Warranty conditions</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Enforceable assurances on availability of maintenance support (technical and financial), manufacturer support, manuals and spare parts</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Training of all users and keep documentation of the same</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>Acceptance testing and commissioning</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Commissioning is done by the manufacturer or his representative, Biomedical Engineer and the Clinical Pharmacist. A record keeping system should also be in place. After commissioning has been completed, the specific tests needed for ongoing quality control and safety assurance will need to be carried out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chemotherapy Unit equipment</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chemotherapy administration area</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chemotherapy chairs</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Assorted hospital beds&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bedside cabinets&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Wheelchairs</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hazardous drug spill kit&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Infusion pumps</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>4-hooked mobile drip stands&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Lockable cabinets&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Crash cart for emergency/resuscitation including ambu-bags and masks for appropriate ages</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Suction machine&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oxygen &amp; oxygen masks</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Weighing scale</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Heightometer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Vital signs monitor including sphygmomanometer, thermometer, pulse oximeter Measuring Cylinders</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stretchers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Procedure trolleys</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Portable examination lamps</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Audio-visual equipment &ndash;Television</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clock</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>ICT equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Chemotherapy reconstitution area-needs to be lockable&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>A biosafety cabinet, class 2B2 and above (must have a exhauster fitted 2 meters above the building roof)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hazardous drug spill kit&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Lockable cabinets&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Steel / granite working surface area&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>An eye wash area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Air conditioner&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Oncology Pharmacy</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pharmaceutical Refrigerator with temperature monitors for oncology medicines</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Lockable cabinets</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Weighing balance</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Measuring Cylinders</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Secure storage</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Steel / granite working surface</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Reference books (e.g. Martindale, other Pharmacopoeias)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Pharmacy consultation room</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Furniture</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chairs</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Desk</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Screening</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>HPV test machines and kits</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>PAP smear kits</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>VIA/VILI reagents and commodities,&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical breast exams</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Fecal occult blood test</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Digital rectal exam</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Cryotherapy and thermal ablation with the appropriate staff</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Consultation room</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Equipment to take vital signs &ndash; BP machine, thermometer,&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Examination table</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Furniture:</p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Desk</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Chair</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Shelves</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Availability of</p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Computer</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Printer</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Scanner</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Health Management Information Service</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chaplaincy and Counseling</p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>IEC materials</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Information on nutrition, sexual dysfunction and healthy lifestyle</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Palliative Care &amp; survivorship Unit</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Furniture&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Examination couch</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Storage cabinets and desks</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chairs</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dressing trolleys</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Drip stands</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>BP machine</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Thermometers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Weighing scales</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Infusion/syringe pumps</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Electronics</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Printer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Rehabilitation unit</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Appropriate rehabilitation equipment and commodities e.g. Lymphedema stockings, stoma bags, prostheses etc</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Cancer registry office</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Lockable designated Office space</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Filing shelves&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computer with internet connectivity</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Furniture</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Working top</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Notice board</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-18 09:47:35','2022-07-18 09:47:35'),(19,20,'Chemotherapy Physical Infrastructure','<p>The cancer centre shall ensure the physical infrastructure meets the following requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient flow</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Capacity for electricity, water, power backup, space</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safety considerations &ndash; fire</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separation of adult from paediatric management areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disability infrastructure in all areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Maintenance considerations</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chemotherapy Unit Services Areas</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient registration and reception area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Triage room/observation room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Procedure rooms&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Counselling room&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waiting area for patients/caregivers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Designated Consultation room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chemotherapy administration area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oncology pharmacy</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chemo holding/receiving station in close proximity to the chemo administration area-with shelves, work tops, a hand washing area and hooks</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>At least one isolation room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Emergency room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Storage area for hazardous chemotherapy drugs with appropriate ventilation. Ideally, storage areas should have negative air pressure in relation to surrounding areas and have 12 air changes per hour</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chemotherapy reconstitution area should be large enough to contain a bio-safety cabinet</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Staff changing area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Staff room/conference room&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pantry room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate staff and patients rest rooms&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Sluice room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Storage facility for cytotoxic waste and other wastes</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disposal facilities for cytotoxic and other wastes Eye wash station/shower</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Waste Management</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Modern incinerator with combustion capacity above 1200oC</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waste Holding Area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-18 09:48:48','2022-07-18 09:48:48'),(20,21,'Surgical Oncology Operational Considerations','<h3><strong>1.1 Service Norms</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The National Guidelines for Cancer Management shall form the basis for clinical management at the facility.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The centre or unit must have NCI-K approved protocols for diagnosis and treatment of all malignancies they manage founded on sound scientific principles and evidence-based medicine which must be accessible to the prescribers, pharmacists and nurses at the centre at all times.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The protocols must be updated as appropriate and be readily available for inspection when needed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The centre or unit shall also commit to quality improvement, supporting cancer research and improving the training and mentoring of health care e. The centre or unit shall have infrastructure in place to be able to carry out cancer registration and reporting to the National Cancer Registry and KHIS.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.2 Service Delivery Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Every cancer centre shall:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Formulate and prominently display a service charter that details the roles and responsibilities of both the patient and the centre.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide integrated and multidisciplinary care&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Prioritize coordination and planning for professionals to help facilitate access to care at other levels of care, including awareness creation, screening/early detection, case management and appropriate downward referrals.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a reasonable time frame &ndash; definitive/tissue diagnosis should be done preferably within 2 weeks and the initiation of appropriate treatment within a month of diagnosis.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The recommended time frame between diagnosis and Surgery should be at least 120 days.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Follow evidence-based protocols and guidelines.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have informed consent obtained prior to all procedures including treatments. In case of a minor, a parent/guardian shall give consent. The information prior to consenting shall be provided in a manner easily understandable by the patient. The rights of the child should be prioritized.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish clear navigation systems to enable patients&rsquo; access to services.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Design patient-tracking systems for patient follow-up throughout the continuum of care.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Develop standard operating procedures for every service being provided</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.3 Clinical considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide cancer management that is holistic and patient-centred for best care outcomes.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Before initiation of treatment, clearly define and communicate the goals of care to the patient in accordance with a patient care plan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide the patient the right to detailed information on his/her condition, treatment options including clinical trials, side effects, expected outcome and prognosis.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow the patient the right to seek a second or additional opinion before consenting to initiation of treatment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all aspects of carefully documented, stored and easily retrievable.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow access of patients to their records as well as laboratory samples when needed&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Comprehensively document patient history</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.4 Multi-disciplinary Tumor Boards</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Definition; the multidisciplinary expert team that should manage cancer patients in a consultative approach</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;The cancer centre shall:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish multidisciplinary teams (MDTs)/tumor boards which shall guide and direct cancer management&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have MDTs meet regularly and have participation from all relevant disciplines depending on the cancer case and the level of care&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all complex cases discussed by a multidisciplinary team&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have an MDT coordinator who will organize for meetings, keep records of discussions and provide reports on cancer patient management&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Utilize technology to convene virtual MDT discussions with proper documentation</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>It consists of different experts including &ndash; medical oncologist, radiation/clinical oncologist, surgeon, pathologist, palliative physician and specialists, oncology pharmacist, oncology nurse, radiologist, interventional radiologist, haematologist, medical physicist, radiation therapist/therapy radiographer, medical laboratory technologists specialized in different laboratory disciplines.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.5 Diagnostic imaging</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(i) Incorporate clinical findings in conducting diagnostic imaging modalities&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(ii) Consider image-guided diagnostics where applicable</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(iii) Use a standard protocol for conducting imaging procedures</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(iv) Use internationally and locally recognized standards and guidelines for the safe installation, operation and use of imaging equipment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(v) Use a standard imaging diagnostic reporting protocol&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(vi) Outsource/provide access to an accredited imaging diagnostic facility</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.6 Nursing Considerations&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:-</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Provide oncology and palliative nursing care for the entire continuum of care(Prevention, Awareness, screening, early detection, diagnosis, treatment, survivorship and end of life care, bereavement).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Support the coordinating role of oncology and palliative care nurses in the&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>care team and community linkage for cancer patients</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.7 Surgical Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:-</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have Surgical site marking protocol implemented (standard site identification process, patient involved in marking, and marking done by the one doing procedure.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a Safe surgery checklist (evidence of use for verifying correct site, correct procedure, correct patient; availability of informed consent; and equipment needed are on hand, correct, and functional) See checklist <a href=\"about:blank\">Resources\\Safe surgery checklist.pdf</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide Evidence that facility has an active process of monitoring safe surgical checklist compliance.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ensure the organization uses a &ldquo;time-out&rdquo; procedure just before starting a surgical procedure.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Facilitate patients to access surgical diagnosis and treatment for solid malignancies through a multidisciplinary team approach.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Where tissue is obtained for histological examination, have the surgeon observe the SOP for histology specimen handling, storage and transport.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have surgical treatment offered conforming to internationally recognized, evidence-based surgical-oncological practices</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.8 Palliative Care and Survivorship Considerations&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Provide palliative care from the point of cancer diagnosis and at all times throughout the course of illness.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Integrate palliative care with other health services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Prioritize and provide effective relief of pain and other distressing symptoms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Provide timely rehabilitative and supportive services.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Facilitate formation of patient support groups.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Establish survivorship programs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Adhere to the National Palliative Care Policy and the National Palliative Care&nbsp;Guideline.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.9 Equipment Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Have all the facilities and equipment registered and licensed for safe and effective conduct of its services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have access to a qualified biomedical engineer, who is ultimately responsible for ensuring that all equipment are in proper working condition and that the necessary safety devices are fitted and in working order.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Maintain service contracts and schedules of service with the contracted service providers to ensure regular servicing as per the manufacturer&rsquo;s instructions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Ensure equipment compliance with relevant regulations according to the appropriate governing regulatory body.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Ensure safe disposal of obsolete or unserviceable equipment as guided by the relevant regulatory body.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.10 Referral Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Develop patient referral SOPs which conform to the national referral guidelines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Properly document referrals to and away from the facility.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Promote upward, downward and horizontal referral where appropriate.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Facilitate referrals for specialized services that are unavailable at the centre to facilities that are accessible and are accredited by the relevant regulatory body.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Assess patients for fitness to travel and provide necessary supportive mechanisms (ambulance, nurse, oxygen supply) before referral.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Provide proper patient counseling on cancer, tests to be done, costs implications and expected treatment before referral.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Refer a patient to the right specialist for further management if a service outside oncology services is required</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.11 Quality Assurance</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Establish a Quality Assurance Programme (QAP) that is adequately supervised and provides reports to NCI Kenya as required.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have risk assessment measures in place with objectives and systematic monitoring and evaluation so as to identify problems and system failures and guide the necessary action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Have regular morbidity and mortality meetings to identify specific clinical performance indicators.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.12 Infection Prevention and Control</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Oncology patients are at increased infection risk due to immunosuppression and frequent exposure to healthcare settings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a hospital&rsquo;s infection prevention and control program must be in accordance with the WHO Practical Guidelines for Infection Control.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have hand-washing facilities for staff readily available. Hand sanitizers should be provided at every work station.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide a designated sluicing area for linen generated in the Surgical area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have isolation rooms and practice barrier nursing by ensuring PPEs are available and easily accessible.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide decontamination and sterilization areas. (The decontaminant, sodium hypochlorite 5%)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.13 Occupational health and safety</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Implement the Occupational, Health &amp; Safety (OSH) Act in the workplace.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide safety and health training at least once every 3 years.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Be subject to annual inspection by the local regulatory body and adhere to the basic safety standards as set by the regulatory body.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disclose labeling laws for identification and classification of chemicals by types of hazards, including medication labels and safety data sheets.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a system for incidents monitoring and management at the workplace.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have programs to monitor and support employee performance, mental health, work-life balance and put in place debriefing programs.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.14 Waste Management</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide waste segregation and disposal amenities.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Conduct regular capacity building on waste disposal for all healthcare providers including support staff.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide appropriate PPEs for handling clinical waste</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.15 Emergency Medical Care&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have facilities and human resources to handle Surgical Oncology emergencies.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ensure medical staffs are trained in BLS/ACLS.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stabilize the patient and expeditiously refer for emergency management where applicable.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Be well equipped with resuscitation commodities and equipment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.16 Adverse Events</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Any adverse event that occurs as a result of the surgery must be documented, discussed internally and reported to the relevant regulatory bodies such as the Pharmacy and Poisons Board, relevant regulatory body and the NCI-K.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.17 Death of a Patient</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Document all deaths occurring whilst patients are undergoing treatment appropriately.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Offer bereavement support to the family.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Have periodic mortality meetings where cancer deaths are discussed by a multidisciplinary team</p>','2022-07-18 09:57:05','2022-07-18 13:34:16'),(21,22,'Surgical Oncology Physical Infrastructure','<p>The cancer centre shall ensure the physical infrastructure meets the following requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient flow</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Capacity for electricity, water, power backup, space</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safety considerations &ndash; fire</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separation of adult from pediatric management areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disability infrastructure in all areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Maintenance considerations</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.1 All departments and units</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>For centres operating within the precincts of a hospital, it can utilize similar facilities within the hospital. For stand-alone centres, these services must be provided for:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>a. Appropriate space for the following administrative services:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Administration</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Finance</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Transport</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iv. Supply chain management</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;v. Laundry</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;vi. Healthcare waste management, including hazardous drug waste, a Lockable holding area, proper segregation and disposal, MOUs with disposal companies</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;vii. Conference room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ix. Reception area</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>b. Utilities</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate patient and staff changing rooms</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate staff and patients rest rooms</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Staff room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.2 Health records and information &ndash; registration area</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Office space</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Filing room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Use of NACARE system for reporting is required using secure internet.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.3 Other supportive services</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Provision for day care services where applicable</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cancer registry office</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Office space</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Filing room</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.4 Surgical Oncology Unit</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Patient registration and reception area</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Waiting area for patients and caregivers</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Consultation room&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Triage/observation room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Counseling room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Procedure room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Pharmacy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>h. Operating theatre capable of handling minor and major surgical procedures with a Patient receiving room and a patient recovery room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>i. Nutrition</p>\r\n\r\n<p>j. Palliative care</p>\r\n\r\n<p>k. Medical Laboratory Unit</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Support from;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Diagnostic radiology unit</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pathology unit</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Blood banking</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Critical care unit</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Rehabilitation centres&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Endoscopy services</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Morgue services</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.5 Inpatient oncology wards</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Separate female, male, adolescents, geriatric and pediatric wards&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Side room facilities for ward reviews of post-operative wounds, minor procedures, and emergency resuscitation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Isolation rooms for patients with infectious conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Waste management facilities</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.6 Palliative Care and Survivorship Unit</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Patient registration and reception area</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Waiting area for patients/caregivers</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Counseling room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Procedure room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Consultation room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Community room large enough to accommodate support groups</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Support services</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Pharmacy</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Nutrition</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Chaplaincy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iv. Counseling&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;v. Rehabilitative unit</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Pediatrics play area</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Nutrition counseling rooms</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.7 Design and construction requirements</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The design of any surgery department revolves around environmental control, traffic control, and the desire to prevent surgical site infection (SSI). <a href=\"about:blank\">Resources\\Surgical Operating Theatres Standards.docx</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Consult the Services of a registered Architectural and structural Engineering firms, with expertise in construction of health care facilities, for the design and construction.</p>','2022-07-18 10:02:47','2022-07-18 13:42:18'),(22,23,'Surgical Oncology Equipment','<p>Equipment must have service contracts and appropriate measures for plans for preventive maintenance purposes and provide service stickers showing dates for last service and next service due dates.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Elements that are important for the life of the equipment and for safety shall be addressed early in the planning stage and should be included in contractual forms, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Compliance with quality and safety standards</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Acceptance tests and conditions to correct deficiencies revealed during acceptance</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Warranty conditions</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Enforceable assurances on availability of maintenance support</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;(technical and financial), manufacturer support, manuals and spare parts</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Training of all users and keep documentation of the same</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Acceptance, testing and commissioning</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Commissioning is done by the manufacturer or his representative, Biomedical Engineer and the Surgeon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A record keeping system should also be in place. After commissioning has been completed, the specific tests needed for ongoing quality control and safety assurance will need to be carried out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Equipment Donation</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The donations should be guided by the principles developed by the WHO.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There should be effective communication between the donor, the recipient authority and, whenever possible, the end-user, before, during and after the donation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Surgical Oncology Unit Equipment</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Fully equipped major and minor theatres with standard anaesthetic, surgical and interventional equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Receiving area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pre-operative room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Post-operative room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Scrubbing room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Changing room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waiting area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Fully equipped endoscopy suite</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>In-patient Surgical Wards</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Wards</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Beds</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Wheelchairs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Trolleys</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iv. Consumable and reusable equipment for IV and medication equipment</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Phlebotomy equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bedside Cabinets</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurses&rsquo; station with cabinets/shelves</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>BP Monitors</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Thermometers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Weighing scale</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Heightometer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Crash cart</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waste segregation bins</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medicine Cabinets&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Consumables cabinets</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Decommissioning requirements</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Safety assessment survey report of the hazards involved during decommissioning exercise. Have a Decommissioning Plan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Have a hazardous waste management, transport and disposal plan for the decommissioning.</p>','2022-07-18 10:54:49','2022-07-18 13:42:46'),(23,24,'Surgical Oncology Human Resource','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Anesthesiologists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Biomedical engineer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical Lab personnel&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Cancer Registrar</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical Officer anesthetist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurse anesthetist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Gynaecology Oncologist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Housekeeping staff</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Interventional radiologists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical Officers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical social worker</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurse &ndash; General with theatre experience</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nutritionist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical/ hemato-onco, Pediatric, Radiation Oncologists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Surgeons</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Q/A</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>IPC</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical Counsellors</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Physiotherapists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pharmacists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurse-palliative care</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Occupational therapists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Core human resource</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Human resource category&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Minimum Qualifications&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Anesthesiologists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMed in Anesthesia&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management;&nbsp;in charge of ICU/HDU</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED and a fellowship in medical oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;as an oncologist by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer&nbsp;centre/facility; assessment, initiation, review of&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>patients cancer treatment; chair MDTs meetings;&nbsp;participate in clinical research in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Pediatric Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED Paediatrics&nbsp;with fellowship in paediatric oncology</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer&nbsp;centre/facility; cancer diagnosis; assessment,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>initiation, review of paediatric patients cancer&nbsp;treatment; chair MDTs meetings; participate in&nbsp;clinical research in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Gynaecology&nbsp;Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED Obs/Gyne with&nbsp;a fellowship in Gynae&nbsp;Oncology.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;as a Gynae oncologist&nbsp;by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer&nbsp;centre/facility; assessment, initiation, surgical&nbsp;management and review of gynaecological&nbsp;cancer patients; participate in MDTs meetings;&nbsp;participate in clinical research in oncology;&nbsp;screening for gynae cancers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation oncologists/clinical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED/Fellowship in&nbsp;radiation oncology/</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Clinical oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;as an oncologist by&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; in charge of radiotherapy treatment;&nbsp;assessment, initiation, review of patients cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>treatment and patient follow up; treatment&nbsp;planning; chair MDTs meetings; participate in&nbsp;clinical research in oncology; participates in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>equipment procurement&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Haemato-oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED/Fellowship&nbsp;with specialization in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>hemato-oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; cancer diagnosis; assessment, initiation, review of patients cancer treatment; chair&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>MDTs meetings; participate in clinical research&nbsp;in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical Officer&nbsp;anesthetist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Higher Diploma in&nbsp;Anesthesia&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by the Clinical Officers Council</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management&nbsp;in consultation with the anesthesiologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer registrars</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Degree/diploma&nbsp;holder in Health Records &amp; information.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>registration from&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>African Cancer Registry Network (AFCRN)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>approved provider</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer data abstraction, maintenance of cancer&nbsp;patients records and participation in cancer&nbsp;research</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical counselors&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma/degree in&nbsp;psychological counseling.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- License to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>from relevant body</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Counseling of patients and their caregivers/families on cancer; patient navigation; research;member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Housekeeping&nbsp;staff</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Relevant training in&nbsp;housekeeping</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training in safe handling of hazardous&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>products</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Handling of waste and cleaning</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical social&nbsp;worker</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma or bachelors&nbsp;in social Sciences</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Assessment of socio-economic background of&nbsp;patients; Contact tracing; patient navigation;&nbsp;research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse - General(adult care and&nbsp;pediatric care)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Have Theatre experience/Training in Theatre Nurs</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Providing nursing care to cancer patients in&nbsp;collaboration with other members of the MDT,&nbsp;in all areas of cancer treatment; health education; screening activities; participate in clinical&nbsp;research in oncology; screening activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nutritionists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or degree in&nbsp;Nutrition&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- License to practice&nbsp;from Nutritionists &amp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Dieticians Council</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provision of nutritional counseling and support&nbsp;to patients and their families/caregivers; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Quality Assurance&nbsp;Officer/ Safety&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>A designated Quality&nbsp;Assurance Officer/&nbsp;Safety health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Liaise with all departments to ensure safety &amp;&nbsp;quality assurance is embedded in their processes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Infection Prevention and Control</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and Certification in IPC</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>-Monitor the rate of infections</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure proper waste management</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure proper use of PPE</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure hand hygiene compliance</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Biomedical engineering officers&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(medical engineers or technologist)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or bachelors&nbsp;in medical engineering&nbsp;and trained on maintenance of cancer equipment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered by the&nbsp;Association of Medical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Engineers of Kenya&nbsp;(AMEK) or relevant&nbsp;international body</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Installation, maintaining service contracts and&nbsp;equipment documentation and regular maintenance of cancer equipment at t</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Pharmacists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Degree in pharmacy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to Practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by PPB&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and certification in chemotherapy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>handling and administration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Preparation of chemotherapy medications under supervision of a clinical pharmacist; member of MDT; research; supply chain management&nbsp;of oncology commodities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Surgeons</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED Surgery or&nbsp;equivalent and/or specialization in Oncology.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of a surgical cancer&nbsp;facility; assessment, conduct surgery and review&nbsp;of cancer patients after surgery; participate in&nbsp;research and MDT activities; patient referrals</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical Laboratory technologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or degree&nbsp;in Medical Laboratory&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(Bsc) or related discipline&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;- Registered and&nbsp;licensed by KMLTTB&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Each section of the&nbsp;laboratory to be headed by a medical laboratory technologist with&nbsp;a diploma in Medical&nbsp;Laboratory Sciences in&nbsp;the disciplines</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;- Clinical Cytology/Histopathology, Biochemistry, Microbiology, Immunology,&nbsp;Molecular Sciences,&nbsp;Blood Transfusion/Haematology Sciences,&nbsp;Epidemiology, public&nbsp;health or virology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provide lab services, research; sample collection;&nbsp;safe waste disposal; relay of results</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Supportive Human Resource/Auxilliary/Adjunct</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Human resource category&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Minimum Qualifications&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical Officers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MBCHB</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by KMPDB - Training&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>and certification in&nbsp;chemotherapy handling and administration</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Health education; screening activities; assess,&nbsp;prescribe, administer subsequent cancer treatment under supervision of an oncologist; participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurses - Palliative&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>care</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Specialized Palliative&nbsp;care nursing - Higher&nbsp;Diploma, MSc Nursing&nbsp;or an accredited Palliative program&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the palliative&nbsp;care services in the facility; nursing care to cancer patients in the MDT; comprehensive patient&nbsp;assessments; Pain and Symptom management;&nbsp;Management of treatment side effects; Patient&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>navigation activities; initiating , organizing and&nbsp;facilitating family conferences and advance care&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>planning; end of life and bereavement care;&nbsp;clinical research in palliative care; advocacy;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>mentorship and teaching; policy formulation&nbsp;and implementation</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse anesthetist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Higher diploma in&nbsp;anesthesia</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed by NCK</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management&nbsp;in consultation with the anesthesiologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Interventional&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>radiologists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED in radiology</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Fellowship in interventional Radiology</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by KMDPB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>In-charge of interventional diagnostic radiology&nbsp;activities including biopsy collection; research;&nbsp;member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Occupational&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>therapists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma, higher diploma or bachelors in&nbsp;occupational therapy</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provision of rehabilitative services to patients;&nbsp;research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Physiotherapists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma, higher diploma or bachelors in&nbsp;physiotherapy</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provision of rehabilitative services to patients;&nbsp;research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>','2022-07-18 11:05:01','2022-07-18 13:43:12'),(24,25,'Radiotherapy Operational Considerations','<h3><strong>1.1 Procedure for designation as a radiotherapy Cancer Centre</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A facility that plans to offer radiotherapy cancer service must apply for designation to NCI Kenya and should adhere to the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The proposal for the radiotherapy Cancer Centre designation shall specify the objectives of the cancer management program, the range of services to be provided, the approximate number of patients to be treated, and the physical infrastructure, equipment, human resources and operational management resources, as laid out in this document.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The facility will be issued with a comprehensive checklist of the components required for a radiotherapy Cancer Centre before it submits the application for designation.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Proposals for a radiotherapy Cancer Centre designation shall be submitted to the Chief Executive Officer National Cancer Institute Kenya (NCI-K), together with the application form for approval not less than 90 days before the intended commencement of operations of the cancer center.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Only upon final approval by the NCI-K will a facility be designated as a radiotherapy Cancer Centre. NCI-K will ensure that the Centre maintains the services and standards outlined in these Guidelines in order to retain this designation. The certificate of radiotherapy Cancer Management Centre designation (based on the service (s) to be offered) will be issued by NCI-K and shall be displayed at the facility.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>NCI-K will conduct inspections and accreditation after every two years to ensure compliance to the guideline, however NCI-K can conduct adhoc inspections to ensure standards are maintained.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.2 Service Norms for Radiotherapy Cancer Centres</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The National Guidelines for radiotherapy Cancer Management shall form the basis for clinical management at the facility.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The radiotherapy centre or unit must have NCI-K approved protocols for treatment of all malignancies they manage founded on sound scientific principles and evidence-based medicine which must be accessible to the radiotherapy clinical team at the centre at all times.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The protocols must be updated as appropriate, readily available and displayed.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The radiotherapy centre or unit shall also commit to quality improvement, supporting cancer research and improving the training and mentoring of health care&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The radiotherapy centre or unit shall have infrastructure in place to be able to carry out cancer registration and notification to the National Cancer Registry.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.3 Service Delivery Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Every radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Formulate and prominently display a service charter that details the roles and responsibilities of both the patient and the centre.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide integrated and multidisciplinary care</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Prioritize coordination and planning for professionals to help facilitate access to care at other levels of care, including awareness creation,screening/early detection, case management and appropriate referrals.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a reasonable time frame &ndash; Radiotherapy treatments should commence &nbsp; within 2 weeks post treatment planning completion.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Follow evidence-based protocols and guidelines.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have informed consent obtained prior to all radiotherapy treatments. In case of a minor, a parent/guardian shall give consent. The information prior to consenting shall be provided in a manner easily understandableby the patient. The rights of the child should be prioritized.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish clear navigation systems to enable patients&rsquo; access to services.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Design patient-tracking systems for patient follow-up throughout the continuum of care.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Develop standard operating procedures for every service being provided.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.4 Clinical Radiotherapy Management Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide cancer management that is holistic and patient-centred for best care outcomes&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Before initiation of treatment, clearly define and communicate the goals of care to the patient in accordance with a patient care plan</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide the patient the right to detailed information on his/her condition, treatment options including clinical trials, side effects, expected outcome and prognosis.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow the patient the right to seek a second or additional opinion before consenting to initiation of treatment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all aspects of carefully documented, stored and easily retrievable.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow access of patients to their records as well as medical reports when needed</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Comprehensively document patient history</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><br />\r\n<strong>1.5 Multi-disciplinary Tumor Boards</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish multidisciplinary teams (MDTs)/tumour boards which shall guide and direct cancer management</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have MDTs meet regularly and have participation from all relevant disciplines depending on the cancer case and the level of care</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all complex cases discussed by a multidisciplinary team</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have an MDT coordinator who will organize for meetings, keep records of discussions and&nbsp; provide reports on cancer patient management</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The outcomes of the MDT&rsquo;s discussion must be documented in the patient file.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Utilize technology to convene virtual MDT discussions with proper documentation of the same&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.6 CT Simulation Capacity Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pretreatment&nbsp; imaging</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Incorporate clinical findings in conducting pretreatment imaging modalities</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use a dedicated wide bore CT simulator with aperture of not less than 70cm preferably 80cm</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Reference room lasers should be installed&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use a standard&nbsp; simulation protocol for pretreatment Imaging</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use internationally and locally recognized standards and guidelines for the safe installation, operation and use of imaging equipment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Incorporate appropriate and site specific immobilization devices&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Incase CT simulator is not available, a conventional simulator must be available.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Radiation Oncology Considerations</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy centre shall:<br />\r\na) Provide radiation oncology services in adherence to IAEA and local regulatory body guidelines including radiation safety protection.<br />\r\nb) Fully document all ionizing radiation therapeutic applications and maintain proper records for treatment planning simulation, isodose distribution plan, dosimetry, brachytherapy and physics documentation.<br />\r\nc) Deliver the most novel and advanced technologies available for radiation oncology. These technologies should be cost-eﬀective, efficient, upgradable and practical.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d) Provide adequate information to patients receiving radiotherapy regarding the procedure to be done.<br />\r\ne) For brachytherapy source, acquire relevant licenses from KNRA that guides source shipping, handling, storage and disposal upon depletion of radioisotopes including radiation safety program designed for the practice.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.7 Occupational health and safety considerations:</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy central shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Be subject to annual inspection by the local regulatory body and adhere to the basic safety standards as set by the regulatory body.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disclose labeling laws for identification and classification of radiation by types of hazards, including radiation labels and safety data sheets.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish a system for identification and surveillance of exposure: estimating the number of workers who come into contact with substances and are employed in occupations with increased carcinogenic risk, and reducing to minimum the number of workers exposed, the duration of exposure and the degree of exposure, and establishing an appropriate system of records.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ensure medical surveillance applies to all healthcare workers in the radiotherapy unit and includes assessment and documentation of symptom complaints, physical findings &amp; laboratory values</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide personal protective equipment for workers and decontamination facilities in the workplace.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish/develop guidelines and recommendations for proper use and handling of radio-active substances and training packages for healthcare workers.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a system of monitoring services at the workplace and assess occupational exposures.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Empower workers by providing them with access to information about their exposures and risks.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have programs to monitor employee performance, mental health, work-life balance and put in place debriefing programs.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.8 Waste Management</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dispose radioactive waste produced in the process of the diagnosis and treatment of cancer in accordance to international and relevant local guidelines.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have written policies and SOPs for hazardous waste describing requirements for the segregation, packaging, labeling, collection, transportation and storage of waste within the facility.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide waste disposal amenities and commodities.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Conduct regular capacity building on waste disposal for all healthcare providers including support staff.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide appropriate PPEs for handling hazardous waste.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Minimize the risk of contaminating the local water supply and/or soil with radio-active waste. Hazardous materials shall never be discarded into waste water (sink or toilet) or into a landfill.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.9 Emergency Medical Care</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Have facilities and human resources to handle oncologic and palliative care emergencies.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Develop and display SOPs on emergency care.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Ensure medical staffs are trained in BLS/ACLS.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Stabilize the patient and expeditiously refer for emergency management where applicable.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Be well equipped with resuscitation commodities and equipment.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.10 Adverse Events</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Document, discuss internally, put in place mitigation measures then report to the relevant regulatory body any adverse event that occurs as a result of cancer diagnosis or treatment.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><br />\r\n<strong>1.11 Death of a Patient</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Document all deaths occurring whilst patients are undergoing treatment appropriately.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Offer bereavement support to the family.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have periodic mortality meetings where cancer deaths are discussed by a multidisciplinary team.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-18 11:15:05','2022-07-18 11:15:05'),(25,26,'Radiotherapy Human Resource','<p>The human resource requirements for the chemotherapy centre are as follows with core staff and supportive staff</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Human resource category</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Minimum Qualifica- tions</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Staff Establishment</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Anesthesiologists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MMed in Anesthesis</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p>(Licensed to practice by&nbsp; KMPDB)</p>\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management; in charge of ICU/HDU</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Biomedical engineering officers (medical engineers or technologist)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or bachelors in medical engineering and trained on maintenance of cancer equipment.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered by the Association of Medical Engineers of Kenya (AMEK) or relevant international body</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Installation, maintaining service contracts and equipment documentation and regular maintenance of cancer equipment at the&nbsp; facility</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer registrars</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Degree/diploma holder in Health Records &amp; information management (registered by AMRO-K or by an established HRIM Board)</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in cancer registration and notification by NCI-K or NCI-K approved provider.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer data abstraction, notification/data entry and maintenance of cancer patients records and participation in cancer research.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Reception and registration, storage, filing and retrieval, clinic preparation, file tracing, report generation/sharing and editing files.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical counselors</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma/degree in psychological counseling.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice from relevant body</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Counseling of patients and their caregivers/ families on cancer; patient navigation; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical Officer anesthetist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Higher Diploma in Anesthesia</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice by the Clinical Officers Council</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management in consultation with the&nbsp; anesthesiologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinically qualified Medical Physicists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Bsc in physics with postgraduate training in medical physics or Msc Medical Physics with clinical training in radiotherapy physics</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Responsible for equipment selection, specifications, acceptance, delivery, design of installations and shielding requirements, com- missioning and management for radiotherapy, diagnostics and nuclear medicine; Treatment planning in collaboration with the radiation oncologist; safety assessment, establishment, measurement and supervision of QA for radiotherapy and nuclear medicine devices; radiation protection and safety; dose calibration and instrumentation; technical supervision of maintenance; research and innovation of new medical devices; teaching &ndash; radiation protection &amp; users of equipment.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Housekeeping staff</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Relevant training in housekeeping</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Training in safe handling of hazardous products</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Handling of waste and cleaning</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical Officers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MBCHB</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice by&nbsp; KMPDB - Training and certification in chemotherapy handling and administration</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Health education; screening activities; assess, prescribe, administer subsequent cancer treatment under supervision of an oncologist; participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical social worker</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or&nbsp; bachelors in social Sciences</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Assessment of socio-economic background of patients; Contact tracing; patient navigation; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Patient navigators</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Training in customer service</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Training in basic life support for non-medical providers</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Receiving and guiding patients</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse anesthetist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Higher diploma in anesthesia</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed by NCK</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management in consultation with the&nbsp; anesthesiologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Oncology nurse&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MSc Nursing or equivalent focused in oncology Nursing or HND oncology nursing&nbsp;</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya (NCK)</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; providing nursing care to cancer patients; health education; screening activities; part of the MDT; comprehensive patient assessments; symptom management; treatment side effects management; patient navigation activities; clinical research in oncology; advocacy; mentorship and teaching; policy formulation and implementation; screening&nbsp; activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>General nurse</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or Degree in Nursing</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>Certification in chemotherapy handling and administration (those working in chemotherapy units)</li>\r\n				<li>Undergone an appropriate induction pro- gram in cancer management</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Providing nursing care to cancer patients in collaboration with other members of the MDT, in all areas of cancer treatment; health education; screening activities; participate in clinical research in oncology; screening&nbsp; activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse Manager</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>BSc Nursing with Specialized oncology nursing training,</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Additional qualification in admin and MSc is an added advantage</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>&nbsp;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Head of Nursing oncology services; Coordination, Directing and organization of patient care activities in the unit; Resource management and Budgeting; Staffing activities; Quality management; Reporting participate in MDTs meetings; Participate in clinical research; policy formulation, implementation and&nbsp; monitoring</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nutritionists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or degree in Nutrition</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>License to practice from Nutritionists &amp; Dieticians Council</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provision of nutritional counseling and support to patients and their families/caregivers; re- search; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation Safety Officer (RSO)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Advanced degree in Medical Physics, Health Physics, radiation physics or equivalent</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Supervised training for 6 months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Radiation Protection and Safety</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Psychologists (both adult and pediatric)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Degree in psychology.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>License to practice from relevant body</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Counseling of patients and their caregivers/ families on cancer; patient navigation; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Quality Assurance Officer/ Safety health officer</p>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Quality assurance officers</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Radiation Safety Officers</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Patient Safety officer</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p>Occupational safe- ty &amp; health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>A designated Quality Assurance Officer/ Safety health officer</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Liaise with all departments to ensure safety &amp; quality assurance is embedded in their processes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation oncologists/clinical oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MMED/Fellowship in radiation oncology/ Clinical oncology</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice as an oncologist by KMPDB</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; in charge of radiotherapy treatment; assessment, initiation, review of patients cancer treatment and patient follow up; treatment planning; chair MDTs meetings; participate in clinical research in oncology; participates in equipment procurement</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Paediatric Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MMED Paediatrics with fellowship in paediatric oncology</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice by&nbsp; KMPDB</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; cancer diagnosis; assessment, initiation, review of paediatric patients cancer treatment; chair MDTs meetings; participate in clinical research in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation Therapists (RTT) /Therapy radiographers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or higher diploma in radiation therapy</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Participate in treatment planning; administer radiotherapy&nbsp; treatment&nbsp; under&nbsp; supervision&nbsp; of the radio-oncologist; participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiotherapy Services Manager</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>The officer in charge to hold at least a bachelor&rsquo;s degree in therapy radiography</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>To head and coordinate radiotherapy services in the centre</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>','2022-07-18 11:20:01','2022-07-18 11:20:01'),(26,27,'Radiotherapy Equipment','<p>Equipment must have service contracts and appropriate measures for plans for preventive maintenance purposes and provide service stickers showing dates for last service and next service due dates. Elements that are important for the life of the equipment and for safety shall be addressed early in the planning stage and should be included in contractual forms, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Compliance with quality and safety standards</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Acceptance tests and conditions to correct deficiencies revealed during acceptance</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Warranty conditions</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Enforceable assurances on availability of maintenance support (technical and financial), manufacturer support, manuals and spare parts</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Training of all users and keep documentation of the same</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Acceptance testing and commissioning</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Radiation sources need to be safely received, registered and stored; radiation measurement equipment tested and calibrated; shielding properties of special rooms measured; and the radiation sources tested and calibrated. All major equipment will require commissioning including tele therapy machines, imaging machines (simulators), brachytherapy units and TPSs. A record keeping system should also be in place. After commissioning has been completed, the specific tests needed for ongoing quality control and safety assurance will need to be carried out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Commissioning requirements for Radiotherapy unit</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The process of Commissioning involves Pre-Commissioning and Trial run permission.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After completion of construction and installation, the applicant should approach the regulatory body for permission to carry out a trial run for commissioning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For this purpose, the applicant should submit the following to the regulatory body:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Acceptance Tests conducted on the following equipment;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation Protection Program (RPP).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Details regarding availability of qualified and trained manpower &ndash; operator(s), radio pharmacist(s)/radio-chemist(s) and a Board approved Radiological Safety Officer (RSO).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Personnel monitoring services for all radiation workers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Appropriate radiation measuring and monitoring Instruments</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Operational procedure manual</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safe handling tools and devices required for operation and maintenance of the medical cyclotron and auxiliary equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Security Plan</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Submit the Commissioning Test Report&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>After successful trial runs, the applicant becomes eligible for obtaining consent for trial operations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Decommissioning requirements</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>When the medical cyclotron is no longer to be used, the permission for decommissioning shall be obtained from the Radiation Protection Board. The licensee should apply for the decommissioning license and supply the Authority with the following;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safety assessment survey report of the radiological and non-radiological hazards involved during decommissioning exercise.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Decommissioning Plan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation Protection considerations for the decommissioning workers.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Public radiation protection consideration at vicinity.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Qualified Radiation safety supervisor designated for the exercise.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation safety equipment to be used for decommissioning.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radioactive waste management, transport and disposal plan for the decommissioning.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Site radiation decontamination and final radiation survey.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>The licensee shall submit a report on the completion of decommissioning, which includes among others; safe disposal of sources and personnel exposures received during decommissioning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>List of Equipment</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>External Beam Radiation Therapy.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Electronic Portal Imaging Device (EPID) photo imaging device for verification</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>High dose Rate (HDR) brachytherapy machine (afterloader)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>CT/Conventional treatment planning simulator complete with accessories</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dosimetry quality assurance equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation Safety monitoring devices and radiation safety checklists and reporting.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>ICT infrastructure and support</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Treatment planning system</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Standardized rulers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Two-way video cameras, with audio capability</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Appropriate shielding requirements of radiation sources</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>3-D water scan phantom</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Range of radiation dosimeters for measuring radiation doses</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Immobilization devices</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mould room equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provision for anaesthesia space and recovery if facility is to offer pediatric radiation therapy</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-18 11:39:45','2022-07-18 11:39:45'),(27,28,'Radiotherapy Physical Infrastructure','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The following section outlines the infrastructural considerations for different units. The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall ensure the physical infrastructure meets the following requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>A standard bunker for Linac</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Brachytherapy suite with a theatre</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>CT simulator room/conventional simulator room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Control room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Physics room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mould room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Administration area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Capacity for electricity, water, power backup, space</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safety considerations &ndash; fire</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disability friendly infrastructure in all areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Maintenance considerations</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Treatment planning room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Recovery area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waiting area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient Reception area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Triage area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nursing station</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Consultation room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Procedure room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Emergency room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nutrition and counselling room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate staff and patient changing rooms</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate male and female toilets for staff and patients</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Sluice room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Registry</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hand wash area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Storage area&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Conference room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Staff room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Laundry</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Holding area in case of a death</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Special considerations:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>For a radiotherapy with in-patient services, separate adult from pediatric unit.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>For pediatric services, dedicated child-friendly rooms should be provided.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-18 11:41:47','2022-07-18 11:42:07'),(28,29,'Nuclear Radiology Human Resource','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The human resource requirements for the chemotherapy centre are as follows with core staff and supportive staff</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Human Resource Category</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Minimum Education</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Specialized Training &amp; Role</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Staff Establishment</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cyclotron Operator(s)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Technical degree or equivalent e.g. BSc in Electrical/Mechanical/Instrumentation/ Bio-medical/Physics</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Supervised training for 6 months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>On the job training</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Radiation Protection and Safety</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Electrical and mechanical repairs</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Production Chemist (s)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma or BSc in Chemistry or equivalent</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>On the job training</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Supervised training for 6 months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Radiation Protection and Safety</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Quality Control Chemist (s)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma or BSc in Chemistry, biochemistry, pharmacy or equivalent</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>On the job training</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Supervised training for 6 months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Radiation Protection and Safety</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Experience in GMP</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Experience in target preparation</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Synthesis of radiotracers</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Training in laboratory operations</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation Safety Officer (RSO)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Advanced degree in Medical Physics, Health Physics, radiation physics or equivalent</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Supervised training for 6 months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Radiation Protection and Safety</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radio-pharmacist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Degree in pharmacy with post graduate training in radiation physics/radiopharmaceutical sciences</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Preparation &amp; dispensing of radio- pharmaceuticals</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Skills in aseptic manipulation &amp; safe handling of radioactive products</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Knowledge on analytical techniques for quality control</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Trained in GMP</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nuclear medicine physician</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MMed or equivalent in Nuclear medicine.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p>Licensed to practice by&nbsp; KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>In-charge of nuclear medicine department; supervision; allocation of duties; assess, prescribe, prepare &amp; administer radioisotopes ; diagnosis; interpretation &amp; reporting of tests; enforce radiation protection standards for patients &amp; staff; quality control of nuclear medicine services; training; research; waste management; equip- ment selection; MDT member</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nuclear medicine technologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Degree/diploma in nuclear medicine</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Obtains patient history &amp; describe procedure to patient; administer nuclear medicine treatment; prepare &amp; administer radiopharmaceuticals; monitors patient&rsquo;s condition during procedure; perform imaging procedures for diagnosis; analyze biological specimens in the lab; nuclear waste disposal; equipment&nbsp; calibration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinically qualified Medical Physicists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Bsc in physics with postgraduate training in medical physics or Msc Medical Physics with clinical training in radiotherapy physics</p>\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Responsible for equipment selection, specifications, acceptance, delivery, design of installations and shielding requirements, com- missioning and management for radiotherapy, diagnostics and nuclear medicine; Treatment planning in collaboration with the radiation oncologist; safety assessment, establishment, measurement and supervision of QA for radiotherapy and nuclear medicine devices; radiation protection and safety; dose calibration and instrumentation; technical supervision of maintenance; research and innovation of new medical devices; teaching &ndash; radiation protection &amp; users of equipment.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer registrars</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Degree/diploma holder in Health Records &amp; information management (registered by AMRO-K or by an established HRIM Board)</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in cancer registration and notification by NCI-K or NCI-K approved provider.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer data abstraction, notification/data entry and maintenance of cancer patients&rsquo; records and participation in cancer research.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Reception and registration, storage, filing and retrieval, clinic preparation, file tracing, report generation/sharing and editing files.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Qualified customer care</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Certificate in customer care</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Receiving and guiding patients</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>General nurse</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or Degree in Nursing</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>Certification in chemotherapy handling and administration (those working in chemotherapy units)</li>\r\n				<li>Undergone an appropriate induction program in cancer management/ OJT on nuclear medicine.</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Providing nursing care to cancer patients in collaboration with other members of the MDT, in all areas of cancer treatment; health education; screening activities; participate in clinical research in oncology; screening activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Patient navigators</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Receiving and guiding patients</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Housekeeping staff</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Relevant training in housekeeping</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Training in safe handling of hazardous products</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Handling of waste and cleaning</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>','2022-07-18 11:46:11','2022-07-18 11:46:53'),(29,30,'Nuclear Radiology Equipment','<p>Equipment must have service contracts and appropriate measures for plans for preventive maintenance purposes and provide service stickers showing dates for last service and next service due dates. Elements that are important for the life of the equipment and for safety shall be addressed early in the planning stage and should be included in contractual forms, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Compliance with quality and safety standards</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Acceptance tests and conditions to correct deficiencies revealed during acceptance</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Warranty conditions</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Enforceable assurances on availability of maintenance support (technical and financial), manufacturer support, manuals and spare parts</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Training of all users and keep documentation of the same</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>List of Equipment for Nuclear medicine Unit</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>PET/CT&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>SPECT</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dose calibrator</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hot cell</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Barcode generator</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>UPS</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stand by generator</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>HVAC</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chiller</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dosimetry and radiation safety equipment (dosimeters, isotope dose calibrators, scintillation counter, Portable contamination monitor/survey meter)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>ICT infrastructure and support</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Standardized rulers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Two-way video cameras, with audio capability</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Appropriate shielding requirements of radiation sources</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Range of radiation dosimeters for measuring radiation doses</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Immobilization devices</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provision for anaesthesia space and recovery for pediatric patients</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computer systems</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PET Equipment PET/CT Scanners</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The basic components of a PET system include the scintillator, detector, photomultiplier tubes (PMT), electronics and reconstruction software. Each of these components contribute to the overall performance of the PET system.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Radionuclide Activity Calibrator</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A radionuclide activity calibrator is a fundamental requirement for the operation of a PET centre. It allows accurately measured radiopharmaceutical doses to be administered to patients, and is also used for other laboratory tasks like measuring time-activity curves. A PET centre will thus be equipped with one or more radionuclide activity calibrators, depending on the type of installation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Radio analytical equipment</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Appropriate quality management systems for validation and the appropriate radio-analytical equipment for radio-analytical testing should be duly considered to ensure safety of drugs administered. HPLC, TLC and gamma spectroscopy are used for this purpose.</p>','2022-07-18 11:52:09','2022-07-18 11:52:09'),(30,31,'Nuclear Radiology Physical Infrastructure','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient registration and reception area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Designated waiting area for patients and caregivers (clearly demarcated as cold area)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clearly demarcated Hot areas including:</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hot cell area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>QC Lab with calibration probes</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hot lab for preparation of radiopharmaceuticals</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Injection room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Uptake room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Scanning room (PET/CT or SPECT)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hot toilet</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waste management facilities as specified by IAEA for example a Decay tank</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stress room to increase cardiac imaging&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient holding, observation and recovery areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radioactive waste store</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Specially designated room with toilet and bathroom facilities for patients&rsquo; exclusive use to minimize contamination</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Imaging, viewing &amp; scan reporting area (with requisite infrastructure)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Iodine wards for inpatients</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ventilation of the radiopharmaceutical production facility should meet the requirements as per IAEA guidelines to prevent contamination of products and exposure of personnel to radioactivity. The production of sterile radioactive products should be carried out under negative pressure surrounded by a positive pressure zone ensuring that appropriate air quality requirements are met.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-18 11:57:05','2022-07-18 11:58:23'),(31,32,'Surgical Oncology Operational Considerations','<h3><strong>1.1 Service Norms</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The National Guidelines for Cancer Management shall form the basis for clinical management at the facility.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The centre or unit must have NCI-K approved protocols for diagnosis and treatment of all malignancies they manage founded on sound scientific principles and evidence-based medicine which must be accessible to the prescribers, pharmacists and nurses at the centre at all times.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The protocols must be updated as appropriate and be readily available for inspection when needed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The centre or unit shall also commit to quality improvement, supporting cancer research and improving the training and mentoring of health care e. The centre or unit shall have infrastructure in place to be able to carry out cancer registration and reporting to the National Cancer Registry and KHIS.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.2 Service Delivery Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Every cancer centre shall:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Formulate and prominently display a service charter that details the roles and responsibilities of both the patient and the centre.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide integrated and multidisciplinary care&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Prioritize coordination and planning for professionals to help facilitate access to care at other levels of care, including awareness creation, screening/early detection, case management and appropriate downward referrals.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a reasonable time frame &ndash; definitive/tissue diagnosis should be done preferably within 2 weeks and the initiation of appropriate treatment within a month of diagnosis.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The recommended time frame between diagnosis and Surgery should be at least 120 days.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Follow evidence-based protocols and guidelines.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have informed consent obtained prior to all procedures including treatments. In case of a minor, a parent/guardian shall give consent. The information prior to consenting shall be provided in a manner easily understandable by the patient. The rights of the child should be prioritized.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish clear navigation systems to enable patients&rsquo; access to services.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Design patient-tracking systems for patient follow-up throughout the continuum of care.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Develop standard operating procedures for every service being provided</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.3 Clinical considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide cancer management that is holistic and patient-centred for best care outcomes.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Before initiation of treatment, clearly define and communicate the goals of care to the patient in accordance with a patient care plan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide the patient the right to detailed information on his/her condition, treatment options including clinical trials, side effects, expected outcome and prognosis.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow the patient the right to seek a second or additional opinion before consenting to initiation of treatment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all aspects of carefully documented, stored and easily retrievable.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow access of patients to their records as well as laboratory samples when needed&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Comprehensively document patient history</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.4 Multi-disciplinary Tumor Boards</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Definition; the multidisciplinary expert team that should manage cancer patients in a consultative approach</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;The cancer centre shall:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish multidisciplinary teams (MDTs)/tumor boards which shall guide and direct cancer management&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have MDTs meet regularly and have participation from all relevant disciplines depending on the cancer case and the level of care&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all complex cases discussed by a multidisciplinary team&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have an MDT coordinator who will organize for meetings, keep records of discussions and provide reports on cancer patient management&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Utilize technology to convene virtual MDT discussions with proper documentation</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>It consists of different experts including &ndash; medical oncologist, radiation/clinical oncologist, surgeon, pathologist, palliative physician and specialists, oncology pharmacist, oncology nurse, radiologist, interventional radiologist, haematologist, medical physicist, radiation therapist/therapy radiographer, medical laboratory technologists specialized in different laboratory disciplines.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.5 Diagnostic imaging</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(i) Incorporate clinical findings in conducting diagnostic imaging modalities&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(ii) Consider image-guided diagnostics where applicable</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(iii) Use a standard protocol for conducting imaging procedures</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(iv) Use internationally and locally recognized standards and guidelines for the safe installation, operation and use of imaging equipment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(v) Use a standard imaging diagnostic reporting protocol&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(vi) Outsource/provide access to an accredited imaging diagnostic facility</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.6 Nursing Considerations&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:-</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Provide oncology and palliative nursing care for the entire continuum of care(Prevention, Awareness, screening, early detection, diagnosis, treatment, survivorship and end of life care, bereavement).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Support the coordinating role of oncology and palliative care nurses in the&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>care team and community linkage for cancer patients</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.7 Surgical Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:-</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have Surgical site marking protocol implemented (standard site identification process, patient involved in marking, and marking done by the one doing procedure.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a Safe surgery checklist (evidence of use for verifying correct site, correct procedure, correct patient; availability of informed consent; and equipment needed are on hand, correct, and functional) See checklist <a href=\"about:blank\">Resources\\Safe surgery checklist.pdf</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide Evidence that facility has an active process of monitoring safe surgical checklist compliance.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ensure the organization uses a &ldquo;time-out&rdquo; procedure just before starting a surgical procedure.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Facilitate patients to access surgical diagnosis and treatment for solid malignancies through a multidisciplinary team approach.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Where tissue is obtained for histological examination, have the surgeon observe the SOP for histology specimen handling, storage and transport.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have surgical treatment offered conforming to internationally recognized, evidence-based surgical-oncological practices</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.8 Palliative Care and Survivorship Considerations&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Provide palliative care from the point of cancer diagnosis and at all times throughout the course of illness.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Integrate palliative care with other health services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Prioritize and provide effective relief of pain and other distressing symptoms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Provide timely rehabilitative and supportive services.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Facilitate formation of patient support groups.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Establish survivorship programs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Adhere to the National Palliative Care Policy and the National Palliative Care&nbsp;Guideline.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.9 Equipment Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Have all the facilities and equipment registered and licensed for safe and effective conduct of its services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have access to a qualified biomedical engineer, who is ultimately responsible for ensuring that all equipment are in proper working condition and that the necessary safety devices are fitted and in working order.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Maintain service contracts and schedules of service with the contracted service providers to ensure regular servicing as per the manufacturer&rsquo;s instructions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Ensure equipment compliance with relevant regulations according to the appropriate governing regulatory body.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Ensure safe disposal of obsolete or unserviceable equipment as guided by the relevant regulatory body.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.10 Referral Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Develop patient referral SOPs which conform to the national referral guidelines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Properly document referrals to and away from the facility.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Promote upward, downward and horizontal referral where appropriate.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Facilitate referrals for specialized services that are unavailable at the centre to facilities that are accessible and are accredited by the relevant regulatory body.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Assess patients for fitness to travel and provide necessary supportive mechanisms (ambulance, nurse, oxygen supply) before referral.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Provide proper patient counseling on cancer, tests to be done, costs implications and expected treatment before referral.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Refer a patient to the right specialist for further management if a service outside oncology services is required</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.11 Quality Assurance</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Establish a Quality Assurance Programme (QAP) that is adequately supervised and provides reports to NCI Kenya as required.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have risk assessment measures in place with objectives and systematic monitoring and evaluation so as to identify problems and system failures and guide the necessary action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Have regular morbidity and mortality meetings to identify specific clinical performance indicators.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.12 Infection Prevention and Control</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Oncology patients are at increased infection risk due to immunosuppression and frequent exposure to healthcare settings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a hospital&rsquo;s infection prevention and control program must be in accordance with the WHO Practical Guidelines for Infection Control.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have hand-washing facilities for staff readily available. Hand sanitizers should be provided at every work station.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide a designated sluicing area for linen generated in the Surgical area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have isolation rooms and practice barrier nursing by ensuring PPEs are available and easily accessible.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide decontamination and sterilization areas. (The decontaminant, sodium hypochlorite 5%)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.13 Occupational health and safety</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Implement the Occupational, Health &amp; Safety (OSH) Act in the workplace.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide safety and health training at least once every 3 years.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Be subject to annual inspection by the local regulatory body and adhere to the basic safety standards as set by the regulatory body.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disclose labeling laws for identification and classification of chemicals by types of hazards, including medication labels and safety data sheets.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a system for incidents monitoring and management at the workplace.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have programs to monitor and support employee performance, mental health, work-life balance and put in place debriefing programs.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.14 Waste Management</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide waste segregation and disposal amenities.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Conduct regular capacity building on waste disposal for all healthcare providers including support staff.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide appropriate PPEs for handling clinical waste</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.15 Emergency Medical Care&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have facilities and human resources to handle Surgical Oncology emergencies.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ensure medical staffs are trained in BLS/ACLS.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stabilize the patient and expeditiously refer for emergency management where applicable.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Be well equipped with resuscitation commodities and equipment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.16 Adverse Events</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Any adverse event that occurs as a result of the surgery must be documented, discussed internally and reported to the relevant regulatory bodies such as the Pharmacy and Poisons Board, relevant regulatory body and the NCI-K.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.17 Death of a Patient</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Document all deaths occurring whilst patients are undergoing treatment appropriately.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Offer bereavement support to the family.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Have periodic mortality meetings where cancer deaths are discussed by a multidisciplinary team</p>','2022-07-18 12:02:17','2022-07-18 13:59:58'),(32,33,'Surgical Oncology Physical Infrastructure','<p>The cancer centre shall ensure the physical infrastructure meets the following requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient flow</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Capacity for electricity, water, power backup, space</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safety considerations &ndash; fire</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separation of adult from pediatric management areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disability infrastructure in all areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Maintenance considerations</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.1 All departments and units</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>For centres operating within the precincts of a hospital, it can utilize similar facilities within the hospital. For stand-alone centres, these services must be provided for:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>a. Appropriate space for the following administrative services:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Administration</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Finance</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Transport</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iv. Supply chain management</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;v. Laundry</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;vi. Healthcare waste management, including hazardous drug waste, a Lockable holding area, proper segregation and disposal, MOUs with disposal companies</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;vii. Conference room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ix. Reception area</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>b. Utilities</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate patient and staff changing rooms</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate staff and patients rest rooms</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Staff room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.2 Health records and information &ndash; registration area</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Office space</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Filing room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Use of NACARE system for reporting is required using secure internet.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.3 Other supportive services</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Provision for day care services where applicable</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cancer registry office</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Office space</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Filing room</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.4 Surgical Oncology Unit</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Patient registration and reception area</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Waiting area for patients and caregivers</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Consultation room&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Triage/observation room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Counseling room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Procedure room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Pharmacy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>h. Operating theatre capable of handling minor and major surgical procedures with a Patient receiving room and a patient recovery room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>i. Nutrition</p>\r\n\r\n<p>j. Palliative care</p>\r\n\r\n<p>k. Medical Laboratory Unit</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Support from;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Diagnostic radiology unit</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pathology unit</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Blood banking</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Critical care unit</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Rehabilitation centres&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Endoscopy services</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Morgue services</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.5 Inpatient oncology wards</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Separate female, male, adolescents, geriatric and pediatric wards&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Side room facilities for ward reviews of post-operative wounds, minor procedures, and emergency resuscitation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Isolation rooms for patients with infectious conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Waste management facilities</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.6 Palliative Care and Survivorship Unit</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Patient registration and reception area</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Waiting area for patients/caregivers</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Counseling room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Procedure room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Consultation room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Community room large enough to accommodate support groups</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Support services</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Pharmacy</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Nutrition</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Chaplaincy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iv. Counseling&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;v. Rehabilitative unit</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Pediatrics play area</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Nutrition counseling rooms</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.7 Design and construction requirements</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>The design of any surgery department revolves around environmental control, traffic control, and the desire to prevent surgical site infection (SSI). <a href=\"about:blank\">Resources\\Surgical Operating Theatres Standards.docx</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Consult the Services of a registered Architectural and structural Engineering firms, with expertise in construction of health care facilities, for the design and construction.</p>','2022-07-18 12:03:10','2022-07-18 14:00:19'),(33,34,'Surgical Oncology Equipment','<p>Equipment must have service contracts and appropriate measures for plans for preventive maintenance purposes and provide service stickers showing dates for last service and next service due dates.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Elements that are important for the life of the equipment and for safety shall be addressed early in the planning stage and should be included in contractual forms, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Compliance with quality and safety standards</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Acceptance tests and conditions to correct deficiencies revealed during acceptance</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Warranty conditions</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Enforceable assurances on availability of maintenance support</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;(technical and financial), manufacturer support, manuals and spare parts</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Training of all users and keep documentation of the same</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Acceptance, testing and commissioning</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Commissioning is done by the manufacturer or his representative, Biomedical Engineer and the Surgeon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A record keeping system should also be in place. After commissioning has been completed, the specific tests needed for ongoing quality control and safety assurance will need to be carried out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Equipment Donation</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The donations should be guided by the principles developed by the WHO.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There should be effective communication between the donor, the recipient authority and, whenever possible, the end-user, before, during and after the donation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Surgical Oncology Unit Equipment</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Fully equipped major and minor theatres with standard anaesthetic, surgical and interventional equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Receiving area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pre-operative room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Post-operative room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Scrubbing room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Changing room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waiting area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Fully equipped endoscopy suite</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>In-patient Surgical Wards</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Wards</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Beds</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Wheelchairs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Trolleys</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iv. Consumable and reusable equipment for IV and medication equipment</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Phlebotomy equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bedside Cabinets</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurses&rsquo; station with cabinets/shelves</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>BP Monitors</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Thermometers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Weighing scale</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Heightometer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Crash cart</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waste segregation bins</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medicine Cabinets&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Consumables cabinets</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Decommissioning requirements</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Safety assessment survey report of the hazards involved during decommissioning exercise. Have a Decommissioning Plan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Have a hazardous waste management, transport and disposal plan for the decommissioning.</p>','2022-07-18 12:05:50','2022-07-18 14:00:45'),(34,36,'Surgical Oncology Human Resource','<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Anesthesiologists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Biomedical engineer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical Lab personnel&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Cancer Registrar</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical Officer anesthetist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurse anesthetist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Gynaecology Oncologist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Housekeeping staff</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Interventional radiologists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical Officers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical social worker</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurse &ndash; General with theatre experience</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nutritionist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical/ hemato-onco, Pediatric, Radiation Oncologists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Surgeons</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Q/A</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>IPC</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical Counsellors</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Physiotherapists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pharmacists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurse-palliative care</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Occupational therapists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Core human resource</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Human resource category&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Minimum Qualifications&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Anesthesiologists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMed in Anesthesia&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management;&nbsp;in charge of ICU/HDU</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED and a fellowship in medical oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;as an oncologist by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer&nbsp;centre/facility; assessment, initiation, review of&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>patients cancer treatment; chair MDTs meetings;&nbsp;participate in clinical research in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Pediatric Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED Paediatrics&nbsp;with fellowship in paediatric oncology</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer&nbsp;centre/facility; cancer diagnosis; assessment,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>initiation, review of paediatric patients cancer&nbsp;treatment; chair MDTs meetings; participate in&nbsp;clinical research in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Gynaecology&nbsp;Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED Obs/Gyne with&nbsp;a fellowship in Gynae&nbsp;Oncology.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;as a Gynae oncologist&nbsp;by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer&nbsp;centre/facility; assessment, initiation, surgical&nbsp;management and review of gynaecological&nbsp;cancer patients; participate in MDTs meetings;&nbsp;participate in clinical research in oncology;&nbsp;screening for gynae cancers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation oncologists/clinical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED/Fellowship in&nbsp;radiation oncology/</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Clinical oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;as an oncologist by&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; in charge of radiotherapy treatment;&nbsp;assessment, initiation, review of patients cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>treatment and patient follow up; treatment&nbsp;planning; chair MDTs meetings; participate in&nbsp;clinical research in oncology; participates in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>equipment procurement&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Haemato-oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED/Fellowship&nbsp;with specialization in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>hemato-oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; cancer diagnosis; assessment, initiation, review of patients cancer treatment; chair&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>MDTs meetings; participate in clinical research&nbsp;in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical Officer&nbsp;anesthetist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Higher Diploma in&nbsp;Anesthesia&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by the Clinical Officers Council</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management&nbsp;in consultation with the anesthesiologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer registrars</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Degree/diploma&nbsp;holder in Health Records &amp; information.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>registration from&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>African Cancer Registry Network (AFCRN)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>approved provider</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer data abstraction, maintenance of cancer&nbsp;patients records and participation in cancer&nbsp;research</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical counselors&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma/degree in&nbsp;psychological counseling.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- License to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>from relevant body</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Counseling of patients and their caregivers/families on cancer; patient navigation; research;member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Housekeeping&nbsp;staff</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Relevant training in&nbsp;housekeeping</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training in safe handling of hazardous&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>products</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Handling of waste and cleaning</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical social&nbsp;worker</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma or bachelors&nbsp;in social Sciences</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Assessment of socio-economic background of&nbsp;patients; Contact tracing; patient navigation;&nbsp;research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse - General(adult care and&nbsp;pediatric care)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Have Theatre experience/Training in Theatre Nurs</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Providing nursing care to cancer patients in&nbsp;collaboration with other members of the MDT,&nbsp;in all areas of cancer treatment; health education; screening activities; participate in clinical&nbsp;research in oncology; screening activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nutritionists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or degree in&nbsp;Nutrition&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- License to practice&nbsp;from Nutritionists &amp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Dieticians Council</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provision of nutritional counseling and support&nbsp;to patients and their families/caregivers; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Quality Assurance&nbsp;Officer/ Safety&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>A designated Quality&nbsp;Assurance Officer/&nbsp;Safety health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Liaise with all departments to ensure safety &amp;&nbsp;quality assurance is embedded in their processes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Infection Prevention and Control</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and Certification in IPC</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>-Monitor the rate of infections</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure proper waste management</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure proper use of PPE</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure hand hygiene compliance</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Biomedical engineering officers&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(medical engineers or technologist)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or bachelors&nbsp;in medical engineering&nbsp;and trained on maintenance of cancer equipment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered by the&nbsp;Association of Medical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Engineers of Kenya&nbsp;(AMEK) or relevant&nbsp;international body</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Installation, maintaining service contracts and&nbsp;equipment documentation and regular maintenance of cancer equipment at t</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Pharmacists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Degree in pharmacy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to Practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by PPB&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and certification in chemotherapy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>handling and administration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Preparation of chemotherapy medications under supervision of a clinical pharmacist; member of MDT; research; supply chain management&nbsp;of oncology commodities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Surgeons</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED Surgery or&nbsp;equivalent and/or specialization in Oncology.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of a surgical cancer&nbsp;facility; assessment, conduct surgery and review&nbsp;of cancer patients after surgery; participate in&nbsp;research and MDT activities; patient referrals</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical Laboratory technologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or degree&nbsp;in Medical Laboratory&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(Bsc) or related discipline&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;- Registered and&nbsp;licensed by KMLTTB&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Each section of the&nbsp;laboratory to be headed by a medical laboratory technologist with&nbsp;a diploma in Medical&nbsp;Laboratory Sciences in&nbsp;the disciplines</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;- Clinical Cytology/Histopathology, Biochemistry, Microbiology, Immunology,&nbsp;Molecular Sciences,&nbsp;Blood Transfusion/Haematology Sciences,&nbsp;Epidemiology, public&nbsp;health or virology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provide lab services, research; sample collection;&nbsp;safe waste disposal; relay of results</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Supportive Human Resource/Auxilliary/Adjunct</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Human resource category&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Minimum Qualifications&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical Officers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MBCHB</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by KMPDB - Training&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>and certification in&nbsp;chemotherapy handling and administration</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Health education; screening activities; assess,&nbsp;prescribe, administer subsequent cancer treatment under supervision of an oncologist; participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurses - Palliative&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>care</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Specialized Palliative&nbsp;care nursing - Higher&nbsp;Diploma, MSc Nursing&nbsp;or an accredited Palliative program&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the palliative&nbsp;care services in the facility; nursing care to cancer patients in the MDT; comprehensive patient&nbsp;assessments; Pain and Symptom management;&nbsp;Management of treatment side effects; Patient&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>navigation activities; initiating , organizing and&nbsp;facilitating family conferences and advance care&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>planning; end of life and bereavement care;&nbsp;clinical research in palliative care; advocacy;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>mentorship and teaching; policy formulation&nbsp;and implementation</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse anesthetist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Higher diploma in&nbsp;anesthesia</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed by NCK</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management&nbsp;in consultation with the anesthesiologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Interventional&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>radiologists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED in radiology</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Fellowship in interventional Radiology</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by KMDPB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>In-charge of interventional diagnostic radiology&nbsp;activities including biopsy collection; research;&nbsp;member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Occupational&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>therapists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma, higher diploma or bachelors in&nbsp;occupational therapy</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provision of rehabilitative services to patients;&nbsp;research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Physiotherapists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma, higher diploma or bachelors in&nbsp;physiotherapy</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provision of rehabilitative services to patients;&nbsp;research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>','2022-07-18 12:06:41','2022-07-18 13:59:34'),(35,37,'Radiotherapy Operational Considerations','<h3><strong>1.1 Procedure for designation as a radiotherapy Cancer Centre</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A facility that plans to offer radiotherapy cancer service must apply for designation to NCI Kenya and should adhere to the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The proposal for the radiotherapy Cancer Centre designation shall specify the objectives of the cancer management program, the range of services to be provided, the approximate number of patients to be treated, and the physical infrastructure, equipment, human resources and operational management resources, as laid out in this document.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The facility will be issued with a comprehensive checklist of the components required for a radiotherapy Cancer Centre before it submits the application for designation.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Proposals for a radiotherapy Cancer Centre designation shall be submitted to the Chief Executive Officer National Cancer Institute Kenya (NCI-K), together with the application form for approval not less than 90 days before the intended commencement of operations of the cancer center.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Only upon final approval by the NCI-K will a facility be designated as a radiotherapy Cancer Centre. NCI-K will ensure that the Centre maintains the services and standards outlined in these Guidelines in order to retain this designation. The certificate of radiotherapy Cancer Management Centre designation (based on the service (s) to be offered) will be issued by NCI-K and shall be displayed at the facility.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>NCI-K will conduct inspections and accreditation after every two years to ensure compliance to the guideline, however NCI-K can conduct adhoc inspections to ensure standards are maintained.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.2 Service Norms for Radiotherapy Cancer Centres</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The National Guidelines for radiotherapy Cancer Management shall form the basis for clinical management at the facility.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The radiotherapy centre or unit must have NCI-K approved protocols for treatment of all malignancies they manage founded on sound scientific principles and evidence-based medicine which must be accessible to the radiotherapy clinical team at the centre at all times.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The protocols must be updated as appropriate, readily available and displayed.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The radiotherapy centre or unit shall also commit to quality improvement, supporting cancer research and improving the training and mentoring of health care&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The radiotherapy centre or unit shall have infrastructure in place to be able to carry out cancer registration and notification to the National Cancer Registry.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.3 Service Delivery Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Every radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Formulate and prominently display a service charter that details the roles and responsibilities of both the patient and the centre.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide integrated and multidisciplinary care</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Prioritize coordination and planning for professionals to help facilitate access to care at other levels of care, including awareness creation,screening/early detection, case management and appropriate referrals.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a reasonable time frame &ndash; Radiotherapy treatments should commence &nbsp; within 2 weeks post treatment planning completion.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Follow evidence-based protocols and guidelines.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have informed consent obtained prior to all radiotherapy treatments. In case of a minor, a parent/guardian shall give consent. The information prior to consenting shall be provided in a manner easily understandableby the patient. The rights of the child should be prioritized.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish clear navigation systems to enable patients&rsquo; access to services.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Design patient-tracking systems for patient follow-up throughout the continuum of care.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Develop standard operating procedures for every service being provided.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.4 Clinical Radiotherapy Management Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide cancer management that is holistic and patient-centred for best care outcomes&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Before initiation of treatment, clearly define and communicate the goals of care to the patient in accordance with a patient care plan</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide the patient the right to detailed information on his/her condition, treatment options including clinical trials, side effects, expected outcome and prognosis.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow the patient the right to seek a second or additional opinion before consenting to initiation of treatment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all aspects of carefully documented, stored and easily retrievable.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow access of patients to their records as well as medical reports when needed</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Comprehensively document patient history</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><br />\r\n<strong>1.5 Multi-disciplinary Tumor Boards</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish multidisciplinary teams (MDTs)/tumour boards which shall guide and direct cancer management</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have MDTs meet regularly and have participation from all relevant disciplines depending on the cancer case and the level of care</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all complex cases discussed by a multidisciplinary team</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have an MDT coordinator who will organize for meetings, keep records of discussions and&nbsp; provide reports on cancer patient management</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The outcomes of the MDT&rsquo;s discussion must be documented in the patient file.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Utilize technology to convene virtual MDT discussions with proper documentation of the same&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.6 CT Simulation Capacity Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pretreatment&nbsp; imaging</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Incorporate clinical findings in conducting pretreatment imaging modalities</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use a dedicated wide bore CT simulator with aperture of not less than 70cm preferably 80cm</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Reference room lasers should be installed&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use a standard&nbsp; simulation protocol for pretreatment Imaging</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use internationally and locally recognized standards and guidelines for the safe installation, operation and use of imaging equipment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Incorporate appropriate and site specific immobilization devices&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Incase CT simulator is not available, a conventional simulator must be available.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Radiation Oncology Considerations</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy centre shall:<br />\r\na) Provide radiation oncology services in adherence to IAEA and local regulatory body guidelines including radiation safety protection.<br />\r\nb) Fully document all ionizing radiation therapeutic applications and maintain proper records for treatment planning simulation, isodose distribution plan, dosimetry, brachytherapy and physics documentation.<br />\r\nc) Deliver the most novel and advanced technologies available for radiation oncology. These technologies should be cost-eﬀective, efficient, upgradable and practical.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d) Provide adequate information to patients receiving radiotherapy regarding the procedure to be done.<br />\r\ne) For brachytherapy source, acquire relevant licenses from KNRA that guides source shipping, handling, storage and disposal upon depletion of radioisotopes including radiation safety program designed for the practice.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.7 Occupational health and safety considerations:</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy central shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Be subject to annual inspection by the local regulatory body and adhere to the basic safety standards as set by the regulatory body.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disclose labeling laws for identification and classification of radiation by types of hazards, including radiation labels and safety data sheets.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish a system for identification and surveillance of exposure: estimating the number of workers who come into contact with substances and are employed in occupations with increased carcinogenic risk, and reducing to minimum the number of workers exposed, the duration of exposure and the degree of exposure, and establishing an appropriate system of records.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ensure medical surveillance applies to all healthcare workers in the radiotherapy unit and includes assessment and documentation of symptom complaints, physical findings &amp; laboratory values</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide personal protective equipment for workers and decontamination facilities in the workplace.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish/develop guidelines and recommendations for proper use and handling of radio-active substances and training packages for healthcare workers.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a system of monitoring services at the workplace and assess occupational exposures.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Empower workers by providing them with access to information about their exposures and risks.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have programs to monitor employee performance, mental health, work-life balance and put in place debriefing programs.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.8 Waste Management</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dispose radioactive waste produced in the process of the diagnosis and treatment of cancer in accordance to international and relevant local guidelines.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have written policies and SOPs for hazardous waste describing requirements for the segregation, packaging, labeling, collection, transportation and storage of waste within the facility.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide waste disposal amenities and commodities.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Conduct regular capacity building on waste disposal for all healthcare providers including support staff.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide appropriate PPEs for handling hazardous waste.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Minimize the risk of contaminating the local water supply and/or soil with radio-active waste. Hazardous materials shall never be discarded into waste water (sink or toilet) or into a landfill.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.9 Emergency Medical Care</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Have facilities and human resources to handle oncologic and palliative care emergencies.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Develop and display SOPs on emergency care.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Ensure medical staffs are trained in BLS/ACLS.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Stabilize the patient and expeditiously refer for emergency management where applicable.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Be well equipped with resuscitation commodities and equipment.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.10 Adverse Events</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Document, discuss internally, put in place mitigation measures then report to the relevant regulatory body any adverse event that occurs as a result of cancer diagnosis or treatment.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><br />\r\n<strong>1.11 Death of a Patient</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Document all deaths occurring whilst patients are undergoing treatment appropriately.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Offer bereavement support to the family.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have periodic mortality meetings where cancer deaths are discussed by a multidisciplinary team.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-18 12:08:20','2022-07-18 12:08:20'),(36,38,'Radiotherapy Human Resource','<p>The human resource requirements for the chemotherapy centre are as follows with core staff and supportive staff</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Human resource category</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Minimum Qualifica- tions</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Staff Establishment</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Anesthesiologists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MMed in Anesthesis</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p>(Licensed to practice by&nbsp; KMPDB)</p>\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management; in charge of ICU/HDU</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Biomedical engineering officers (medical engineers or technologist)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or bachelors in medical engineering and trained on maintenance of cancer equipment.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered by the Association of Medical Engineers of Kenya (AMEK) or relevant international body</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Installation, maintaining service contracts and equipment documentation and regular maintenance of cancer equipment at the&nbsp; facility</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer registrars</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Degree/diploma holder in Health Records &amp; information management (registered by AMRO-K or by an established HRIM Board)</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in cancer registration and notification by NCI-K or NCI-K approved provider.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer data abstraction, notification/data entry and maintenance of cancer patients records and participation in cancer research.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Reception and registration, storage, filing and retrieval, clinic preparation, file tracing, report generation/sharing and editing files.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical counselors</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma/degree in psychological counseling.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice from relevant body</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Counseling of patients and their caregivers/ families on cancer; patient navigation; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical Officer anesthetist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Higher Diploma in Anesthesia</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice by the Clinical Officers Council</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management in consultation with the&nbsp; anesthesiologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinically qualified Medical Physicists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Bsc in physics with postgraduate training in medical physics or Msc Medical Physics with clinical training in radiotherapy physics</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Responsible for equipment selection, specifications, acceptance, delivery, design of installations and shielding requirements, com- missioning and management for radiotherapy, diagnostics and nuclear medicine; Treatment planning in collaboration with the radiation oncologist; safety assessment, establishment, measurement and supervision of QA for radiotherapy and nuclear medicine devices; radiation protection and safety; dose calibration and instrumentation; technical supervision of maintenance; research and innovation of new medical devices; teaching &ndash; radiation protection &amp; users of equipment.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Housekeeping staff</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Relevant training in housekeeping</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Training in safe handling of hazardous products</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Handling of waste and cleaning</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical Officers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MBCHB</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice by&nbsp; KMPDB - Training and certification in chemotherapy handling and administration</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Health education; screening activities; assess, prescribe, administer subsequent cancer treatment under supervision of an oncologist; participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical social worker</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or&nbsp; bachelors in social Sciences</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Assessment of socio-economic background of patients; Contact tracing; patient navigation; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Patient navigators</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Training in customer service</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Training in basic life support for non-medical providers</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Receiving and guiding patients</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse anesthetist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Higher diploma in anesthesia</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed by NCK</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management in consultation with the&nbsp; anesthesiologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Oncology nurse&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MSc Nursing or equivalent focused in oncology Nursing or HND oncology nursing&nbsp;</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya (NCK)</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; providing nursing care to cancer patients; health education; screening activities; part of the MDT; comprehensive patient assessments; symptom management; treatment side effects management; patient navigation activities; clinical research in oncology; advocacy; mentorship and teaching; policy formulation and implementation; screening&nbsp; activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>General nurse</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or Degree in Nursing</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>Certification in chemotherapy handling and administration (those working in chemotherapy units)</li>\r\n				<li>Undergone an appropriate induction pro- gram in cancer management</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Providing nursing care to cancer patients in collaboration with other members of the MDT, in all areas of cancer treatment; health education; screening activities; participate in clinical research in oncology; screening&nbsp; activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse Manager</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>BSc Nursing with Specialized oncology nursing training,</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Additional qualification in admin and MSc is an added advantage</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>&nbsp;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Head of Nursing oncology services; Coordination, Directing and organization of patient care activities in the unit; Resource management and Budgeting; Staffing activities; Quality management; Reporting participate in MDTs meetings; Participate in clinical research; policy formulation, implementation and&nbsp; monitoring</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nutritionists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or degree in Nutrition</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>License to practice from Nutritionists &amp; Dieticians Council</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provision of nutritional counseling and support to patients and their families/caregivers; re- search; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation Safety Officer (RSO)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Advanced degree in Medical Physics, Health Physics, radiation physics or equivalent</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Supervised training for 6 months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Radiation Protection and Safety</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Psychologists (both adult and pediatric)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Degree in psychology.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>License to practice from relevant body</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Counseling of patients and their caregivers/ families on cancer; patient navigation; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Quality Assurance Officer/ Safety health officer</p>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Quality assurance officers</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Radiation Safety Officers</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Patient Safety officer</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p>Occupational safe- ty &amp; health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>A designated Quality Assurance Officer/ Safety health officer</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Liaise with all departments to ensure safety &amp; quality assurance is embedded in their processes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation oncologists/clinical oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MMED/Fellowship in radiation oncology/ Clinical oncology</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice as an oncologist by KMPDB</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; in charge of radiotherapy treatment; assessment, initiation, review of patients cancer treatment and patient follow up; treatment planning; chair MDTs meetings; participate in clinical research in oncology; participates in equipment procurement</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Paediatric Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MMED Paediatrics with fellowship in paediatric oncology</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice by&nbsp; KMPDB</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; cancer diagnosis; assessment, initiation, review of paediatric patients cancer treatment; chair MDTs meetings; participate in clinical research in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation Therapists (RTT) /Therapy radiographers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or higher diploma in radiation therapy</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Participate in treatment planning; administer radiotherapy&nbsp; treatment&nbsp; under&nbsp; supervision&nbsp; of the radio-oncologist; participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiotherapy Services Manager</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>The officer in charge to hold at least a bachelor&rsquo;s degree in therapy radiography</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>To head and coordinate radiotherapy services in the centre</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>','2022-07-18 12:09:15','2022-07-18 12:09:15'),(37,39,'Radiotherapy Equipment','<p>Equipment must have service contracts and appropriate measures for plans for preventive maintenance purposes and provide service stickers showing dates for last service and next service due dates. Elements that are important for the life of the equipment and for safety shall be addressed early in the planning stage and should be included in contractual forms, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Compliance with quality and safety standards</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Acceptance tests and conditions to correct deficiencies revealed during acceptance</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Warranty conditions</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Enforceable assurances on availability of maintenance support (technical and financial), manufacturer support, manuals and spare parts</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Training of all users and keep documentation of the same</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Acceptance testing and commissioning</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Radiation sources need to be safely received, registered and stored; radiation measurement equipment tested and calibrated; shielding properties of special rooms measured; and the radiation sources tested and calibrated. All major equipment will require commissioning including tele therapy machines, imaging machines (simulators), brachytherapy units and TPSs. A record keeping system should also be in place. After commissioning has been completed, the specific tests needed for ongoing quality control and safety assurance will need to be carried out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Commissioning requirements for Radiotherapy unit</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The process of Commissioning involves Pre-Commissioning and Trial run permission.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After completion of construction and installation, the applicant should approach the regulatory body for permission to carry out a trial run for commissioning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For this purpose, the applicant should submit the following to the regulatory body:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Acceptance Tests conducted on the following equipment;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation Protection Program (RPP).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Details regarding availability of qualified and trained manpower &ndash; operator(s), radio pharmacist(s)/radio-chemist(s) and a Board approved Radiological Safety Officer (RSO).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Personnel monitoring services for all radiation workers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Appropriate radiation measuring and monitoring Instruments</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Operational procedure manual</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safe handling tools and devices required for operation and maintenance of the medical cyclotron and auxiliary equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Security Plan</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Submit the Commissioning Test Report&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>After successful trial runs, the applicant becomes eligible for obtaining consent for trial operations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Decommissioning requirements</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>When the medical cyclotron is no longer to be used, the permission for decommissioning shall be obtained from the Radiation Protection Board. The licensee should apply for the decommissioning license and supply the Authority with the following;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safety assessment survey report of the radiological and non-radiological hazards involved during decommissioning exercise.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Decommissioning Plan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation Protection considerations for the decommissioning workers.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Public radiation protection consideration at vicinity.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Qualified Radiation safety supervisor designated for the exercise.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation safety equipment to be used for decommissioning.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radioactive waste management, transport and disposal plan for the decommissioning.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Site radiation decontamination and final radiation survey.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>The licensee shall submit a report on the completion of decommissioning, which includes among others; safe disposal of sources and personnel exposures received during decommissioning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>List of Equipment</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>External Beam Radiation Therapy.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Electronic Portal Imaging Device (EPID) photo imaging device for verification</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>High dose Rate (HDR) brachytherapy machine (afterloader)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>CT/Conventional treatment planning simulator complete with accessories</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dosimetry quality assurance equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation Safety monitoring devices and radiation safety checklists and reporting.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>ICT infrastructure and support</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Treatment planning system</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Standardized rulers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Two-way video cameras, with audio capability</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Appropriate shielding requirements of radiation sources</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>3-D water scan phantom</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Range of radiation dosimeters for measuring radiation doses</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Immobilization devices</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mould room equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provision for anaesthesia space and recovery if facility is to offer pediatric radiation therapy</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-18 12:10:29','2022-07-18 12:10:29'),(38,40,'Radiotherapy Physical Infrastructure','<p>The following section outlines the infrastructural considerations for different units. The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall ensure the physical infrastructure meets the following requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>A standard bunker for Linac</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Brachytherapy suite with a theatre</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>CT simulator room/conventional simulator room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Control room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Physics room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mould room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Administration area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Capacity for electricity, water, power backup, space</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safety considerations &ndash; fire</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disability friendly infrastructure in all areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Maintenance considerations</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Treatment planning room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Recovery area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waiting area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient Reception area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Triage area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nursing station</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Consultation room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Procedure room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Emergency room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nutrition and counselling room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate staff and patient changing rooms</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate male and female toilets for staff and patients</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Sluice room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Registry</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hand wash area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Storage area&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Conference room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Staff room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Laundry</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Holding area in case of a death</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Special considerations:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>For a radiotherapy with in-patient services, separate adult from pediatric unit.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>For pediatric services, dedicated child-friendly rooms should be provided.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-18 12:12:45','2022-07-18 12:12:45'),(39,41,'Cancer Research','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The goal of studying cancer is to develop safe and effective methods to prevent, detect, diagnose, treat, and, ultimately, cure the collections of diseases we call cancer. Cancer research can be divided into several broad categories:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Basic research is the study of animals, cells, molecules, or genes to gain new knowledge about cellular and molecular changes that occur naturally or during the development of a disease. Basic research is also referred to as lab research or preclinical research.​</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Translational research describes an approach that seeks to accelerate the application of discoveries in the laboratory to clinical practice. This is often referred to as moving advances from bench to bedside.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical research involves the application of treatments and procedures in patients. Clinical researchers conduct clinical trials, study a particular patient or group of patients, including their behaviors, or use materials from humans, such as blood or tissue samples, to learn about disease, how the healthy body works, or how it responds to treatment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Population research is the study of causes and patterns of occurrence of cancer and evaluation of risk. Population scientists, also known as epidemiologists, study the patterns, causes, and effects of health and diseases in defined groups. Population research is highly collaborative and can span the spectrum from basic to clinical research.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-18 12:16:10','2022-07-18 12:16:27'),(40,42,'Oncology Training Program','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Oncology training program is defined as any of the following:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>an accredited postgraduate programme at a medical school,&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>continuing medical education initiative,&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>diploma/certificate programme&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>a clinical placement programme</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre/ medical school/ hospital has to have an approved curriculum that is certified by the respective academic/ regulatory bodies</p>','2022-07-18 12:17:55','2022-07-18 12:18:06'),(41,43,'Comprehensive pathology','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The whole spectrum of services and tests done to determine both definitive tissue diagnosis of cancer as well as hematology, microbiology, chemistry and immunology to enable the initiation, continuation and monitoring of cancer treatment. This definition applies to comprehensive cancer centres/ centres of excellence which are expected to do both diagnosis and treatment</p>','2022-07-18 12:18:50','2022-07-18 12:18:59'),(42,44,'Comprehensive laboratory','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Services and tests in hematology, microbiology, clinical chemistry, histopathology, molecular PCR and immunology to enable the initiation, continuation and monitoring of cancer treatment. This definition applies to cancer management centres which may receive results of the tissue diagnosis of cancer from another facility and only have capacity to treat.</p>','2022-07-18 12:20:04','2022-07-18 12:20:18'),(43,45,'Cancer Screening','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cancer Screening involves applying simple tests or procedures across a healthy population in order to identify unrecognized cancer disease in individuals before they develop any symptoms of the cancer. This has to be provided in every cancer centre and should cater for both men and women.</p>','2022-07-18 12:23:13','2022-07-18 12:24:01'),(44,46,'Chemotherapy Operational Considerations','<h3><strong>1.1 Service Norms</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>a. The National Guidelines for Cancer Management shall form the basis for clinical management at the facility.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. The centre or unit must have NCI-K approved protocols for diagnosis and treatment of all malignancies they manage founded on sound scientific principles and evidence-based medicine which must be accessible to the prescribers, pharmacists and nurses at the centre at all times.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. The protocols must be updated as appropriate and be readily available for inspection when needed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. The centre or unit shall also commit to quality improvement, supporting cancer research and improving the training and mentoring of health care e. The centre or unit shall have infrastructure in place to be able to carry out cancer registration and reporting to the National Cancer Registry and DHIS.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.2 Service Delivery Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Service Delivery Considerations Every cancer centre shall:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Formulate and prominently display a service charter that details the roles and responsibilities of both the patient and the centre.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Provide integrated and multidisciplinary care&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Prioritize coordination and planning for professionals to help facilitate access to care at other levels of care, including awareness creation, screening/early detection, case management and appropriate downward referrals.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Have a reasonable time frame &ndash; definitive/tissue diagnosis should be done preferably within 2 weeks and the initiation of appropriate treatment within a month of diagnosis.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Follow evidence-based protocols and guidelines.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Have informed consent obtained prior to all procedures including treatments. In case of a minor, a parent/guardian shall give consent. The information prior to consenting shall be provided in a manner easily understandable by the patient. The rights of the child should be prioritized.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Establish clear navigation systems to enable patients&rsquo; access to services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;h. Design patient-tracking systems for patient follow-up throughout the continuum of care. i. Develop standard operating procedures for every service being provided</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.3 Clinical considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Provide cancer management that is holistic and patient-centred for best care outcomes</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Before initiation of treatment, clearly define and communicate the goals of care to the patient in accordance with a patient care plan</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Provide the patient the right to detailed information on his/her condition, treatment options including clinical trials, side effects, expected outcome and prognosis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Allow the patient the right to seek a second or additional opinion before consenting to initiation of treatment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Have all aspects of carefully documented, stored and easily retrievable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Allow access of patients to their records as well as laboratory samples when needed</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Comprehensively document patient history</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.4 Multi-disciplinary Tumor Boards</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Definition; the multidisciplinary expert team that should manage cancer patients in a consultative approach</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Establish multidisciplinary teams (MDTs)/tumor boards which shall guide and direct cancer management</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have MDTs meet regularly and have participation from all relevant disciplines depending on the cancer case and the level of care</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Have all complex cases discussed by a multidisciplinary team</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Have an MDT coordinator who will organize for meetings, keep records of discussions and provide reports on cancer patient management</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Utilize technology to convene virtual MDT discussions with proper documentation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It consists of different experts including &ndash; medical oncologist, radiation/clinical oncologist, surgeon, pathologist, palliative physician and specialists, oncology pharmacist, oncology nurse, radiologist, interventional radiologist, haematologist, medical physicist, radiation therapist/therapy radiographer, medical laboratory technologists specialized in different laboratory disciplines.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.5 Diagnostic imaging</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Incorporate clinical findings in conducting diagnostic imaging modalities&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Consider image-guided diagnostics where applicable</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use a standard protocol for conducting imaging procedures or an MOU with a facility with that has standard protocol for conducting imaging procedures.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use internationally and locally recognized standards and guidelines for the safe installation, operation and use of imaging equipment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use a standard imaging diagnostic reporting protocol&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Outsource/provide access to an accredited imaging diagnostic facility</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.6 Nursing Considerations&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:-</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide oncology and palliative nursing care for the entire continuum of care (Prevention, Awareness, screening, early detection, diagnosis, treatment, survivorship and end of life care, bereavement).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Support the coordinating role of oncology and palliative care nurses in the care team and community linkage for cancer patients</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.7 Chemotherapy Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Definition of Chemotherapy</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Have only appropriately qualified oncologists initiate cancer patients on chemotherapy and biotherapies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;b. Have chemotherapy medications prepared by a pharmacist or pharmaceutical technologist in a bio-safety cabinet class 2B2 vented to the outside.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Provide personal protective equipment to all members of the health care team who prepare, mix, administer and transport hazardous chemotherapy drugs.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Have a program that monitors exposure to hazardous chemotherapy drugs for all health workers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Ensure pregnant and lactating health workers are not assigned to an area where chemotherapy drugs are present/being administered</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Provide education and training for safe handling of these drugs to health workers exposed to hazardous chemotherapy drugs prior to their being assigned to an area where chemotherapy agents are present. Training must be done for all staff in the facility, annually, with the educational content being specific to the activities for which the health worker is responsible.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Prior to administration of chemotherapy ensure there is a system in place to confirm that the correct medication and dosage is administered to the correct patient.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>h. Chemotherapy medicines especially vesicants like vinca alkaloids shall be whenever possible be administered via a central line e.g. using chemoports. Chemotherapy shall be administered through infusion pumps for accuracy and safety.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Have the facility ensure provision for management of extravasations and spills.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>j. Provide patients and caregivers involved in the delivery of chemotherapy at home receive some basic education and training on the principles of safe handling, dealing with spills, waste disposal and patients&rsquo; excreta. Written instructions shall be given to the patient and/or caregiver, including information on the use of oral chemotherapeutic agents.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>k. Document the process for handling hazardous drugs waste generated during compounding and administration or during spills, as well as waste (bulk) products for chemotherapy.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>l. Store chemotherapy medicines separately from other medicines &ndash; both storage area and refrigerator&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>m. Transport of chemotherapy medicines should maintain the integrity of the drug to avoid breakage or leakage that leads to spillages, contamination and exposure to the hazardous drug&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>n. Ensure labelling of chemotherapeutic agents includes storage, handling and disposal instructions&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>o. Develop facility SOPs for &ndash; designation of HD areas; receipt of HDs; storage of HDs; compounding of HDs; use and maintenance of proper engineering controls; hand hygiene and use of PPEs; deactivation, decontamination, cleaning &amp; disinfection; dispensing of HDs; transport of HDs; administering HDs, environmental monitoring; disposal of HDs; spill control and medical surveillance.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.8 Health Information and Records &amp; Cancer Registry Office Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Designate an office for Cancer registry- the office should be lockable, with lockable cabinets and a computer with internet access.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Establish a health records department that will maintain all patient records in a system that is secure, confidential and easy to retrieve.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Capture data for all cancer cases comprehensively.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Notify the National Cancer Registry all new cancer cases using the cancer&nbsp;abstract form&nbsp;<a href=\"about:blank\">National Cancer Notification Form_FINAL copy.pdf</a>(NACARE) as provided for by the Cancer Control Act 2012.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Ensure that the health records department sends reports to the National&nbsp;Cancer Registry and MoH-KHIS monthly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Permanently archive cancer patient records.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Respect patients&rsquo; rights to access their records at any point in their lifetime.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.9 Palliative Care and Survivorship Considerations&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Provide palliative care from the point of cancer diagnosis and at all times throughout the course of illness.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Integrate palliative care with other health services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Prioritize and provide effective relief of pain and other distressing symptoms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Provide timely rehabilitative and supportive services.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Facilitate formation of patient support groups.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Establish survivorship programs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Adhere to the National Palliative Care Policy and the National Palliative Care&nbsp;Guideline.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.10 Equipment Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Have all the facilities and equipment registered and licensed for safe and effective conduct of its services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have access to a qualified biomedical engineer, who is ultimately responsible for ensuring that all equipment are in proper working condition and that the necessary safety devices are fitted and in working order.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Maintain service contracts and schedules of service with the contracted service providers to ensure regular servicing as per the manufacturer&rsquo;s instructions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Ensure equipment compliance with relevant regulations according to the appropriate governing regulatory body. Equipment more than 7 years old should not be acquired for cancer treatment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Ensure safe disposal of obsolete or unserviceable equipment as guided by the relevant regulatory body.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.11 Referral Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Develop patient referral SOPs (<a href=\"about:blank\">ministry-of-health-referral-guidelines-37-40.pdf</a>&nbsp;) which conform to the national referral guidelines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Properly document referrals to and away from the facility.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Promote upward, downward and horizontal referral where appropriate.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Facilitate referrals for specialized services that are unavailable at the centre to facilities that are accessible and are accredited by the relevant regulatory body.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Assess patients for fitness to travel and provide necessary supportive&nbsp;mechanisms (ambulance, nurse, oxygen supply) before referral.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Provide proper patient counseling on cancer, tests to be done, costs implications and expected treatment before referral.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Refer a patient to the right specialist for further management if a service outside oncology services is required</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.12 Quality Assurance</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Establish a Quality Assurance Programme (QAP) that is adequately supervised and provides reports to NCI Kenya as required.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have risk assessment measures in place with objectives and systematic monitoring and evaluation so as to identify problems and system failures and guide the necessary action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Have regular morbidity and mortality meetings to identify specific clinical performance indicators.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.13 Infection Prevention and Control</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oncology patients are at increased infection risk due to immunosuppression and frequent exposure to healthcare settings.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Have a hospital&rsquo;s infection prevention and control program must be in accordance with the WHO Practical Guidelines for Infection Control<a href=\"about:blank\">.File571.pdf</a>.</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Have hand-washing facilities for staff readily available. Hand sanitizers should be provided at every work station.</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have eyewash facilities for staff in Chemo mixing and administration areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide a designated sluicing area for linen generated in the chemo area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have isolation rooms and practice barrier nursing by ensuring PPEs are&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>available and easily accessible.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.14 Occupational health and safety</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Implement the Occupational, Health &amp; Safety (OSH) Act in the workplace.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Provide safety and health training at least once every 3 years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Be subject to annual inspection by the local regulatory body and adhere to the basic safety standards as set by the regulatory body.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Disclose labeling laws for identification and classification of chemicals by types of hazards, including medication labels and safety data sheets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Establish a system for identification and surveillance of exposure: estimating the number of workers who come into contact with substances and are employed in occupations with increased carcinogenic risk, and reducing to minimum the number of workers exposed, the duration of exposure and the degree of exposure, and establishing an appropriate system of records.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Ensure medical surveillance applies to all healthcare workers handling hazardous drugs and includes assessment and documentation of symptom complaints, physical findings &amp; laboratory values</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Provide personal protective equipment i.e N95 masks, powder-free Nitrile gloves, shoe covers, head net, goggles, non-absorbent gown, face shield for health workers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>h. Establish/develop guidelines and recommendations for proper use and handling of carcinogenic chemicals and training packages for healthcare workers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>i. Have a system for incidents monitoring and management at the workplace.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>j. Empower workers by providing them with access to information about their exposures and risks.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>k. Have programs to monitor and support employee performance, mental health, work-life balance and put in place debriefing programs.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.15 Waste Management</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Dispose cytotoxic waste produced in the process of the diagnosis and treatment of cancer in accordance to international and relevant local guidelines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have written policies and SOPs for hazardous waste describing requirements for the segregation, packaging, labeling, collection, transportation storage and on site treatment of waste within the facility.<a href=\"about:blank\">National-Guidelines-for-Safe-management-of-health-care-waste-Final1.pdf</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Provide waste disposal amenities and commodities.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Conduct regular capacity building on waste disposal for all healthcare providers including support staff.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Provide appropriate PPEs for handling hazardous waste.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Incinerate hazardous waste using special incinerators that can combust at 1200&deg;Centigrade and maintain documentation on the same.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Minimize the risk of contaminating the local water supply and/or soil with hazardous drugs. Hazardous drug waste shall never be discarded into waste water (sink or toilet) or into a landfill.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.16 Emergency Medical Care&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Have facilities and human resources to handle oncologic and palliative care emergencies.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Ensure medical staffs are trained in BLS/ACLS.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Stabilize the patient and expeditiously refer for emergency management where applicable.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Be well equipped with resuscitation commodities and equipment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.17 Adverse Events</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Any adverse event that occurs as a result of cancer diagnosis or treatment must be documented, discussed internally and reported to the relevant regulatory bodies such as the Pharmacy and Poisons Board, relevant regulatory body and the NCI-K.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.18 Death of a Patient</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Document all deaths occurring whilst patients are undergoing treatment appropriately.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Offer bereavement support to the family.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Have periodic mortality meetings where cancer deaths are discussed by a multidisciplinary team</p>','2022-07-18 12:46:26','2022-07-20 07:34:13'),(45,47,'Chemotherapy Human Resource','<p>The human resource requirements for the chemotherapy centre are as follows with core staff and supportive staff</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oncologist (Medical, Clinical)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oncology Nurse</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical Pharmacist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Cancer Registrar</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical Counsellor&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nutritionist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical social worker</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Infection Prevention and Control Expert&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Quality Assurance Expert</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient navigators</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Core Human Resource</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Minimum Qualifications&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Required staff establishment (number)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation oncologist/ Medical oncologist/clinical&nbsp;Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED/Fellowship in&nbsp;radiation oncology/Clinical oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;as an oncologist by&nbsp;KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; in charge of radiotherapy treatment;&nbsp;assessment, initiation, review of patients cancer&nbsp;treatment and patient follow up; treatment&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>planning; chair MDTs meetings; participate in clinical research in oncology; participates in&nbsp;equipment procurement&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse - Specialized oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or BSc&nbsp;Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Specialized oncology nursing training&nbsp;at Higher Diploma,&nbsp;MSc Nursing or an&nbsp;accredited oncology program&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provide nursing care to cancer patients in&nbsp;collaboration with other members of the MDT;&nbsp;health education; screening activities; comprehensive patient assessments; symptom&nbsp;management; management of treatment side&nbsp;effects; patient navigation activities; clinical research in oncology; advocacy; mentorship and&nbsp;teaching; policy formulation and implementation; screening activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer registrars</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Degree/diploma&nbsp;holder in Health Records &amp; information.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in cancer&nbsp;registration from&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>African Cancer Registry Network (AFCRN)&nbsp;approved provider</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer data abstraction, maintenance of cancer&nbsp;patients records and participation in cancer&nbsp;research</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical pharmacist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Masters in clinical&nbsp;pharmacy or equivalent&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to Practice&nbsp;by PPB.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;- Training and certification in chemotherapy&nbsp;handling and administration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Head of pharmaceutical oncology services; allocation of duties; supervision; member of MDT;&nbsp;research; in charge of supply chain of oncology&nbsp;commodities; in-charge of preparation of chemotherapy medications</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical counselors&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma/degree in&nbsp;Psychological counseling.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- License to practice&nbsp;from relevant body</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Counseling of patients and their caregivers/families on cancer; patient navigation; research;&nbsp;member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Housekeeping&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Staff</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Relevant training in&nbsp;housekeeping</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training in safe handling of hazardous&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Products</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Handling of waste and cleaning</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical social&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Worker</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma or bachelors&nbsp;in social Sciences</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Assessment of socio-economic background of&nbsp;patients; Contact tracing; patient navigation;&nbsp;research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse - General&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(adult care and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>pediatric care)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Certification in chemotherapy handling and&nbsp;administration (those&nbsp;working in chemotherapy units)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Undergone an appropriate preceptorship/mentorship program in cancer management for at least 3 or 6&nbsp; months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Providing nursing care to cancer patients in&nbsp;collaboration with other members of the MDT,&nbsp;in all areas of cancer treatment; health education; screening activities; participate in clinical&nbsp;research in oncology; screening activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nutritionists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or degree in&nbsp;Nutrition or Masters</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- License to practice&nbsp;from Nutritionists &amp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Dieticians Council</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provision of nutritional counseling and support&nbsp;to patients and their families/caregivers; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Porters/patient navigators</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training in customer&nbsp;service&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- First aid Training&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Ferrying of patients between service points&nbsp;within the facility</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Quality Assurance&nbsp;Officer/ Safety&nbsp;health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>A designated Quality&nbsp;Assurance Officer/&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Safety health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Liaise with all departments to ensure safety &amp;&nbsp;quality assurance is embedded in their processes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Infection Prevention and Control</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and Certification in IPC</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>-Monitor the rate of infections</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure proper waste management</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure proper use of PPE</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure hand hygiene compliance</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Supportive Human Resource</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Human resource category&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Minimum Qualifications&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Required staff establishment (number)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical Officers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MBCHB</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by KMPDB - Training&nbsp;and certification in&nbsp;chemotherapy handling and administration</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Health education; screening activities; assess,&nbsp;prescribe, administer subsequent cancer treatment under supervision of an oncologist; participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical Officers in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Higher National&nbsp;Diploma in Clinical&nbsp;Medicine Oncology.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by the Clinical Officers&nbsp;Council</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Health education; screening activities; assess,prescribe and administer subsequent cancer&nbsp;treatment under supervision of an oncologist;&nbsp;participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurses - Palliative&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>care</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Specialized Palliative&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>care nursing - Higher&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Diploma, MSc Nursing&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>or an accredited Palliative program&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of K</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the palliative&nbsp;care services in the facility; nursing care to cancer patients in the MDT; comprehensive patient&nbsp;assessments; Pain and Symptom management;&nbsp;Management of treatment side effects; Patient&nbsp;navigation activities; initiating , organizing and&nbsp;facilitating family conferences and advance care&nbsp;planning; end of life and bereavement care;&nbsp;clinical research in palliative care; advocacy;&nbsp;mentorship and teaching; policy formulation&nbsp;and implementation</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Pharmaceutical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>technologists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma/Higher&nbsp;National diploma in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Pharmacy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Enrolled to Practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by PPB&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and certification in chemotherapy handling and administration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Preparation of chemotherapy medications&nbsp;under supervision of a clinical pharmacist; research; supply chain management of oncology&nbsp;commodities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Pharmacists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Degree in pharmacy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to Practice&nbsp;by PPB&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and certification in chemotherapy&nbsp;handling and administration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Preparation of chemotherapy medications under supervision of a clinical pharmacist; member of MDT; research; supply chain management&nbsp;of oncology commodities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>','2022-07-18 12:47:14','2022-07-18 12:47:14'),(46,48,'Chemotherapy Equipment','<p>Equipment must have service contracts and appropriate measures for plans for preventive maintenance purposes and provide service stickers showing dates for last service and next service due dates. Elements that are important for the life of the equipment and for safety shall be addressed early in the planning stage and should be included in contractual forms, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Compliance with quality and safety standards</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Acceptance tests and conditions to correct deficiencies revealed during acceptance</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Warranty conditions</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Enforceable assurances on availability of maintenance support (technical and financial), manufacturer support, manuals and spare parts</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Training of all users and keep documentation of the same</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>Acceptance testing and commissioning</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Commissioning is done by the manufacturer or his representative, Biomedical Engineer and the Clinical Pharmacist. A record keeping system should also be in place. After commissioning has been completed, the specific tests needed for ongoing quality control and safety assurance will need to be carried out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chemotherapy Unit equipment</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chemotherapy administration area</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chemotherapy chairs</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Assorted hospital beds&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bedside cabinets&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Wheelchairs</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hazardous drug spill kit&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Infusion pumps</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>4-hooked mobile drip stands&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Lockable cabinets&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Crash cart for emergency/resuscitation including ambu-bags and masks for appropriate ages</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Suction machine&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oxygen &amp; oxygen masks</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Weighing scale</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Heightometer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Vital signs monitor including sphygmomanometer, thermometer, pulse oximeter Measuring Cylinders</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stretchers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Procedure trolleys</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Portable examination lamps</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Audio-visual equipment &ndash;Television</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clock</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>ICT equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Chemotherapy reconstitution area-needs to be lockable&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>A biosafety cabinet, class 2B2 and above (must have a exhauster fitted 2 meters above the building roof)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hazardous drug spill kit&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Lockable cabinets&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Steel / granite working surface area&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>An eye wash area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Air conditioner&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Oncology Pharmacy</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pharmaceutical Refrigerator with temperature monitors for oncology medicines</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Lockable cabinets</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Weighing balance</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Measuring Cylinders</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Secure storage</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Steel / granite working surface</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Reference books (e.g. Martindale, other Pharmacopoeias)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Pharmacy consultation room</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Furniture</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chairs</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Desk</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Screening</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>HPV test machines and kits</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>PAP smear kits</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>VIA/VILI reagents and commodities,&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical breast exams</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Fecal occult blood test</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Digital rectal exam</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Cryotherapy and thermal ablation with the appropriate staff</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Consultation room</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Equipment to take vital signs &ndash; BP machine, thermometer,&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Examination table</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Furniture:</p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Desk</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Chair</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Shelves</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Availability of</p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Computer</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Printer</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Scanner</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Health Management Information Service</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chaplaincy and Counseling</p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>IEC materials</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Information on nutrition, sexual dysfunction and healthy lifestyle</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Palliative Care &amp; survivorship Unit</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Furniture&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Examination couch</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Storage cabinets and desks</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chairs</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dressing trolleys</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Drip stands</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>BP machine</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Thermometers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Weighing scales</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Infusion/syringe pumps</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Electronics</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Printer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Rehabilitation unit</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Appropriate rehabilitation equipment and commodities e.g. Lymphedema stockings, stoma bags, prostheses etc</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Cancer registry office</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Lockable designated Office space</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Filing shelves&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computer with internet connectivity</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Furniture</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Working top</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Notice board</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-18 12:48:11','2022-07-18 12:48:11'),(47,49,'Chemotherapy Physical Infrastructure','<p>The cancer centre shall ensure the physical infrastructure meets the following requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient flow</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Capacity for electricity, water, power backup, space</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safety considerations &ndash; fire</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separation of adult from paediatric management areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disability infrastructure in all areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Maintenance considerations</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chemotherapy Unit Services Areas</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient registration and reception area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Triage room/observation room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Procedure rooms&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Counselling room&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waiting area for patients/caregivers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Designated Consultation room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chemotherapy administration area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oncology pharmacy</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chemo holding/receiving station in close proximity to the chemo administration area-with shelves, work tops, a hand washing area and hooks</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>At least one isolation room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Emergency room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Storage area for hazardous chemotherapy drugs with appropriate ventilation. Ideally, storage areas should have negative air pressure in relation to surrounding areas and have 12 air changes per hour</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chemotherapy reconstitution area should be large enough to contain a bio-safety cabinet</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Staff changing area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Staff room/conference room&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pantry room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate staff and patients rest rooms&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Sluice room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Storage facility for cytotoxic waste and other wastes</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disposal facilities for cytotoxic and other wastes Eye wash station/shower</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Waste Management</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Modern incinerator with combustion capacity above 1200oC</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waste Holding Area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-18 12:48:50','2022-07-18 12:48:50'),(48,50,'Surgical Oncology Operational Considerations','<h3><strong>1.1 Service Norms</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The National Guidelines for Cancer Management shall form the basis for clinical management at the facility.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The centre or unit must have NCI-K approved protocols for diagnosis and treatment of all malignancies they manage founded on sound scientific principles and evidence-based medicine which must be accessible to the prescribers, pharmacists and nurses at the centre at all times.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The protocols must be updated as appropriate and be readily available for inspection when needed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The centre or unit shall also commit to quality improvement, supporting cancer research and improving the training and mentoring of health care e. The centre or unit shall have infrastructure in place to be able to carry out cancer registration and reporting to the National Cancer Registry and KHIS.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.2 Service Delivery Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Every cancer centre shall:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Formulate and prominently display a service charter that details the roles and responsibilities of both the patient and the centre.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide integrated and multidisciplinary care&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Prioritize coordination and planning for professionals to help facilitate access to care at other levels of care, including awareness creation, screening/early detection, case management and appropriate downward referrals.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a reasonable time frame &ndash; definitive/tissue diagnosis should be done preferably within 2 weeks and the initiation of appropriate treatment within a month of diagnosis.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The recommended time frame between diagnosis and Surgery should be at least 120 days.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Follow evidence-based protocols and guidelines.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have informed consent obtained prior to all procedures including treatments. In case of a minor, a parent/guardian shall give consent. The information prior to consenting shall be provided in a manner easily understandable by the patient. The rights of the child should be prioritized.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish clear navigation systems to enable patients&rsquo; access to services.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Design patient-tracking systems for patient follow-up throughout the continuum of care.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Develop standard operating procedures for every service being provided</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.3 Clinical considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide cancer management that is holistic and patient-centred for best care outcomes.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Before initiation of treatment, clearly define and communicate the goals of care to the patient in accordance with a patient care plan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide the patient the right to detailed information on his/her condition, treatment options including clinical trials, side effects, expected outcome and prognosis.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow the patient the right to seek a second or additional opinion before consenting to initiation of treatment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all aspects of carefully documented, stored and easily retrievable.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow access of patients to their records as well as laboratory samples when needed&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Comprehensively document patient history</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.4 Multi-disciplinary Tumor Boards</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Definition; the multidisciplinary expert team that should manage cancer patients in a consultative approach</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;The cancer centre shall:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish multidisciplinary teams (MDTs)/tumor boards which shall guide and direct cancer management&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have MDTs meet regularly and have participation from all relevant disciplines depending on the cancer case and the level of care&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all complex cases discussed by a multidisciplinary team&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have an MDT coordinator who will organize for meetings, keep records of discussions and provide reports on cancer patient management&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Utilize technology to convene virtual MDT discussions with proper documentation</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>It consists of different experts including &ndash; medical oncologist, radiation/clinical oncologist, surgeon, pathologist, palliative physician and specialists, oncology pharmacist, oncology nurse, radiologist, interventional radiologist, haematologist, medical physicist, radiation therapist/therapy radiographer, medical laboratory technologists specialized in different laboratory disciplines.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.5 Diagnostic imaging</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(i) Incorporate clinical findings in conducting diagnostic imaging modalities&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(ii) Consider image-guided diagnostics where applicable</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(iii) Use a standard protocol for conducting imaging procedures</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(iv) Use internationally and locally recognized standards and guidelines for the safe installation, operation and use of imaging equipment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(v) Use a standard imaging diagnostic reporting protocol&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(vi) Outsource/provide access to an accredited imaging diagnostic facility</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.6 Nursing Considerations&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:-</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Provide oncology and palliative nursing care for the entire continuum of care(Prevention, Awareness, screening, early detection, diagnosis, treatment, survivorship and end of life care, bereavement).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Support the coordinating role of oncology and palliative care nurses in the&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>care team and community linkage for cancer patients</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.7 Surgical Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:-</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have Surgical site marking protocol implemented (standard site identification process, patient involved in marking, and marking done by the one doing procedure.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a Safe surgery checklist (evidence of use for verifying correct site, correct procedure, correct patient; availability of informed consent; and equipment needed are on hand, correct, and functional) See checklist&nbsp;<a href=\"about:blank\">Resources\\Safe surgery checklist.pdf</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide Evidence that facility has an active process of monitoring safe surgical checklist compliance.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ensure the organization uses a &ldquo;time-out&rdquo; procedure just before starting a surgical procedure.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Facilitate patients to access surgical diagnosis and treatment for solid malignancies through a multidisciplinary team approach.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Where tissue is obtained for histological examination, have the surgeon observe the SOP for histology specimen handling, storage and transport.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have surgical treatment offered conforming to internationally recognized, evidence-based surgical-oncological practices</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.8 Palliative Care and Survivorship Considerations&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Provide palliative care from the point of cancer diagnosis and at all times throughout the course of illness.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Integrate palliative care with other health services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Prioritize and provide effective relief of pain and other distressing symptoms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Provide timely rehabilitative and supportive services.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Facilitate formation of patient support groups.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Establish survivorship programs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Adhere to the National Palliative Care Policy and the National Palliative Care&nbsp;Guideline.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.9 Equipment Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Have all the facilities and equipment registered and licensed for safe and effective conduct of its services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have access to a qualified biomedical engineer, who is ultimately responsible for ensuring that all equipment are in proper working condition and that the necessary safety devices are fitted and in working order.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Maintain service contracts and schedules of service with the contracted service providers to ensure regular servicing as per the manufacturer&rsquo;s instructions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Ensure equipment compliance with relevant regulations according to the appropriate governing regulatory body.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Ensure safe disposal of obsolete or unserviceable equipment as guided by the relevant regulatory body.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.10 Referral Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Develop patient referral SOPs which conform to the national referral guidelines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Properly document referrals to and away from the facility.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Promote upward, downward and horizontal referral where appropriate.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Facilitate referrals for specialized services that are unavailable at the centre to facilities that are accessible and are accredited by the relevant regulatory body.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Assess patients for fitness to travel and provide necessary supportive mechanisms (ambulance, nurse, oxygen supply) before referral.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Provide proper patient counseling on cancer, tests to be done, costs implications and expected treatment before referral.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Refer a patient to the right specialist for further management if a service outside oncology services is required</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.11 Quality Assurance</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Establish a Quality Assurance Programme (QAP) that is adequately supervised and provides reports to NCI Kenya as required.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have risk assessment measures in place with objectives and systematic monitoring and evaluation so as to identify problems and system failures and guide the necessary action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Have regular morbidity and mortality meetings to identify specific clinical performance indicators.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.12 Infection Prevention and Control</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Oncology patients are at increased infection risk due to immunosuppression and frequent exposure to healthcare settings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a hospital&rsquo;s infection prevention and control program must be in accordance with the WHO Practical Guidelines for Infection Control.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have hand-washing facilities for staff readily available. Hand sanitizers should be provided at every work station.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide a designated sluicing area for linen generated in the Surgical area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have isolation rooms and practice barrier nursing by ensuring PPEs are available and easily accessible.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide decontamination and sterilization areas. (The decontaminant, sodium hypochlorite 5%)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.13 Occupational health and safety</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Implement the Occupational, Health &amp; Safety (OSH) Act in the workplace.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide safety and health training at least once every 3 years.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Be subject to annual inspection by the local regulatory body and adhere to the basic safety standards as set by the regulatory body.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disclose labeling laws for identification and classification of chemicals by types of hazards, including medication labels and safety data sheets.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a system for incidents monitoring and management at the workplace.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have programs to monitor and support employee performance, mental health, work-life balance and put in place debriefing programs.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.14 Waste Management</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide waste segregation and disposal amenities.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Conduct regular capacity building on waste disposal for all healthcare providers including support staff.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide appropriate PPEs for handling clinical waste</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.15 Emergency Medical Care&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have facilities and human resources to handle Surgical Oncology emergencies.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ensure medical staffs are trained in BLS/ACLS.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stabilize the patient and expeditiously refer for emergency management where applicable.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Be well equipped with resuscitation commodities and equipment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.16 Adverse Events</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Any adverse event that occurs as a result of the surgery must be documented, discussed internally and reported to the relevant regulatory bodies such as the Pharmacy and Poisons Board, relevant regulatory body and the NCI-K.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.17 Death of a Patient</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Document all deaths occurring whilst patients are undergoing treatment appropriately.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Offer bereavement support to the family.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Have periodic mortality meetings where cancer deaths are discussed by a multidisciplinary team</p>','2022-07-18 12:49:51','2022-07-18 13:45:20'),(49,51,'Surgical Oncology Physical Infrastructure','<p>The cancer centre shall ensure the physical infrastructure meets the following requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient flow</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Capacity for electricity, water, power backup, space</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safety considerations &ndash; fire</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separation of adult from pediatric management areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disability infrastructure in all areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Maintenance considerations</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.1 All departments and units</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>For centres operating within the precincts of a hospital, it can utilize similar facilities within the hospital. For stand-alone centres, these services must be provided for:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>a. Appropriate space for the following administrative services:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Administration</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Finance</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Transport</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iv. Supply chain management</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;v. Laundry</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;vi. Healthcare waste management, including hazardous drug waste, a Lockable holding area, proper segregation and disposal, MOUs with disposal companies</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;vii. Conference room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ix. Reception area</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>b. Utilities</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate patient and staff changing rooms</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate staff and patients rest rooms</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Staff room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.2 Health records and information &ndash; registration area</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Office space</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Filing room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Use of NACARE system for reporting is required using secure internet.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.3 Other supportive services</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Provision for day care services where applicable</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cancer registry office</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Office space</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Filing room</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.4 Surgical Oncology Unit</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Patient registration and reception area</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Waiting area for patients and caregivers</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Consultation room&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Triage/observation room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Counseling room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Procedure room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Pharmacy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>h. Operating theatre capable of handling minor and major surgical procedures with a Patient receiving room and a patient recovery room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>i. Nutrition</p>\r\n\r\n<p>j. Palliative care</p>\r\n\r\n<p>k. Medical Laboratory Unit</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Support from;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Diagnostic radiology unit</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pathology unit</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Blood banking</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Critical care unit</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Rehabilitation centres&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Endoscopy services</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Morgue services</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.5 Inpatient oncology wards</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Separate female, male, adolescents, geriatric and pediatric wards&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Side room facilities for ward reviews of post-operative wounds, minor procedures, and emergency resuscitation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Isolation rooms for patients with infectious conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Waste management facilities</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.6 Palliative Care and Survivorship Unit</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Patient registration and reception area</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Waiting area for patients/caregivers</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Counseling room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Procedure room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Consultation room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Community room large enough to accommodate support groups</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Support services</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Pharmacy</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Nutrition</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Chaplaincy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iv. Counseling&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;v. Rehabilitative unit</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Pediatrics play area</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Nutrition counseling rooms</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.7 Design and construction requirements</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The design of any surgery department revolves around environmental control, traffic control, and the desire to prevent surgical site infection (SSI).&nbsp;<a href=\"about:blank\">Resources\\Surgical Operating Theatres Standards.docx</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Consult the Services of a registered Architectural and structural Engineering firms, with expertise in construction of health care facilities, for the design and construction.</p>','2022-07-18 12:51:04','2022-07-18 13:54:08'),(50,52,'Surgical Oncology Equipment','<p>Equipment must have service contracts and appropriate measures for plans for preventive maintenance purposes and provide service stickers showing dates for last service and next service due dates.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Elements that are important for the life of the equipment and for safety shall be addressed early in the planning stage and should be included in contractual forms, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Compliance with quality and safety standards</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Acceptance tests and conditions to correct deficiencies revealed during acceptance</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Warranty conditions</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Enforceable assurances on availability of maintenance support</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;(technical and financial), manufacturer support, manuals and spare parts</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Training of all users and keep documentation of the same</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Acceptance, testing and commissioning</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Commissioning is done by the manufacturer or his representative, Biomedical Engineer and the Surgeon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A record keeping system should also be in place. After commissioning has been completed, the specific tests needed for ongoing quality control and safety assurance will need to be carried out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Equipment Donation</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The donations should be guided by the principles developed by the WHO.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There should be effective communication between the donor, the recipient authority and, whenever possible, the end-user, before, during and after the donation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Surgical Oncology Unit Equipment</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Fully equipped major and minor theatres with standard anaesthetic, surgical and interventional equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Receiving area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pre-operative room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Post-operative room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Scrubbing room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Changing room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waiting area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Fully equipped endoscopy suite</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>In-patient Surgical Wards</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Wards</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Beds</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Wheelchairs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Trolleys</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iv. Consumable and reusable equipment for IV and medication equipment</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Phlebotomy equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bedside Cabinets</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurses&rsquo; station with cabinets/shelves</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>BP Monitors</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Thermometers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Weighing scale</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Heightometer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Crash cart</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waste segregation bins</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medicine Cabinets&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Consumables cabinets</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Decommissioning requirements</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Safety assessment survey report of the hazards involved during decommissioning exercise. Have a Decommissioning Plan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Have a hazardous waste management, transport and disposal plan for the decommissioning.</p>','2022-07-18 12:52:20','2022-07-18 13:44:55'),(51,53,'Surgical Oncology Human Resource','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Anesthesiologists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Biomedical engineer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical Lab personnel&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Cancer Registrar</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical Officer anesthetist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurse anesthetist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Gynaecology Oncologist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Housekeeping staff</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Interventional radiologists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical Officers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical social worker</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurse &ndash; General with theatre experience</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nutritionist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical/ hemato-onco, Pediatric, Radiation Oncologists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Surgeons</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Q/A</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>IPC</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical Counsellors</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Physiotherapists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pharmacists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurse-palliative care</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Occupational therapists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Core human resource</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Human resource category&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Minimum Qualifications&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Anesthesiologists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMed in Anesthesia&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management;&nbsp;in charge of ICU/HDU</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED and a fellowship in medical oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;as an oncologist by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer&nbsp;centre/facility; assessment, initiation, review of&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>patients cancer treatment; chair MDTs meetings;&nbsp;participate in clinical research in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Pediatric Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED Paediatrics&nbsp;with fellowship in paediatric oncology</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer&nbsp;centre/facility; cancer diagnosis; assessment,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>initiation, review of paediatric patients cancer&nbsp;treatment; chair MDTs meetings; participate in&nbsp;clinical research in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Gynaecology&nbsp;Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED Obs/Gyne with&nbsp;a fellowship in Gynae&nbsp;Oncology.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;as a Gynae oncologist&nbsp;by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer&nbsp;centre/facility; assessment, initiation, surgical&nbsp;management and review of gynaecological&nbsp;cancer patients; participate in MDTs meetings;&nbsp;participate in clinical research in oncology;&nbsp;screening for gynae cancers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation oncologists/clinical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED/Fellowship in&nbsp;radiation oncology/</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Clinical oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;as an oncologist by&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; in charge of radiotherapy treatment;&nbsp;assessment, initiation, review of patients cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>treatment and patient follow up; treatment&nbsp;planning; chair MDTs meetings; participate in&nbsp;clinical research in oncology; participates in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>equipment procurement&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Haemato-oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED/Fellowship&nbsp;with specialization in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>hemato-oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; cancer diagnosis; assessment, initiation, review of patients cancer treatment; chair&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>MDTs meetings; participate in clinical research&nbsp;in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical Officer&nbsp;anesthetist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Higher Diploma in&nbsp;Anesthesia&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by the Clinical Officers Council</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management&nbsp;in consultation with the anesthesiologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer registrars</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Degree/diploma&nbsp;holder in Health Records &amp; information.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>registration from&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>African Cancer Registry Network (AFCRN)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>approved provider</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer data abstraction, maintenance of cancer&nbsp;patients records and participation in cancer&nbsp;research</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical counselors&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma/degree in&nbsp;psychological counseling.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- License to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>from relevant body</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Counseling of patients and their caregivers/families on cancer; patient navigation; research;member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Housekeeping&nbsp;staff</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Relevant training in&nbsp;housekeeping</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training in safe handling of hazardous&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>products</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Handling of waste and cleaning</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical social&nbsp;worker</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma or bachelors&nbsp;in social Sciences</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Assessment of socio-economic background of&nbsp;patients; Contact tracing; patient navigation;&nbsp;research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse - General(adult care and&nbsp;pediatric care)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Have Theatre experience/Training in Theatre Nurs</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Providing nursing care to cancer patients in&nbsp;collaboration with other members of the MDT,&nbsp;in all areas of cancer treatment; health education; screening activities; participate in clinical&nbsp;research in oncology; screening activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nutritionists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or degree in&nbsp;Nutrition&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- License to practice&nbsp;from Nutritionists &amp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Dieticians Council</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provision of nutritional counseling and support&nbsp;to patients and their families/caregivers; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Quality Assurance&nbsp;Officer/ Safety&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>A designated Quality&nbsp;Assurance Officer/&nbsp;Safety health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Liaise with all departments to ensure safety &amp;&nbsp;quality assurance is embedded in their processes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Infection Prevention and Control</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and Certification in IPC</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>-Monitor the rate of infections</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure proper waste management</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure proper use of PPE</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure hand hygiene compliance</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Biomedical engineering officers&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(medical engineers or technologist)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or bachelors&nbsp;in medical engineering&nbsp;and trained on maintenance of cancer equipment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered by the&nbsp;Association of Medical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Engineers of Kenya&nbsp;(AMEK) or relevant&nbsp;international body</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Installation, maintaining service contracts and&nbsp;equipment documentation and regular maintenance of cancer equipment at t</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Pharmacists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Degree in pharmacy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to Practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by PPB&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and certification in chemotherapy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>handling and administration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Preparation of chemotherapy medications under supervision of a clinical pharmacist; member of MDT; research; supply chain management&nbsp;of oncology commodities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Surgeons</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED Surgery or&nbsp;equivalent and/or specialization in Oncology.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of a surgical cancer&nbsp;facility; assessment, conduct surgery and review&nbsp;of cancer patients after surgery; participate in&nbsp;research and MDT activities; patient referrals</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical Laboratory technologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or degree&nbsp;in Medical Laboratory&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(Bsc) or related discipline&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;- Registered and&nbsp;licensed by KMLTTB&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Each section of the&nbsp;laboratory to be headed by a medical laboratory technologist with&nbsp;a diploma in Medical&nbsp;Laboratory Sciences in&nbsp;the disciplines</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;- Clinical Cytology/Histopathology, Biochemistry, Microbiology, Immunology,&nbsp;Molecular Sciences,&nbsp;Blood Transfusion/Haematology Sciences,&nbsp;Epidemiology, public&nbsp;health or virology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provide lab services, research; sample collection;&nbsp;safe waste disposal; relay of results</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Supportive Human Resource/Auxilliary/Adjunct</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Human resource category&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Minimum Qualifications&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical Officers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MBCHB</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by KMPDB - Training&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>and certification in&nbsp;chemotherapy handling and administration</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Health education; screening activities; assess,&nbsp;prescribe, administer subsequent cancer treatment under supervision of an oncologist; participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurses - Palliative&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>care</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Specialized Palliative&nbsp;care nursing - Higher&nbsp;Diploma, MSc Nursing&nbsp;or an accredited Palliative program&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the palliative&nbsp;care services in the facility; nursing care to cancer patients in the MDT; comprehensive patient&nbsp;assessments; Pain and Symptom management;&nbsp;Management of treatment side effects; Patient&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>navigation activities; initiating , organizing and&nbsp;facilitating family conferences and advance care&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>planning; end of life and bereavement care;&nbsp;clinical research in palliative care; advocacy;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>mentorship and teaching; policy formulation&nbsp;and implementation</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse anesthetist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Higher diploma in&nbsp;anesthesia</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed by NCK</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management&nbsp;in consultation with the anesthesiologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Interventional&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>radiologists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED in radiology</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Fellowship in interventional Radiology</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;by KMDPB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>In-charge of interventional diagnostic radiology&nbsp;activities including biopsy collection; research;&nbsp;member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Occupational&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>therapists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma, higher diploma or bachelors in&nbsp;occupational therapy</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provision of rehabilitative services to patients;&nbsp;research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Physiotherapists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma, higher diploma or bachelors in&nbsp;physiotherapy</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provision of rehabilitative services to patients;&nbsp;research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-18 12:53:30','2022-07-18 13:44:28'),(52,54,'Radiotherapy Operational Considerations','<h3><strong>1.1 Procedure for designation as a radiotherapy Cancer Centre</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A facility that plans to offer radiotherapy cancer service must apply for designation to NCI Kenya and should adhere to the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The proposal for the radiotherapy Cancer Centre designation shall specify the objectives of the cancer management program, the range of services to be provided, the approximate number of patients to be treated, and the physical infrastructure, equipment, human resources and operational management resources, as laid out in this document.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The facility will be issued with a comprehensive checklist of the components required for a radiotherapy Cancer Centre before it submits the application for designation.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Proposals for a radiotherapy Cancer Centre designation shall be submitted to the Chief Executive Officer National Cancer Institute Kenya (NCI-K), together with the application form for approval not less than 90 days before the intended commencement of operations of the cancer center.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Only upon final approval by the NCI-K will a facility be designated as a radiotherapy Cancer Centre. NCI-K will ensure that the Centre maintains the services and standards outlined in these Guidelines in order to retain this designation. The certificate of radiotherapy Cancer Management Centre designation (based on the service (s) to be offered) will be issued by NCI-K and shall be displayed at the facility.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>NCI-K will conduct inspections and accreditation after every two years to ensure compliance to the guideline, however NCI-K can conduct adhoc inspections to ensure standards are maintained.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.2 Service Norms for Radiotherapy Cancer Centres</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The National Guidelines for radiotherapy Cancer Management shall form the basis for clinical management at the facility.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The radiotherapy centre or unit must have NCI-K approved protocols for treatment of all malignancies they manage founded on sound scientific principles and evidence-based medicine which must be accessible to the radiotherapy clinical team at the centre at all times.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The protocols must be updated as appropriate, readily available and displayed.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The radiotherapy centre or unit shall also commit to quality improvement, supporting cancer research and improving the training and mentoring of health care&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The radiotherapy centre or unit shall have infrastructure in place to be able to carry out cancer registration and notification to the National Cancer Registry.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.3 Service Delivery Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Every radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Formulate and prominently display a service charter that details the roles and responsibilities of both the patient and the centre.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide integrated and multidisciplinary care</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Prioritize coordination and planning for professionals to help facilitate access to care at other levels of care, including awareness creation,screening/early detection, case management and appropriate referrals.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a reasonable time frame &ndash; Radiotherapy treatments should commence &nbsp; within 2 weeks post treatment planning completion.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Follow evidence-based protocols and guidelines.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have informed consent obtained prior to all radiotherapy treatments. In case of a minor, a parent/guardian shall give consent. The information prior to consenting shall be provided in a manner easily understandableby the patient. The rights of the child should be prioritized.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish clear navigation systems to enable patients&rsquo; access to services.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Design patient-tracking systems for patient follow-up throughout the continuum of care.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Develop standard operating procedures for every service being provided.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.4 Clinical Radiotherapy Management Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide cancer management that is holistic and patient-centred for best care outcomes&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Before initiation of treatment, clearly define and communicate the goals of care to the patient in accordance with a patient care plan</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide the patient the right to detailed information on his/her condition, treatment options including clinical trials, side effects, expected outcome and prognosis.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow the patient the right to seek a second or additional opinion before consenting to initiation of treatment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all aspects of carefully documented, stored and easily retrievable.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow access of patients to their records as well as medical reports when needed</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Comprehensively document patient history</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3><br />\r\n<strong>1.5 Multi-disciplinary Tumor Boards</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish multidisciplinary teams (MDTs)/tumour boards which shall guide and direct cancer management</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have MDTs meet regularly and have participation from all relevant disciplines depending on the cancer case and the level of care</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all complex cases discussed by a multidisciplinary team</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have an MDT coordinator who will organize for meetings, keep records of discussions and&nbsp; provide reports on cancer patient management</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The outcomes of the MDT&rsquo;s discussion must be documented in the patient file.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Utilize technology to convene virtual MDT discussions with proper documentation of the same&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.6 CT Simulation Capacity Considerations</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pretreatment&nbsp; imaging</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Incorporate clinical findings in conducting pretreatment imaging modalities</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use a dedicated wide bore CT simulator with aperture of not less than 70cm preferably 80cm</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Reference room lasers should be installed&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use a standard&nbsp; simulation protocol for pretreatment Imaging</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use internationally and locally recognized standards and guidelines for the safe installation, operation and use of imaging equipment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Incorporate appropriate and site specific immobilization devices&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Incase CT simulator is not available, a conventional simulator must be available.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Radiation Oncology Considerations</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy centre shall:<br />\r\na) Provide radiation oncology services in adherence to IAEA and local regulatory body guidelines including radiation safety protection.<br />\r\nb) Fully document all ionizing radiation therapeutic applications and maintain proper records for treatment planning simulation, isodose distribution plan, dosimetry, brachytherapy and physics documentation.<br />\r\nc) Deliver the most novel and advanced technologies available for radiation oncology. These technologies should be cost-eﬀective, efficient, upgradable and practical.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d) Provide adequate information to patients receiving radiotherapy regarding the procedure to be done.<br />\r\ne) For brachytherapy source, acquire relevant licenses from KNRA that guides source shipping, handling, storage and disposal upon depletion of radioisotopes including radiation safety program designed for the practice.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.7 Occupational health and safety considerations:</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy central shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Be subject to annual inspection by the local regulatory body and adhere to the basic safety standards as set by the regulatory body.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disclose labeling laws for identification and classification of radiation by types of hazards, including radiation labels and safety data sheets.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish a system for identification and surveillance of exposure: estimating the number of workers who come into contact with substances and are employed in occupations with increased carcinogenic risk, and reducing to minimum the number of workers exposed, the duration of exposure and the degree of exposure, and establishing an appropriate system of records.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ensure medical surveillance applies to all healthcare workers in the radiotherapy unit and includes assessment and documentation of symptom complaints, physical findings &amp; laboratory values</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide personal protective equipment for workers and decontamination facilities in the workplace.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish/develop guidelines and recommendations for proper use and handling of radio-active substances and training packages for healthcare workers.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a system of monitoring services at the workplace and assess occupational exposures.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Empower workers by providing them with access to information about their exposures and risks.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have programs to monitor employee performance, mental health, work-life balance and put in place debriefing programs.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.8 Waste Management</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dispose radioactive waste produced in the process of the diagnosis and treatment of cancer in accordance to international and relevant local guidelines.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have written policies and SOPs for hazardous waste describing requirements for the segregation, packaging, labeling, collection, transportation and storage of waste within the facility.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide waste disposal amenities and commodities.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Conduct regular capacity building on waste disposal for all healthcare providers including support staff.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide appropriate PPEs for handling hazardous waste.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Minimize the risk of contaminating the local water supply and/or soil with radio-active waste. Hazardous materials shall never be discarded into waste water (sink or toilet) or into a landfill.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.9 Emergency Medical Care</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Have facilities and human resources to handle oncologic and palliative care emergencies.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Develop and display SOPs on emergency care.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Ensure medical staffs are trained in BLS/ACLS.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Stabilize the patient and expeditiously refer for emergency management where applicable.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Be well equipped with resuscitation commodities and equipment.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1.10 Adverse Events</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Document, discuss internally, put in place mitigation measures then report to the relevant regulatory body any adverse event that occurs as a result of cancer diagnosis or treatment.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><br />\r\n<strong>1.11 Death of a Patient</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Document all deaths occurring whilst patients are undergoing treatment appropriately.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Offer bereavement support to the family.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have periodic mortality meetings where cancer deaths are discussed by a multidisciplinary team.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-18 12:56:33','2022-07-18 12:56:33'),(53,55,'Radiotherapy Human Resource','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The human resource requirements for the chemotherapy centre are as follows with core staff and supportive staff</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Human resource category</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Minimum Qualifica- tions</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Staff Establishment</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Anesthesiologists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MMed in Anesthesis</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p>(Licensed to practice by&nbsp; KMPDB)</p>\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management; in charge of ICU/HDU</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Biomedical engineering officers (medical engineers or technologist)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or bachelors in medical engineering and trained on maintenance of cancer equipment.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered by the Association of Medical Engineers of Kenya (AMEK) or relevant international body</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Installation, maintaining service contracts and equipment documentation and regular maintenance of cancer equipment at the&nbsp; facility</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer registrars</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Degree/diploma holder in Health Records &amp; information management (registered by AMRO-K or by an established HRIM Board)</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in cancer registration and notification by NCI-K or NCI-K approved provider.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer data abstraction, notification/data entry and maintenance of cancer patients records and participation in cancer research.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Reception and registration, storage, filing and retrieval, clinic preparation, file tracing, report generation/sharing and editing files.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical counselors</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma/degree in psychological counseling.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice from relevant body</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Counseling of patients and their caregivers/ families on cancer; patient navigation; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical Officer anesthetist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Higher Diploma in Anesthesia</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice by the Clinical Officers Council</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management in consultation with the&nbsp; anesthesiologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinically qualified Medical Physicists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Bsc in physics with postgraduate training in medical physics or Msc Medical Physics with clinical training in radiotherapy physics</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Responsible for equipment selection, specifications, acceptance, delivery, design of installations and shielding requirements, com- missioning and management for radiotherapy, diagnostics and nuclear medicine; Treatment planning in collaboration with the radiation oncologist; safety assessment, establishment, measurement and supervision of QA for radiotherapy and nuclear medicine devices; radiation protection and safety; dose calibration and instrumentation; technical supervision of maintenance; research and innovation of new medical devices; teaching &ndash; radiation protection &amp; users of equipment.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Housekeeping staff</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Relevant training in housekeeping</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Training in safe handling of hazardous products</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Handling of waste and cleaning</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical Officers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MBCHB</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice by&nbsp; KMPDB - Training and certification in chemotherapy handling and administration</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Health education; screening activities; assess, prescribe, administer subsequent cancer treatment under supervision of an oncologist; participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical social worker</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or&nbsp; bachelors in social Sciences</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Assessment of socio-economic background of patients; Contact tracing; patient navigation; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Patient navigators</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Training in customer service</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Training in basic life support for non-medical providers</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Receiving and guiding patients</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse anesthetist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Higher diploma in anesthesia</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed by NCK</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management in consultation with the&nbsp; anesthesiologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Oncology nurse&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MSc Nursing or equivalent focused in oncology Nursing or HND oncology nursing&nbsp;</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya (NCK)</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; providing nursing care to cancer patients; health education; screening activities; part of the MDT; comprehensive patient assessments; symptom management; treatment side effects management; patient navigation activities; clinical research in oncology; advocacy; mentorship and teaching; policy formulation and implementation; screening&nbsp; activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>General nurse</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or Degree in Nursing</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>Certification in chemotherapy handling and administration (those working in chemotherapy units)</li>\r\n				<li>Undergone an appropriate induction pro- gram in cancer management</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Providing nursing care to cancer patients in collaboration with other members of the MDT, in all areas of cancer treatment; health education; screening activities; participate in clinical research in oncology; screening&nbsp; activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse Manager</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>BSc Nursing with Specialized oncology nursing training,</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Additional qualification in admin and MSc is an added advantage</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>&nbsp;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Head of Nursing oncology services; Coordination, Directing and organization of patient care activities in the unit; Resource management and Budgeting; Staffing activities; Quality management; Reporting participate in MDTs meetings; Participate in clinical research; policy formulation, implementation and&nbsp; monitoring</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nutritionists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or degree in Nutrition</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>License to practice from Nutritionists &amp; Dieticians Council</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provision of nutritional counseling and support to patients and their families/caregivers; re- search; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation Safety Officer (RSO)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Advanced degree in Medical Physics, Health Physics, radiation physics or equivalent</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Supervised training for 6 months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Radiation Protection and Safety</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Psychologists (both adult and pediatric)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Degree in psychology.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>License to practice from relevant body</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Counseling of patients and their caregivers/ families on cancer; patient navigation; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Quality Assurance Officer/ Safety health officer</p>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Quality assurance officers</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Radiation Safety Officers</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Patient Safety officer</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p>Occupational safe- ty &amp; health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>A designated Quality Assurance Officer/ Safety health officer</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Liaise with all departments to ensure safety &amp; quality assurance is embedded in their processes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation oncologists/clinical oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MMED/Fellowship in radiation oncology/ Clinical oncology</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice as an oncologist by KMPDB</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; in charge of radiotherapy treatment; assessment, initiation, review of patients cancer treatment and patient follow up; treatment planning; chair MDTs meetings; participate in clinical research in oncology; participates in equipment procurement</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Paediatric Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MMED Paediatrics with fellowship in paediatric oncology</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice by&nbsp; KMPDB</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; cancer diagnosis; assessment, initiation, review of paediatric patients cancer treatment; chair MDTs meetings; participate in clinical research in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation Therapists (RTT) /Therapy radiographers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or higher diploma in radiation therapy</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Participate in treatment planning; administer radiotherapy&nbsp; treatment&nbsp; under&nbsp; supervision&nbsp; of the radio-oncologist; participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiotherapy Services Manager</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>The officer in charge to hold at least a bachelor&rsquo;s degree in therapy radiography</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>To head and coordinate radiotherapy services in the centre</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-18 12:57:24','2022-07-18 12:57:24'),(54,56,'Radiotherapy Equipment','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Equipment must have service contracts and appropriate measures for plans for preventive maintenance purposes and provide service stickers showing dates for last service and next service due dates. Elements that are important for the life of the equipment and for safety shall be addressed early in the planning stage and should be included in contractual forms, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Compliance with quality and safety standards</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Acceptance tests and conditions to correct deficiencies revealed during acceptance</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Warranty conditions</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Enforceable assurances on availability of maintenance support (technical and financial), manufacturer support, manuals and spare parts</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Training of all users and keep documentation of the same</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Acceptance testing and commissioning</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Radiation sources need to be safely received, registered and stored; radiation measurement equipment tested and calibrated; shielding properties of special rooms measured; and the radiation sources tested and calibrated. All major equipment will require commissioning including tele therapy machines, imaging machines (simulators), brachytherapy units and TPSs. A record keeping system should also be in place. After commissioning has been completed, the specific tests needed for ongoing quality control and safety assurance will need to be carried out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Commissioning requirements for Radiotherapy unit</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The process of Commissioning involves Pre-Commissioning and Trial run permission.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After completion of construction and installation, the applicant should approach the regulatory body for permission to carry out a trial run for commissioning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For this purpose, the applicant should submit the following to the regulatory body:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Acceptance Tests conducted on the following equipment;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation Protection Program (RPP).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Details regarding availability of qualified and trained manpower &ndash; operator(s), radio pharmacist(s)/radio-chemist(s) and a Board approved Radiological Safety Officer (RSO).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Personnel monitoring services for all radiation workers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Appropriate radiation measuring and monitoring Instruments</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Operational procedure manual</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safe handling tools and devices required for operation and maintenance of the medical cyclotron and auxiliary equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Security Plan</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Submit the Commissioning Test Report&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>After successful trial runs, the applicant becomes eligible for obtaining consent for trial operations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Decommissioning requirements</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>When the medical cyclotron is no longer to be used, the permission for decommissioning shall be obtained from the Radiation Protection Board. The licensee should apply for the decommissioning license and supply the Authority with the following;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safety assessment survey report of the radiological and non-radiological hazards involved during decommissioning exercise.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Decommissioning Plan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation Protection considerations for the decommissioning workers.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Public radiation protection consideration at vicinity.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Qualified Radiation safety supervisor designated for the exercise.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation safety equipment to be used for decommissioning.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radioactive waste management, transport and disposal plan for the decommissioning.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Site radiation decontamination and final radiation survey.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>The licensee shall submit a report on the completion of decommissioning, which includes among others; safe disposal of sources and personnel exposures received during decommissioning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>List of Equipment</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>External Beam Radiation Therapy.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Electronic Portal Imaging Device (EPID) photo imaging device for verification</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>High dose Rate (HDR) brachytherapy machine (afterloader)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>CT/Conventional treatment planning simulator complete with accessories</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dosimetry quality assurance equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation Safety monitoring devices and radiation safety checklists and reporting.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>ICT infrastructure and support</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Treatment planning system</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Standardized rulers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Two-way video cameras, with audio capability</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Appropriate shielding requirements of radiation sources</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>3-D water scan phantom</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Range of radiation dosimeters for measuring radiation doses</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Immobilization devices</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mould room equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provision for anaesthesia space and recovery if facility is to offer pediatric radiation therapy</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-18 12:58:29','2022-07-18 12:58:29'),(55,57,'Radiotherapy Physical Infrastructure','<p>The following section outlines the infrastructural considerations for different units. The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall ensure the physical infrastructure meets the following requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>A standard bunker for Linac</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Brachytherapy suite with a theatre</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>CT simulator room/conventional simulator room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Control room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Physics room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mould room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Administration area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Capacity for electricity, water, power backup, space</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safety considerations &ndash; fire</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disability friendly infrastructure in all areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Maintenance considerations</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Treatment planning room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Recovery area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waiting area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient Reception area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Triage area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nursing station</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Consultation room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Procedure room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Emergency room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nutrition and counselling room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate staff and patient changing rooms</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate male and female toilets for staff and patients</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Sluice room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Registry</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hand wash area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Storage area&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Conference room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Staff room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Laundry</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Holding area in case of a death</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Special considerations:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>For a radiotherapy with in-patient services, separate adult from pediatric unit.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>For pediatric services, dedicated child-friendly rooms should be provided.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-18 12:59:22','2022-07-18 12:59:22'),(56,58,'Nuclear Radiology Human Resource','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The human resource requirements for the chemotherapy centre are as follows with core staff and supportive staff</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Human Resource Category</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Minimum Education</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Specialized Training &amp; Role</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Staff Establishment</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cyclotron Operator(s)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Technical degree or equivalent e.g. BSc in Electrical/Mechanical/Instrumentation/ Bio-medical/Physics</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Supervised training for 6 months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>On the job training</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Radiation Protection and Safety</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Electrical and mechanical repairs</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Production Chemist (s)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma or BSc in Chemistry or equivalent</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>On the job training</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Supervised training for 6 months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Radiation Protection and Safety</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Quality Control Chemist (s)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma or BSc in Chemistry, biochemistry, pharmacy or equivalent</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>On the job training</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Supervised training for 6 months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Radiation Protection and Safety</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Experience in GMP</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Experience in target preparation</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Synthesis of radiotracers</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Training in laboratory operations</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation Safety Officer (RSO)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Advanced degree in Medical Physics, Health Physics, radiation physics or equivalent</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Supervised training for 6 months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Radiation Protection and Safety</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radio-pharmacist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Degree in pharmacy with post graduate training in radiation physics/radiopharmaceutical sciences</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Preparation &amp; dispensing of radio- pharmaceuticals</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Skills in aseptic manipulation &amp; safe handling of radioactive products</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Knowledge on analytical techniques for quality control</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Trained in GMP</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nuclear medicine physician</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MMed or equivalent in Nuclear medicine.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p>Licensed to practice by&nbsp; KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>In-charge of nuclear medicine department; supervision; allocation of duties; assess, prescribe, prepare &amp; administer radioisotopes ; diagnosis; interpretation &amp; reporting of tests; enforce radiation protection standards for patients &amp; staff; quality control of nuclear medicine services; training; research; waste management; equip- ment selection; MDT member</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nuclear medicine technologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Degree/diploma in nuclear medicine</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Obtains patient history &amp; describe procedure to patient; administer nuclear medicine treatment; prepare &amp; administer radiopharmaceuticals; monitors patient&rsquo;s condition during procedure; perform imaging procedures for diagnosis; analyze biological specimens in the lab; nuclear waste disposal; equipment&nbsp; calibration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinically qualified Medical Physicists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Bsc in physics with postgraduate training in medical physics or Msc Medical Physics with clinical training in radiotherapy physics</p>\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Responsible for equipment selection, specifications, acceptance, delivery, design of installations and shielding requirements, com- missioning and management for radiotherapy, diagnostics and nuclear medicine; Treatment planning in collaboration with the radiation oncologist; safety assessment, establishment, measurement and supervision of QA for radiotherapy and nuclear medicine devices; radiation protection and safety; dose calibration and instrumentation; technical supervision of maintenance; research and innovation of new medical devices; teaching &ndash; radiation protection &amp; users of equipment.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer registrars</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Degree/diploma holder in Health Records &amp; information management (registered by AMRO-K or by an established HRIM Board)</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in cancer registration and notification by NCI-K or NCI-K approved provider.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer data abstraction, notification/data entry and maintenance of cancer patients&rsquo; records and participation in cancer research.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Reception and registration, storage, filing and retrieval, clinic preparation, file tracing, report generation/sharing and editing files.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Qualified customer care</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Certificate in customer care</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Receiving and guiding patients</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>General nurse</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or Degree in Nursing</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>Certification in chemotherapy handling and administration (those working in chemotherapy units)</li>\r\n				<li>Undergone an appropriate induction program in cancer management/ OJT on nuclear medicine.</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Providing nursing care to cancer patients in collaboration with other members of the MDT, in all areas of cancer treatment; health education; screening activities; participate in clinical research in oncology; screening activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Patient navigators</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Receiving and guiding patients</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Housekeeping staff</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Relevant training in housekeeping</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Training in safe handling of hazardous products</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Handling of waste and cleaning</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-18 13:01:04','2022-07-18 13:01:04'),(57,59,'Nuclear Radiology Equipment','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Equipment must have service contracts and appropriate measures for plans for preventive maintenance purposes and provide service stickers showing dates for last service and next service due dates. Elements that are important for the life of the equipment and for safety shall be addressed early in the planning stage and should be included in contractual forms, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Compliance with quality and safety standards</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Acceptance tests and conditions to correct deficiencies revealed during acceptance</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Warranty conditions</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Enforceable assurances on availability of maintenance support (technical and financial), manufacturer support, manuals and spare parts</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Training of all users and keep documentation of the same</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>List of Equipment for Nuclear medicine Unit</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>PET/CT&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>SPECT</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dose calibrator</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hot cell</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Barcode generator</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>UPS</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stand by generator</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>HVAC</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chiller</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dosimetry and radiation safety equipment (dosimeters, isotope dose calibrators, scintillation counter, Portable contamination monitor/survey meter)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>ICT infrastructure and support</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Standardized rulers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Two-way video cameras, with audio capability</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Appropriate shielding requirements of radiation sources</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Range of radiation dosimeters for measuring radiation doses</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Immobilization devices</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provision for anaesthesia space and recovery for pediatric patients</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computer systems</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PET Equipment PET/CT Scanners</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The basic components of a PET system include the scintillator, detector, photomultiplier tubes (PMT), electronics and reconstruction software. Each of these components contribute to the overall performance of the PET system.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Radionuclide Activity Calibrator</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A radionuclide activity calibrator is a fundamental requirement for the operation of a PET centre. It allows accurately measured radiopharmaceutical doses to be administered to patients, and is also used for other laboratory tasks like measuring time-activity curves. A PET centre will thus be equipped with one or more radionuclide activity calibrators, depending on the type of installation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Radio analytical equipment</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Appropriate quality management systems for validation and the appropriate radio-analytical equipment for radio-analytical testing should be duly considered to ensure safety of drugs administered. HPLC, TLC and gamma spectroscopy are used for this purpose.</p>','2022-07-18 13:02:10','2022-07-18 13:02:10'),(58,60,'Nuclear Radiology Physical Infrastructure','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient registration and reception area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Designated waiting area for patients and caregivers (clearly demarcated as cold area)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clearly demarcated Hot areas including:</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hot cell area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>QC Lab with calibration probes</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hot lab for preparation of radiopharmaceuticals</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Injection room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Uptake room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Scanning room (PET/CT or SPECT)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hot toilet</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waste management facilities as specified by IAEA for example a Decay tank</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stress room to increase cardiac imaging&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient holding, observation and recovery areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radioactive waste store</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Specially designated room with toilet and bathroom facilities for patients&rsquo; exclusive use to minimize contamination</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Imaging, viewing &amp; scan reporting area (with requisite infrastructure)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Iodine wards for inpatients</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ventilation of the radiopharmaceutical production facility should meet the requirements as per IAEA guidelines to prevent contamination of products and exposure of personnel to radioactivity. The production of sterile radioactive products should be carried out under negative pressure surrounded by a positive pressure zone ensuring that appropriate air quality requirements are met.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-18 13:02:53','2022-07-18 13:03:09'),(59,61,'Cancer Screening','<p>Cancer Screening involves applying simple tests or procedures across a healthy population in order to identify unrecognized cancer disease in individuals before they develop any symptoms of the cancer. This has to be provided in every cancer centre and should cater for both men and women.</p>','2022-07-18 13:04:05','2022-07-18 13:04:05'),(60,62,'Test','<h3><strong>1.2 Service Norms</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>a. The National Guidelines for Cancer Management shall form the basis for clinical management at the facility.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. The centre or unit must have NCI-K approved protocols for diagnosis and treatment of all malignancies they manage founded on sound scientific principles and evidence-based medicine which must be accessible to the prescribers, pharmacists and nurses at the centre at all times.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. The protocols must be updated as appropriate and be readily available for inspection when needed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. The centre or unit shall also commit to quality improvement, supporting cancer research and improving the training and mentoring of health care e. The centre or unit shall have infrastructure in place to be able to carry out cancer registration and reporting to the National Cancer Registry and DHIS</p>','2022-07-20 07:34:36','2022-07-20 07:39:24'),(61,62,'test','<p>test</p>','2022-07-20 07:39:24','2022-07-20 07:39:24'),(62,62,'','<p>test</p>','2022-07-20 07:39:24','2022-07-20 07:39:24'),(64,65,'CWEVCW','<p>CWECVWQEC</p>','2022-07-20 11:59:44','2022-07-20 11:59:44'),(65,67,'HGGH','<p>BJHW</p>','2022-07-20 12:04:19','2022-07-20 12:04:19'),(66,68,'B NDS','<p>MNBC</p>','2022-07-20 12:05:32','2022-07-20 12:05:32'),(100,75,'Service Norms','<p>The National Guidelines for Cancer Management shall form the basis for clinical management at the facility.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. The centre or unit must have NCI-K approved protocols for diagnosis and treatment of all malignancies they manage founded on sound scientific principles and evidence-based medicine which must be accessible to the prescribers, pharmacists and nurses at the centre at all times.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. The protocols must be updated as appropriate and be readily available for inspection when needed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. The centre or unit shall also commit to quality improvement, supporting cancer research and improving the training and mentoring of health care e. The centre or unit shall have infrastructure in place to be able to carry out cancer registration and reporting to the National Cancer Registry and DHIS.</p>','2022-07-20 13:25:55','2022-07-21 12:22:12'),(101,75,'Service Delivery Considerations','<p>Service Delivery Considerations Every cancer centre shall:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Formulate and prominently display a service charter that details the roles and responsibilities of both the patient and the centre.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Provide integrated and multidisciplinary care&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Prioritize coordination and planning for professionals to help facilitate access to care at other levels of care, including awareness creation, screening/early detection, case management and appropriate downward referrals.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Have a reasonable time frame &ndash; definitive/tissue diagnosis should be done preferably within 2 weeks and the initiation of appropriate treatment within a month of diagnosis.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Follow evidence-based protocols and guidelines.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Have informed consent obtained prior to all procedures including treatments. In case of a minor, a parent/guardian shall give consent. The information prior to consenting shall be provided in a manner easily understandable by the patient. The rights of the child should be prioritized.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Establish clear navigation systems to enable patients&rsquo; access to services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;h. Design patient-tracking systems for patient follow-up throughout the continuum of care. i. Develop standard operating procedures for every service being provided</p>','2022-07-20 13:25:55','2022-07-21 12:22:12'),(102,75,'Clinical Considerations','<p>Provide cancer management that is holistic and patient-centred for best care outcomes b. Before initiation of treatment, clearly define and communicate the goals of care to the patient in accordance with a patient care plan c. Provide the patient the right to detailed information on his/her condition, treatment options including clinical trials, side effects, expected outcome and prognosis. d. Allow the patient the right to seek a second or additional opinion before consenting to initiation of treatment. e. Have all aspects of carefully documented, stored and easily retrievable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Allow access of patients to their records as well as laboratory samples when needed g. Comprehensively document patient history</p>','2022-07-20 13:25:55','2022-07-21 12:22:12'),(103,75,'Multi-disciplinary Tumor Boards','<p>Definition; the multidisciplinary expert team that should manage cancer patients in a consultative approach</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;The cancer centre shall: a. Establish multidisciplinary teams (MDTs)/tumor boards which shall guide and direct cancer management b. Have MDTs meet regularly and have participation from all relevant disciplines depending on the cancer case and the level of care c. Have all complex cases discussed by a multidisciplinary team d. Have an MDT coordinator who will organize for meetings, keep records of discussions and provide reports on cancer patient management e. Utilize technology to convene virtual MDT discussions with proper documentation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It consists of different experts including &ndash; medical oncologist, radiation/clinical oncologist, surgeon, pathologist, palliative physician and specialists, oncology pharmacist, oncology nurse, radiologist, interventional radiologists, haematologist, medical physicist, radiation therapist/therapy radiographer, medical laboratory technologists specialized in different laboratory disciplines.</p>','2022-07-20 13:25:55','2022-07-21 12:22:12'),(104,75,'Diagnostic Imaging','<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Incorporate clinical findings in conducting diagnostic imaging modalities&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Consider image-guided diagnostics where applicable</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use a standard protocol for conducting imaging procedures or an MOU with a facility with that has standard protocol for conducting imaging procedures.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use internationally and locally recognized standards and guidelines for the safe installation, operation and use of imaging equipment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use a standard imaging diagnostic reporting protocol&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Outsource/provide access to an accredited imaging diagnostic facility</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-20 13:25:55','2022-07-21 12:22:12'),(105,75,'Nursing Considerations','<p>The cancer center shall:-</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide oncology and palliative nursing care for the entire continuum of care (Prevention, Awareness, screening, early detection, diagnosis, treatment, survivorship and end of life care, and bereavement).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Support the coordinating role of oncology and palliative care nurses in the care team and community linkage for cancer patients</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-20 13:25:55','2022-07-21 12:22:12'),(106,75,'Chemotherapy Considerations','<p>Definition of Chemotherapy</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Have only appropriately qualified oncologists initiate cancer patients on chemotherapy and biotherapies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;b. Have chemotherapy medications prepared by a pharmacist or pharmaceutical technologist in a bio-safety cabinet class 2B2 vented to the outside.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Provide personal protective equipment to all members of the health care team who prepare, mix, administer and transport hazardous chemotherapy drugs.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Have a program that monitors exposure to hazardous chemotherapy drugs for all health workers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Ensure pregnant and lactating health workers are not assigned to an area where chemotherapy drugs are present/being administered</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Provide education and training for safe handling of these drugs to health workers exposed to hazardous chemotherapy drugs prior to their being assigned to an area where chemotherapy agents are present. Training must be done for all staff in the facility, annually, with the educational content being specific to the activities for which the health worker is responsible.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Prior to administration of chemotherapy ensure there is a system in place to confirm that the correct medication and dosage is administered to the correct patient.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>h. Chemotherapy medicines especially vesicants like vinca alkaloids shall be whenever possible be administered via a central line e.g. using chemoports. Chemotherapy shall be administered through infusion pumps for accuracy and safety.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Have the facility ensure provision for management of extravasations and spills.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>j. Provide patients and caregivers involved in the delivery of chemotherapy at home receive some basic education and training on the principles of safe handling, dealing with spills, waste disposal and patients&rsquo; excreta. Written instructions shall be given to the patient and/or caregiver, including information on the use of oral chemotherapeutic agents.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>k. Document the process for handling hazardous drugs waste generated during compounding and administration or during spills, as well as waste (bulk) products for chemotherapy.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>l. Store chemotherapy medicines separately from other medicines &ndash; both storage area and refrigerator&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>m. Transport of chemotherapy medicines should maintain the integrity of the drug to avoid breakage or leakage that leads to spillages, contamination and exposure to the hazardous drug&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>n. Ensure labelling of chemotherapeutic agents includes storage, handling and disposal instructions&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>o. Develop facility SOPs for &ndash; designation of HD areas; receipt of HDs; storage of HDs; compounding of HDs; use and maintenance of proper engineering controls; hand hygiene and use of PPEs; deactivation, decontamination, cleaning &amp; disinfection; dispensing of HDs; transport of HDs; administering HDs, environmental monitoring; disposal of HDs; spill control and medical surveillance.</p>','2022-07-20 13:25:55','2022-07-21 12:22:12'),(107,75,'Health Information and Records & Cancer Registry Office Considerations','<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Designate an office for Cancer registry- the office should be lockable, with lockable cabinets and a computer with internet access.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Establish a health records department that will maintain all patient records in a system that is secure, confidential and easy to retrieve.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Capture data for all cancer cases comprehensively.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Notify the National Cancer Registry all new cancer cases using the cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>abstract form <a href=\"about:blank\">National Cancer Notification Form_FINAL copy.pdf</a>(NACARE) as provided for by the Cancer Control Act 2012.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Ensure that the health records department sends reports to the National&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cancer Registry and MoH-KHIS monthly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Permanently archive cancer patient records.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Respect patients&rsquo; rights to access their records at any point in their lifetime.</p>','2022-07-20 13:25:55','2022-07-21 12:22:12'),(108,75,'Palliative Care and Survivorship Considerations','<p>&nbsp;The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Provide palliative care from the point of cancer diagnosis and at all times throughout the course of illness.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Integrate palliative care with other health services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Prioritize and provide effective relief of pain and other distressing symptoms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Provide timely rehabilitative and supportive services.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Facilitate formation of patient support groups.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Establish survivorship programs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Adhere to the National Palliative Care Policy and the National Palliative Care&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Guideline.</p>','2022-07-20 13:25:55','2022-07-21 12:22:12'),(109,75,'Equipment Considerations','<p>The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Have all the facilities and equipment registered and licensed for the safe and effective conduct of its services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have access to a qualified biomedical engineer, who is ultimately responsible for ensuring that all equipment is in proper working condition and that the necessary safety devices are fitted and in working order.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Maintain service contracts and schedules of service with the contracted service providers to ensure regular servicing as per the manufacturer&rsquo;s instructions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Ensure equipment compliance with relevant regulations according to the appropriate governing regulatory body. Equipment more than 7 years old should not be acquired for cancer treatment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Ensure safe disposal of obsolete or unserviceable equipment as guided by the relevant regulatory body.&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-20 13:40:28','2022-07-21 12:22:12'),(110,75,'Referral Considerations','<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Develop patient referral SOPs (<a href=\"about:blank\">ministry-of-health-referral-guidelines-37-40.pdf</a> ) which conform to the national referral guidelines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Properly document referrals to and away from the facility.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Promote upward, downward and horizontal referral where appropriate.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Facilitate referrals for specialized services that are unavailable at the centre to facilities that are accessible and are accredited by the relevant regulatory body.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Assess patients for fitness to travel and provide necessary supportive&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>mechanisms (ambulance, nurse, oxygen supply) before referral.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Provide proper patient counseling on cancer, tests to be done, costs implications and expected treatment before referral.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Refer a patient to the right specialist for further management if a service outside oncology services is required</p>','2022-07-20 13:40:28','2022-07-21 12:22:12'),(111,75,'Quality Assurance','<p>The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish a Quality Assurance Programme (QAP) that is adequately supervised and provides reports to NCI Kenya as required.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have risk assessment measures in place with objectives and systematic monitoring and evaluation so as to identify problems and system failures and guide the necessary action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Have regular morbidity and mortality meetings to identify specific clinical performance indicators.&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-20 13:40:28','2022-07-21 12:22:12'),(112,75,'Infection Prevention and Control','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oncology patients are at increased infection risk due to immunosuppression and frequent exposure to healthcare settings.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Have a hospital&rsquo;s infection prevention and control program must be in accordance with the WHO Practical Guidelines for Infection Control<a href=\"about:blank\">.File571.pdf</a>.</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Have hand-washing facilities for staff readily available. Hand sanitizers should be provided at every work station.</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have eyewash facilities for staff in Chemo mixing and administration areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide a designated sluicing area for linen generated in the chemo area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have isolation rooms and practice barrier nursing by ensuring PPEs are&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>available and easily accessible.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-20 13:40:28','2022-07-21 12:22:12'),(113,75,'Occupational Health and Safety','<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Implement the Occupational, Health &amp; Safety (OSH) Act in the workplace.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Provide safety and health training at least once every 3 years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Be subject to annual inspection by the local regulatory body and adhere to the basic safety standards as set by the regulatory body.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Disclose labeling laws for identification and classification of chemicals by types of hazards, including medication labels and safety data sheets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Establish a system for identification and surveillance of exposure: estimating the number of workers who come into contact with substances and are employed in occupations with increased carcinogenic risk, and reducing to minimum the number of workers exposed, the duration of exposure and the degree of exposure, and establishing an appropriate system of records.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Ensure medical surveillance applies to all healthcare workers handling hazardous drugs and includes assessment and documentation of symptom complaints, physical findings &amp; laboratory values</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Provide personal protective equipment i.e N95 masks, powder-free Nitrile gloves, shoe covers, head net, goggles, non-absorbent gown, face shield for health workers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>h. Establish/develop guidelines and recommendations for proper use and handling of carcinogenic chemicals and training packages for healthcare workers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>i. Have a system for incidents monitoring and management at the workplace.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>j. Empower workers by providing them with access to information about their exposures and risks.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>k. Have programs to monitor and support employee performance, mental health, work-life balance and put in place debriefing programs.</p>','2022-07-20 13:40:28','2022-07-21 12:22:12'),(114,75,'Waste Management','<p>he cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Dispose cytotoxic waste produced in the process of the diagnosis and treatment of cancer in accordance to international and relevant local guidelines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have written policies and SOPs for hazardous waste describing requirements for the segregation, packaging, labeling, collection, transportation storage and on site treatment of waste within the facility.<a href=\"about:blank\">National-Guidelines-for-Safe-management-of-health-care-waste-Final1.pdf</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Provide waste disposal amenities and commodities.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Conduct regular capacity building on waste disposal for all healthcare providers including support staff.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Provide appropriate PPEs for handling hazardous waste.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Incinerate hazardous waste using special incinerators that can combust at 1200&deg;Centigrade and maintain documentation on the same.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Minimize the risk of contaminating the local water supply and/or soil with hazardous drugs. Hazardous drug waste shall never be discarded into waste water (sink or toilet) or into a landfill.</p>','2022-07-20 13:40:28','2022-07-21 12:22:12'),(115,75,'Emergency Medical Care','<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Have facilities and human resources to handle oncologic and palliative care emergencies.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Ensure medical staffs are trained in BLS/ACLS.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Stabilize the patient and expeditiously refer for emergency management where applicable.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Be well equipped with resuscitation commodities and equipment.</p>','2022-07-20 13:40:28','2022-07-21 12:22:12'),(116,75,'Adverse Events','<p>Any adverse event that occurs as a result of cancer diagnosis or treatment must be documented, discussed internally and reported to the relevant regulatory bodies such as the Pharmacy and Poisons Board, relevant regulatory body and the NCI-K.&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-20 13:40:28','2022-07-21 12:22:12'),(117,75,'Death of a Patient','<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Document all deaths occurring whilst patients are undergoing treatment appropriately.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Offer bereavement support to the family.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Have periodic mortality meetings where cancer deaths are discussed by a multidisciplinary team</p>','2022-07-20 13:40:28','2022-07-21 12:22:12'),(118,76,'Core Human Resource','<p>The human resource requirements for the chemotherapy centre are as follows with core staff and supportive staff</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oncologist (Medical, Clinical)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oncology Nurse</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical Pharmacist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Cancer Registrar</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical Counsellor&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nutritionist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical social worker</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Infection Prevention and Control Expert&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Quality Assurance Expert</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient navigators</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Core Human Resource</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Human resource category&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Minimum Qualifications&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Required staff establishment (number)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Radiation oncologist/ Medical oncologist/clinical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>- MMED/Fellowship in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>radiation oncology/</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Clinical oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>as an oncologist by&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; in charge of radiotherapy treatment;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>assessment, initiation, review of patients cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>treatment and patient follow up; treatment&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>planning; chair MDTs meetings; participate in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>clinical research in oncology; participates in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>equipment procurement&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Nurse - Specialized oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Diploma or BSc&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Specialized oncology nursing training&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>at Higher Diploma,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>MSc Nursing or an&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>accredited oncology program&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Provide nursing care to cancer patients in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>collaboration with other members of the MDT;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>health education; screening activities; comprehensive patient assessments; symptom&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>management; management of treatment side&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>effects; patient navigation activities; clinical research in oncology; advocacy; mentorship and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>teaching; policy formulation and implementation; screening activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Cancer registrars</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>- Degree/diploma&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>holder in Health Records &amp; information.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>registration from&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>African Cancer Registry Network (AFCRN)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>approved provider</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Cancer data abstraction, maintenance of cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>patients records and participation in cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Clinical pharmacist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>- Masters in clinical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>pharmacy or equivalent&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to Practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by PPB.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;- Training and certification in chemotherapy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>handling and administration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Head of pharmaceutical oncology services; allocation of duties; supervision; member of MDT;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research; in charge of supply chain of oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>commodities; in-charge of preparation of chemotherapy medications</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Clinical counselors&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Diploma/degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Psychological counseling.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- License to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>from relevant body</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Counseling of patients and their caregivers/</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>families on cancer; patient navigation; research;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Housekeeping&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Staff</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Relevant training in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>housekeeping</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training in safe handling of hazardous&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Products</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Handling of waste and cleaning</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Medical social&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Worker</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Diploma or bachelors&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in social Sciences</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Assessment of socio-economic background of&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>patients; Contact tracing; patient navigation;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Nurse - General&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(adult care and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>pediatric care)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Certification in chemotherapy handling and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>administration (those&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>working in chemotherapy units)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Undergone an appropriate preceptorship/mentorship program in cancer management for at least 3 or 6&nbsp; months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Providing nursing care to cancer patients in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>collaboration with other members of the MDT,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in all areas of cancer treatment; health education; screening activities; participate in clinical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research in oncology; screening activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Nutritionists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>- Diploma or degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nutrition or Masters</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- License to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>from Nutritionists &amp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Dieticians Council</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Provision of nutritional counseling and support&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>to patients and their families/caregivers; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Porters/patient navigators</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>-KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training in customer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>service&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- First aid Training&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Ferrying of patients between service points&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>within the facility</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Quality Assurance&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Officer/ Safety&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>A designated Quality&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Assurance Officer/&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Safety health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Liaise with all departments to ensure safety &amp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>quality assurance is embedded in their processes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Infection Prevention and Control</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>-Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and Certification in IPC</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>-Monitor the rate of infections</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure proper waste management</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure proper use of PPE</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure hand hygiene compliance</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 04:58:50','2022-07-21 05:00:22'),(119,76,'Supportive Human Resource','<p>The human resource requirements for the chemotherapy centre are as follows with core staff and supportive staff</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oncologist (Medical, Clinical)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oncology Nurse</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical Pharmacist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Cancer Registrar</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical Counsellor&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nutritionist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical social worker</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Infection Prevention and Control Expert&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Quality Assurance Expert</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient navigators</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Core Human Resource</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Human resource category&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Minimum Qualifications&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Required staff establishment (number)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Radiation oncologist/ Medical oncologist/clinical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>- MMED/Fellowship in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>radiation oncology/</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Clinical oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>as an oncologist by&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; in charge of radiotherapy treatment;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>assessment, initiation, review of patients cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>treatment and patient follow up; treatment&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>planning; chair MDTs meetings; participate in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>clinical research in oncology; participates in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>equipment procurement&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Nurse - Specialized oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Diploma or BSc&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Specialized oncology nursing training&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>at Higher Diploma,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>MSc Nursing or an&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>accredited oncology program&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Provide nursing care to cancer patients in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>collaboration with other members of the MDT;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>health education; screening activities; comprehensive patient assessments; symptom&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>management; management of treatment side&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>effects; patient navigation activities; clinical research in oncology; advocacy; mentorship and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>teaching; policy formulation and implementation; screening activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Cancer registrars</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>- Degree/diploma&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>holder in Health Records &amp; information.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>registration from&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>African Cancer Registry Network (AFCRN)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>approved provider</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Cancer data abstraction, maintenance of cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>patients records and participation in cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Clinical pharmacist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>- Masters in clinical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>pharmacy or equivalent&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to Practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by PPB.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;- Training and certification in chemotherapy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>handling and administration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Head of pharmaceutical oncology services; allocation of duties; supervision; member of MDT;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research; in charge of supply chain of oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>commodities; in-charge of preparation of chemotherapy medications</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Clinical counselors&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Diploma/degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Psychological counseling.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- License to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>from relevant body</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Counseling of patients and their caregivers/</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>families on cancer; patient navigation; research;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Housekeeping&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Staff</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Relevant training in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>housekeeping</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training in safe handling of hazardous&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Products</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Handling of waste and cleaning</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Medical social&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Worker</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Diploma or bachelors&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in social Sciences</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Assessment of socio-economic background of&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>patients; Contact tracing; patient navigation;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Nurse - General&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(adult care and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>pediatric care)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Certification in chemotherapy handling and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>administration (those&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>working in chemotherapy units)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Undergone an appropriate preceptorship/mentorship program in cancer management for at least 3 or 6&nbsp; months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Providing nursing care to cancer patients in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>collaboration with other members of the MDT,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in all areas of cancer treatment; health education; screening activities; participate in clinical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research in oncology; screening activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Nutritionists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>- Diploma or degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nutrition or Masters</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- License to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>from Nutritionists &amp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Dieticians Council</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Provision of nutritional counseling and support&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>to patients and their families/caregivers; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Porters/patient navigators</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>-KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training in customer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>service&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- First aid Training&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Ferrying of patients between service points&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>within the facility</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Quality Assurance&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Officer/ Safety&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>A designated Quality&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Assurance Officer/&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Safety health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Liaise with all departments to ensure safety &amp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>quality assurance is embedded in their processes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Infection Prevention and Control</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>-Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and Certification in IPC</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>-Monitor the rate of infections</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure proper waste management</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure proper use of PPE</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure hand hygiene compliance</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Supportive Human Resource</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Human resource category&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Minimum Qualifications&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Required staff establishment (number)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Medical Officers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>- MBCHB</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by KMPDB - Training&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>and certification in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>chemotherapy handling and administration</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Health education; screening activities; assess,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>prescribe, administer subsequent cancer treatment under supervision of an oncologist; participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Clinical Officers in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Higher National&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Diploma in Clinical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Medicine Oncology.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by the Clinical Officers&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Council</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Health education; screening activities; assess,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>prescribe and administer subsequent cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>treatment under supervision of an oncologist;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Nurses - Palliative&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>care</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Specialized Palliative&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>care nursing - Higher&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Diploma, MSc Nursing&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>or an accredited Palliative program&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of K</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the palliative&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>care services in the facility; nursing care to cancer patients in the MDT; comprehensive patient&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>assessments; Pain and Symptom management;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Management of treatment side effects; Patient&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>navigation activities; initiating , organizing and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>facilitating family conferences and advance care&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>planning; end of life and bereavement care;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>clinical research in palliative care; advocacy;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>mentorship and teaching; policy formulation&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>and implementation</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Pharmaceutical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>technologists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Diploma/Higher&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>National diploma in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Pharmacy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Enrolled to Practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by PPB&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and certification in chemotherapy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>handling and administration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Preparation of chemotherapy medications&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>under supervision of a clinical pharmacist; research; supply chain management of oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>commodities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Pharmacists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>- Degree in pharmacy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to Practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by PPB&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and certification in chemotherapy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>handling and administration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Preparation of chemotherapy medications under supervision of a clinical pharmacist; member of MDT; research; supply chain management&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>of oncology commodities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 05:00:22','2022-07-21 05:00:22'),(120,77,'Equipment','<p>Equipment must have service contracts and appropriate measures for plans for preventive maintenance purposes and provide service stickers showing dates for last service and next service due dates. Elements that are important for the life of the equipment and for safety shall be addressed early in the planning stage and should be included in contractual forms, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Compliance with quality and safety standards</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Acceptance tests and conditions to correct deficiencies revealed during acceptance</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Warranty conditions</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Enforceable assurances on availability of maintenance support (technical and financial), manufacturer support, manuals and spare parts</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Training of all users and keeping documentation of the same</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 05:07:33','2022-07-21 06:44:19'),(121,77,'Acceptance testing and commissioning','<p>Commissioning is done by the manufacturer or his representative, Biomedical Engineer and the Clinical Pharmacist. A record keeping system should also be in place. After commissioning has been completed, the specific tests needed for ongoing quality control and safety assurance will need to be carried out</p>','2022-07-21 05:07:33','2022-07-21 06:44:19'),(122,77,'Chemotherapy Administration Area','<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chemotherapy chairs</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Assorted hospital beds&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bedside cabinets&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Wheelchairs</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hazardous drug spill kit&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Infusion pumps</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>4-hooked mobile drip stands&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Lockable cabinets&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Crash cart for emergency/resuscitation including ambu-bags and masks for appropriate ages</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Suction machine&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oxygen &amp; oxygen masks</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Weighing scale</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Heightometer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Vital signs monitor including sphygmomanometer, thermometer, pulse oximeter Measuring Cylinders</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stretchers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Procedure trolleys</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Portable examination lamps</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Audio-visual equipment &ndash;Television</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clock</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>ICT equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 05:07:33','2022-07-21 06:44:19'),(123,77,'Chemotherapy Reconstitution Area','<p><em>Chemotherapy reconstitution area needs to be lockable&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>A biosafety cabinet, class 2B2 and above (must have an exhauster fitted 2 meters above the building roof)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hazardous drug spill kit&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Lockable cabinets&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Steel/granite working surface area&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>An eye wash area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Air conditioner</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 05:07:33','2022-07-21 06:44:19'),(124,77,'Oncology Pharmacy','<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pharmaceutical Refrigerator with temperature monitors for oncology medicines</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Lockable cabinets</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Weighing balance</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Measuring Cylinders</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Secure storage</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Steel / granite working surface</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Reference books (e.g. Martindale, other Pharmacopoeias)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 05:07:33','2022-07-21 06:44:19'),(125,77,'Pharmacy Consultation Room','<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Furniture</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chairs</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Desk</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 05:07:33','2022-07-21 06:44:19'),(126,77,'Screening','<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>HPV test machines and kits</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>PAP smear kits</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>VIA/VILI reagents and commodities,&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical breast exams</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Fecal occult blood test</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Digital rectal exam</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Cryotherapy and thermal ablation with the appropriate staff</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 05:07:33','2022-07-21 06:44:19'),(127,77,'Palliative Care & survivorship Unit','<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Furniture&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Examination couch</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Storage cabinets and desks</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chairs</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dressing trolleys</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Drip stands</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>BP machine</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Thermometers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Weighing scales</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Infusion/syringe pumps</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Electronics</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Printer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 06:44:19','2022-07-21 06:44:19'),(128,77,'Rehabilitation unit','<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Appropriate rehabilitation equipment and commodities e.g. Lymphedema stockings, stoma bags, prostheses etc</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 06:44:19','2022-07-21 06:44:19'),(129,77,'Cancer Registry Office','<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Lockable designated Office space</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Filing shelves&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computer with internet connectivity</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Furniture</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Working top</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Notice board</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 06:44:19','2022-07-21 06:44:19'),(130,78,'Physical Infrastructure','<p>The cancer center shall ensure the physical infrastructure meets the following requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient flow</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Capacity for electricity, water, power backup, space</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safety considerations &ndash; fire</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separation of adults from pediatric management areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disability infrastructure in all areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Maintenance considerations</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 06:47:20','2022-07-21 06:47:20'),(131,78,'Chemotherapy Unit Services Areas','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient registration and reception area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Triage room/observation room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Procedure rooms&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Counselling room&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waiting area for patients/caregivers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Designated Consultation room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chemotherapy administration area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oncology pharmacy</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chemo holding/receiving station in close proximity to the chemo administration area-with shelves, work tops, a hand washing area and hooks</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>At least one isolation room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Emergency room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Storage area for hazardous chemotherapy drugs with appropriate ventilation. Ideally, storage areas should have negative air pressure in relation to surrounding areas and have 12 air changes per hour</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chemotherapy reconstitution area should be large enough to contain a bio-safety cabinet</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Staff changing area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Staff room/conference room&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pantry room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate staff and patients rest rooms&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Sluice room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Storage facility for cytotoxic waste and other wastes</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disposal facilities for cytotoxic and other wastes Eye wash station/shower</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 06:47:20','2022-07-21 06:47:20'),(132,78,'Waste Management','<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Modern incinerator with combustion capacity above 1200oC</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waste Holding Area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 06:47:20','2022-07-21 06:47:20'),(133,79,'Service Norms','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The National Guidelines for Cancer Management shall form the basis for clinical management at the facility.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The center or unit must have NCI-K-approved protocols for diagnosis and treatment of all malignancies they manage founded on sound scientific principles and evidence-based medicine which must be accessible to the prescribers, pharmacists, and nurses at the center at all times.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The protocols must be updated as appropriate and be readily available for inspection when needed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The centre or unit shall also commit to quality improvement, supporting cancer research and improving the training and mentoring of health care e. The centre or unit shall have infrastructure in place to be able to carry out cancer registration and reporting to the National Cancer Registry and KHIS.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 08:25:28','2022-07-22 06:03:33'),(134,79,'Service Delivery Considerations','<p>Every cancer center shall:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Formulate and prominently display a service charter that details the roles and responsibilities of both the patient and the centre.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide integrated and multidisciplinary care&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Prioritize coordination and planning for professionals to help facilitate access to care at other levels of care, including awareness creation, screening/early detection, case management and appropriate downward referrals.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a reasonable time frame &ndash; definitive/tissue diagnosis should be done preferably within 2 weeks and the initiation of appropriate treatment within a month of diagnosis.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The recommended time frame between diagnosis and Surgery should be at least 120 days.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Follow evidence-based protocols and guidelines.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have informed consent obtained prior to all procedures including treatments. In case of a minor, a parent/guardian shall give consent. The information prior to consenting shall be provided in a manner easily understandable by the patient. The rights of the child should be prioritized.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish clear navigation systems to enable patients&rsquo; access to services.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Design patient-tracking systems for patient follow-up throughout the continuum of care.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Develop standard operating procedures for every service being provided</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 08:29:51','2022-07-22 06:03:33'),(135,79,'Clinical Considerations','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide cancer management that is holistic and patient-centered for best care outcomes.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Before initiation of treatment, clearly define and communicate the goals of care to the patient in accordance with a patient care plan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide the patient the right to detailed information on his/her condition, and treatment options including clinical trials, side effects, expected outcome and prognosis.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow the patient the right to seek a second or additional opinion before consenting to initiation of treatment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all aspects carefully documented, stored, and easily retrievable.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow access of patients to their records as well as laboratory samples when needed&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Comprehensively document patient history</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 08:35:46','2022-07-22 06:03:33'),(136,79,'Multi-disciplinary Tumor Boards','<p>Definition; the multidisciplinary expert team that should manage cancer patients in a consultative approach</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;The cancer center shall:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish multidisciplinary teams (MDTs)/tumor boards which shall guide and direct cancer management&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have MDTs meet regularly and have participation from all relevant disciplines depending on the cancer case and the level of care&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all complex cases discussed by a multidisciplinary team&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have an MDT coordinator who will organize for meetings, keep records of discussions and provide reports on cancer patient management&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Utilize technology to convene virtual MDT discussions with proper documentation</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>It consists of different experts including &ndash; medical oncologist, radiation/clinical oncologist, surgeon, pathologist, palliative physician and specialists, oncology pharmacist, oncology nurse, radiologist, interventional radiologist, haematologist, medical physicist, radiation therapist/therapy radiographer, medical laboratory technologists specialized in different laboratory disciplines.</p>','2022-07-21 08:35:46','2022-07-22 06:03:33'),(137,79,'Diagnostic Imaging','<p>&nbsp;The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(i) Incorporate clinical findings in conducting diagnostic imaging modalities&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(ii) Consider image-guided diagnostics where applicable</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(iii) Use a standard protocol for conducting imaging procedures</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(iv) Use internationally and locally recognized standards and guidelines for the safe installation, operation and use of imaging equipment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(v) Use a standard imaging diagnostic reporting protocol&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(vi) Outsource/provide access to an accredited imaging diagnostic facility</p>','2022-07-21 08:35:46','2022-07-22 06:03:33'),(138,79,'Nursing Considerations','<p>The cancer center shall:-</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Provide oncology and palliative nursing care for the entire continuum of care(Prevention, Awareness, screening, early detection, diagnosis, treatment, survivorship and end-of-life care, bereavement).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Support the coordinating role of oncology and palliative care nurses in the&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>care team and community linkage for cancer patients</p>','2022-07-21 08:35:46','2022-07-22 06:03:33'),(139,79,'Surgical Considerations','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer center shall:-</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have Surgical site marking protocol implemented (standard site identification process, the patient involved in marking, and marking done by the one doing the procedure.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a safe surgery checklist (evidence of use for verifying correct site, correct procedure, correct patient; availability of informed consent; and equipment needed are on hand, correct, and functional) See checklist <a href=\"about:blank\">Resources\\Safe surgery checklist.pdf</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide Evidence that the facility has an active process of monitoring safe surgical checklist compliance.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ensure the organization uses a &ldquo;time-out&rdquo; procedure just before starting a surgical procedure.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Facilitate patients to access surgical diagnosis and treatment for solid malignancies through a multidisciplinary team approach.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Where tissue is obtained for histological examination, have the surgeon observe the SOP for histology specimen handling, storage and transport.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have surgical treatment offered conforming to internationally recognized, evidence-based surgical-oncological practices</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 08:35:46','2022-07-22 06:03:33'),(140,79,'Palliative Care and Survivorship Considerations','<p>&nbsp;The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Provide palliative care from the point of cancer diagnosis and at all times throughout the course of illness.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Integrate palliative care with other health services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Prioritize and provide effective relief of pain and other distressing symptoms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Provide timely rehabilitative and supportive services.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Facilitate formation of patient support groups.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Establish survivorship programs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Adhere to the National Palliative Care Policy and the National Palliative Care&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Guideline.</p>','2022-07-21 08:38:42','2022-07-22 06:03:33'),(141,79,'Equipment Considerations','<p>The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Have all the facilities and equipment registered and licensed for the safe and effective conduct of its services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have access to a qualified biomedical engineer, who is ultimately responsible for ensuring that all equipment is in proper working condition and that the necessary safety devices are fitted and in working order.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Maintain service contracts and schedules of service with the contracted service providers to ensure regular servicing as per the manufacturer&rsquo;s instructions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Ensure equipment compliance with relevant regulations according to the appropriate governing regulatory body.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Ensure safe disposal of obsolete or unserviceable equipment as guided by the relevant regulatory body.&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 08:38:42','2022-07-22 06:03:33'),(142,79,'Referral Considerations','<p>The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Develop patient referral SOPs which conform to the national referral guidelines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Properly document referrals to and away from the facility.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Promote upward, downward and horizontal referral where appropriate.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Facilitate referrals for specialized services that are unavailable at the centre to facilities that are accessible and are accredited by the relevant regulatory body.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Assess patients for fitness to travel and provide necessary supportive mechanisms (ambulance, nurse, oxygen supply) before referral.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Provide proper patient counseling on cancer, tests to be done, costs implications and expected treatment before referral.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Refer a patient to the right specialist for further management if a service outside oncology services is required</p>','2022-07-21 08:38:42','2022-07-22 06:03:33'),(143,79,'Quality Assurance','<p>The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish a Quality Assurance Programme (QAP) that is adequately supervised and provides reports to NCI Kenya as required.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have risk assessment measures in place with objectives and systematic monitoring and evaluation so as to identify problems and system failures and guide the necessary action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Have regular morbidity and mortality meetings to identify specific clinical performance indicators.</p>','2022-07-21 08:44:23','2022-07-22 06:03:33'),(144,79,'Infection Prevention and Control','<p>Oncology patients are at increased infection risk due to immunosuppression and frequent exposure to healthcare settings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a hospital&rsquo;s infection prevention and control program must be in accordance with the WHO Practical Guidelines for Infection Control.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have hand-washing facilities for staff readily available. Hand sanitizers should be provided at every workstation.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide a designated sluicing area for linen generated in the Surgical area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have isolation rooms and practice barrier nursing by ensuring PPEs are available and easily accessible.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide decontamination and sterilization areas. (The decontaminant, sodium hypochlorite 5%)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 08:44:23','2022-07-22 06:03:33'),(145,79,'Occupational Health and Safety','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Implement the Occupational, Health &amp; Safety (OSH) Act in the workplace.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide safety and health training at least once every 3 years.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Be subject to an annual inspection by the local regulatory body and adhere to the basic safety standards as set by the regulatory body.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disclose labeling laws for identification and classification of chemicals by types of hazards, including medication labels and safety data sheets.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a system for incidents monitoring and management at the workplace.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have programs to monitor and support employee performance, mental health, work-life balance and put in place debriefing programs.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 08:44:23','2022-07-22 06:03:33'),(146,79,'Waste Management','<p>The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide waste segregation and disposal amenities.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Conduct regular capacity building on waste disposal for all healthcare providers including support staff.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide appropriate PPEs for handling clinical waste</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 08:44:23','2022-07-22 06:03:33'),(147,79,'Emergency Medical Care','<p>The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have facilities and human resources to handle Surgical Oncology emergencies.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ensure medical staff are trained in BLS/ACLS.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stabilize the patient and expeditiously refer for emergency management where applicable.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Be well equipped with resuscitation commodities and equipment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 08:44:23','2022-07-22 06:03:33'),(148,79,'Adverse Events','<p>Any adverse event that occurs as a result of the surgery must be documented, discussed internally and reported to the relevant regulatory bodies such as the Pharmacy and Poisons Board, relevant regulatory body, and the NCI-K.&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 08:44:23','2022-07-22 06:03:33'),(149,79,'Death of a Patient','<p>The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Document all deaths occurring whilst patients are undergoing treatment appropriately.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Offer bereavement support to the family.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Have periodic mortality meetings where cancer deaths are discussed by a multidisciplinary team</p>','2022-07-21 08:44:23','2022-07-22 06:03:33'),(150,81,'Surgical Unit Physical Infrastructure Requirements','<p>The cancer centre shall ensure the physical infrastructure meets the following requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient flow</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Capacity for electricity, water, power backup, space</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safety considerations &ndash; fire</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separation of adults from pediatric management areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disability infrastructure in all areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Maintenance considerations</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 08:56:07','2022-07-21 08:56:47'),(151,81,'All Departments and Units','<p>For centers operating within the precincts of a hospital, it can utilize similar facilities within the hospital. For stand-alone centers, these services must be provided for:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Appropriate space for the following administrative services:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Administration</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Finance</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Transport</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iv. Supply chain management</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;v. Laundry</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;vi. Healthcare waste management, including hazardous drug waste, a Lockable holding area, proper segregation and disposal, MOUs with disposal companies</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;vii. Conference room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ix. Reception area</p>','2022-07-21 08:56:07','2022-07-21 08:56:47'),(152,81,'Utilities','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate patient and staff changing rooms</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate staff and patients rest rooms</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Staff room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 08:56:07','2022-07-21 08:56:47'),(153,81,'Health records and information – Registration Area','<p>&nbsp;i. Office space</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Filing room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Use of NACARE system for reporting is required using secure internet.</p>','2022-07-21 08:56:07','2022-07-21 08:56:47'),(154,81,'Other supportive services','<p>&nbsp;i. Provision for daycare services where applicable.</p>','2022-07-21 08:56:07','2022-07-21 08:56:47'),(155,81,'Cancer registry office','<p>&nbsp;i. Office space</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Filing room</p>','2022-07-21 08:56:07','2022-07-21 08:56:47'),(156,81,'Surgical Oncology Unit','<p>a. Patient registration and reception area</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Waiting area for patients and caregivers</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Consultation room&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Triage/observation room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Counseling room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Procedure room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Pharmacy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>h. Operating theatre capable of handling minor and major surgical procedures with a Patient receiving room and a patient recovery room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>i. Nutrition</p>\r\n\r\n<p>j. Palliative care</p>\r\n\r\n<p>k. Medical Laboratory Unit</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Support from;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Diagnostic radiology unit</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pathology unit</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Blood banking</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Critical care unit</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Rehabilitation centres&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Endoscopy services</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Morgue services</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 08:56:07','2022-07-21 08:56:47'),(157,81,'Inpatient Oncology Wards','<p>Separate female, male, adolescents, geriatric and pediatric wards&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Side room facilities for ward reviews of post-operative wounds, minor procedures, and emergency resuscitation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Isolation rooms for patients with infectious conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Waste management facilities</p>','2022-07-21 08:56:07','2022-07-21 08:56:47'),(158,81,'Palliative Care and Survivorship Unit','<p>a. Patient registration and reception area</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Waiting area for patients/caregivers</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Counseling room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Procedure room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Consultation room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Community room large enough to accommodate support groups</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Support services</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Pharmacy</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Nutrition</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Chaplaincy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iv. Counseling&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;v. Rehabilitative unit</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Pediatrics play area</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Nutrition counseling rooms</p>','2022-07-21 08:56:07','2022-07-21 08:56:47'),(159,81,'Design and Construction Requirements','<p>The design of any surgery department revolves around environmental control, traffic control, and the desire to prevent surgical site infection (SSI). <a href=\"about:blank\">Resources\\Surgical Operating Theatres Standards.docx</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Consult the Services of a registered Architectural and structural Engineering firms, with expertise in construction of health care facilities, for the design and construction.</p>','2022-07-21 08:56:07','2022-07-21 08:56:47'),(160,82,'Equipment','<p>Equipment must have service contracts and appropriate measures for plans for preventive maintenance purposes and provide service stickers showing dates for last service and next service due dates.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Elements that are important for the life of the equipment and for safety shall be addressed early in the planning stage and should be included in contractual forms, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Compliance with quality and safety standards</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Acceptance tests and conditions to correct deficiencies revealed during acceptance</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Warranty conditions</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Enforceable assurances on availability of maintenance support</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;(technical and financial), manufacturer support, manuals and spare parts</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Training of all users and keep documentation of the same</p>','2022-07-21 09:04:39','2022-07-21 09:04:39'),(161,82,'Acceptance, Testing and Commissioning','<p>Commissioning is done by the manufacturer or his representative, Biomedical Engineer and the Surgeon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A record-keeping system should also be in place. After commissioning has been completed, the specific tests needed for ongoing quality control and safety assurance will need to be carried out.</p>','2022-07-21 09:04:39','2022-07-21 09:04:39'),(162,82,'Equipment Donation','<p>The donations should be guided by the principles developed by the WHO.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There should be effective communication between the donor, the recipient authority, and, whenever possible, the end-user, before, during, and after the donation.</p>','2022-07-21 09:04:39','2022-07-21 09:04:39'),(163,82,'Surgical Oncology Unit Equipment','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Fully equipped major and minor theatres with standard anesthetic, surgical and interventional equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Receiving area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pre-operative room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Post-operative room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Scrubbing room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Changing room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waiting area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Fully equipped endoscopy suite</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 09:04:39','2022-07-21 09:04:39'),(164,82,'In-patient Surgical Wards','<p>a. Wards</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Beds</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Wheelchairs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Trolleys</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iv. Consumable and reusable equipment for IV and medication equipment</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Phlebotomy equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bedside Cabinets</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurses&rsquo; station with cabinets/shelves</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>BP Monitors</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Thermometers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Weighing scale</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Heightometer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Crash cart</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waste segregation bins</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medicine Cabinets&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Consumables cabinets</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 09:04:39','2022-07-21 09:04:39'),(165,82,'Decommissioning Requirements','<p>Safety assessment survey report of the hazards involved during decommissioning exercise. Have a Decommissioning Plan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Have hazardous waste management, transport, and disposal plan for the decommissioning.</p>','2022-07-21 09:04:39','2022-07-21 09:04:39'),(166,83,'Human Resource','<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Anesthesiologists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Biomedical engineer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical Lab personnel&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Cancer Registrar</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical Officer anesthetist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurse anesthetist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Gynaecology Oncologist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Housekeeping staff</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Interventional radiologists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical Officers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical social worker</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurse &ndash; General with theatre experience</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nutritionist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical/ hemato-onco, Pediatric, Radiation Oncologists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Surgeons</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Q/A</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>IPC</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical Counsellors</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Physiotherapists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pharmacists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurse-palliative care</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Occupational therapists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 09:10:40','2022-07-21 09:10:40'),(167,83,'Core human resource','<table cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Human resource category&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Minimum Qualifications&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Anesthesiologists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>- </strong>MMed in Anesthesia&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in charge of ICU/HDU</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Medical oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>- MMED and a fellowship in medical oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>as an oncologist by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>centre/facility; assessment, initiation, review of&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>patients cancer treatment; chair MDTs meetings;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>participate in clinical research in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Pediatric Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>MMED Paediatrics&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>with fellowship in paediatric oncology</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>centre/facility; cancer diagnosis; assessment,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>initiation, review of paediatric patients cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>treatment; chair MDTs meetings; participate in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>clinical research in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Gynaecology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>MMED Obs/Gyne with&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>a fellowship in Gynae&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Oncology.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>as a Gynae oncologist&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>centre/facility; assessment, initiation, surgical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>management and review of gynaecological&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>cancer patients; participate in MDTs meetings;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>participate in clinical research in oncology;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>screening for gynae cancers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Radiation oncologists/clinical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>- MMED/Fellowship in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>radiation oncology/</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Clinical oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>as an oncologist by&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; in charge of radiotherapy treatment;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>assessment, initiation, review of patients cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>treatment and patient follow up; treatment&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>planning; chair MDTs meetings; participate in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>clinical research in oncology; participates in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>equipment procurement&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Haemato-oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>- MMED/Fellowship&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>with specialization in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>hemato-oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; cancer diagnosis; assessment, initiation, review of patients cancer treatment; chair&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>MDTs meetings; participate in clinical research&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Clinical Officer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>anesthetist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>- Higher Diploma in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Anesthesia&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by the Clinical Officers Council</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in consultation with the anesthesiologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Cancer registrars</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>- Degree/diploma&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>holder in Health Records &amp; information.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>registration from&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>African Cancer Registry Network (AFCRN)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>approved provider</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Cancer data abstraction, maintenance of cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>patients records and participation in cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Clinical counselors&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Diploma/degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>psychological counseling.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- License to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>from relevant body</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Counseling of patients and their caregivers/</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>families on cancer; patient navigation; research;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Housekeeping&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>staff</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Relevant training in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>housekeeping</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training in safe handling of hazardous&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>products</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Handling of waste and cleaning</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Medical social&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>worker</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Diploma or bachelors&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in social Sciences</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Assessment of socio-economic background of&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>patients; Contact tracing; patient navigation;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Nurse - General&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(adult care and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>pediatric care)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Have Theatre experience/Training in Theatre Nurs</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Providing nursing care to cancer patients in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>collaboration with other members of the MDT,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in all areas of cancer treatment; health education; screening activities; participate in clinical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research in oncology; screening activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Nutritionists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>- Diploma or degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nutrition&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- License to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>from Nutritionists &amp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Dieticians Council</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Provision of nutritional counseling and support&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>to patients and their families/caregivers; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Quality Assurance&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Officer/ Safety&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>A designated Quality&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Assurance Officer/&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Safety health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Liaise with all departments to ensure safety &amp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>quality assurance is embedded in their processes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Infection Prevention and Control</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>-Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and Certification in IPC</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>-Monitor the rate of infections</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure proper waste management</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure proper use of PPE</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure hand hygiene compliance</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Biomedical engineering officers&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(medical engineers or technologist)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>- Diploma or bachelors&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in medical engineering&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>and trained on maintenance of cancer equipment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered by the&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Association of Medical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Engineers of Kenya&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(AMEK) or relevant&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>international body</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Installation, maintaining service contracts and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>equipment documentation and regular maintenance of cancer equipment at t</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Pharmacists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>- Degree in pharmacy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to Practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by PPB&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and certification in chemotherapy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>handling and administration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Preparation of chemotherapy medications under supervision of a clinical pharmacist; member of MDT; research; supply chain management&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>of oncology commodities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Surgeons</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>MMED Surgery or&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>equivalent and/or specialization in Oncology.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of a surgical cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>facility; assessment, conduct surgery and review&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>of cancer patients after surgery; participate in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research and MDT activities; patient referrals</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Medical Laboratory technologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Diploma or degree&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in Medical Laboratory&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(Bsc) or related discipline&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;- Registered and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>licensed by KMLTTB&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Each section of the&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>laboratory to be headed by a medical laboratory technologist with&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>a diploma in Medical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Laboratory Sciences in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>the disciplines</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;- Clinical Cytology/</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Histopathology, Biochemistry, Microbiology, Immunology,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Molecular Sciences,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Blood Transfusion/</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Haematology Sciences,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Epidemiology, public&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>health or virology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Provide lab services, research; sample collection;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>safe waste disposal; relay of results</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>','2022-07-21 09:10:40','2022-07-21 09:10:40'),(168,83,'Supportive Human Resource/Auxilliary/Adjunct','<table cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Human resource category&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Minimum Qualifications&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Medical Officers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>- MBCHB</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by KMPDB - Training&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>and certification in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>chemotherapy handling and administration</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Health education; screening activities; assess,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>prescribe, administer subsequent cancer treatment under supervision of an oncologist; participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Nurses - Palliative&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>care</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Specialized Palliative&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>care nursing - Higher&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Diploma, MSc Nursing&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>or an accredited Palliative program&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the palliative&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>care services in the facility; nursing care to cancer patients in the MDT; comprehensive patient&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>assessments; Pain and Symptom management;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Management of treatment side effects; Patient&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>navigation activities; initiating , organizing and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>facilitating family conferences and advance care&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>planning; end of life and bereavement care;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>clinical research in palliative care; advocacy;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>mentorship and teaching; policy formulation&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>and implementation</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Nurse anesthetist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Higher diploma in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>anesthesia</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed by NCK</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in consultation with the anesthesiologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Interventional&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>radiologists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>- MMED in radiology</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Fellowship in interventional Radiology</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by KMDPB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>In-charge of interventional diagnostic radiology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>activities including biopsy collection; research;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Occupational&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>therapists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Diploma, higher diploma or bachelors in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>occupational therapy</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Provision of rehabilitative services to patients;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Physiotherapists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Diploma, higher diploma or bachelors in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>physiotherapy</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Provision of rehabilitative services to patients;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:0pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>','2022-07-21 09:10:40','2022-07-21 09:10:40'),(169,84,'Operational Considerations','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><em>Procedure for designation as a radiotherapy Cancer Centre</em></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>A facility that plans to offer radiotherapy cancer service must apply for designation to NCI Kenya and should adhere to the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The proposal for the radiotherapy Cancer Centre designation shall specify the objectives of the cancer management program, the range of services to be provided, the approximate number of patients to be treated, and the physical infrastructure, equipment, human resources and operational management resources, as laid out in this document.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The facility will be issued with a comprehensive checklist of the components required for a radiotherapy Cancer Centre before it submits the application for designation.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Proposals for a radiotherapy Cancer Centre designation shall be submitted to the Chief Executive Officer National Cancer Institute Kenya (NCI-K), together with the application form for approval not less than 90 days before the intended commencement of operations of the cancer center.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Only upon final approval by the NCI-K will a facility be designated as a radiotherapy Cancer Centre. NCI-K will ensure that the Centre maintains the services and standards outlined in these Guidelines in order to retain this designation. The certificate of radiotherapy Cancer Management Centre designation (based on the service (s) to be offered) will be issued by NCI-K and shall be displayed at the facility.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>NCI-K will conduct inspections and accreditation after every two years to ensure compliance to the guideline, however NCI-K can conduct adhoc inspections to ensure standards are maintained</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 09:26:02','2022-07-21 09:26:02'),(170,84,'Service Norms','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The National Guidelines for radiotherapy Cancer Management shall form the basis for clinical management at the facility.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The radiotherapy center or unit must have NCI-K-approved protocols for the treatment of all malignancies they manage founded on sound scientific principles and evidence-based medicine which must be accessible to the radiotherapy clinical team at the center at all times.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The protocols must be updated as appropriate, readily available, and displayed.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The radiotherapy center or unit shall also commit to quality improvement, supporting cancer research and improving the training and mentoring of health care&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The radiotherapy center or unit shall have the infrastructure in place to be able to carry out cancer registration and notification to the National Cancer Registry.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 09:26:02','2022-07-21 09:26:02'),(171,84,'Service Delivery Considerations','<p>Every radiotherapy cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Formulate and prominently display a service charter that details the roles and responsibilities of both the patient and the center.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide integrated and multidisciplinary care</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Prioritize coordination and planning for professionals to help facilitate access to care at other levels of care, including awareness creation,</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>screening/early detection, case management, and appropriate referrals.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a reasonable time frame &ndash; Radiotherapy treatments should commence &nbsp; within 2 weeks post treatment planning completion.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Follow evidence-based protocols and guidelines.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have informed consent obtained prior to all radiotherapy treatments. In case of a minor, a parent/guardian shall give consent. The information prior to consenting shall be provided in a manner easily understandable</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>by the patient. The rights of the child should be prioritized.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish clear navigation systems to enable patients&rsquo; access to services.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Design patient-tracking systems for patient follow-up throughout the continuum of care.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Develop standard operating procedures for every service being provided.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 09:26:02','2022-07-21 09:26:02'),(172,84,'Clinical Radiotherapy Management Considerations','<p>The radiotherapy cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide cancer management that is holistic and patient-centered for best care outcomes&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Before initiation of treatment, clearly define and communicate the goals of care to the patient in accordance with a patient care plan</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide the patient the right to detailed information on his/her condition, and treatment options including clinical trials, side effects, expected outcome, and prognosis.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow the patient the right to seek a second or additional opinion before consenting to initiation of treatment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all aspects of carefully documented, stored and easily retrievable.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow access of patients to their records as well as medical reports when needed</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Comprehensively document patient history</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 09:26:02','2022-07-21 09:26:02'),(173,84,'Multi-disciplinary Tumor Boards','<p>The radiotherapy cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish multidisciplinary teams (MDTs)/tumor boards which shall guide and direct cancer management</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have MDTs meet regularly and have participation from all relevant disciplines depending on the cancer case and the level of care</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all complex cases discussed by a multidisciplinary team</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have an MDT coordinator who will organize for meetings, keep records of discussions and&nbsp; provide reports on cancer patient management</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The outcomes of the MDT&rsquo;s discussion must be documented in the patient file.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Utilize technology to convene virtual MDT discussions with proper documentation of the same&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 09:26:02','2022-07-21 09:26:02'),(174,84,'CT Simulation Capacity Considerations','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Pretreatment&nbsp; imaging</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Incorporate clinical findings in conducting pretreatment imaging modalities</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use a dedicated wide bore CT simulator with aperture of not less than 70cm preferably 80cm</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Reference room lasers should be installed&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use a standard&nbsp; simulation protocol for pretreatment Imaging</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use internationally and locally recognized standards and guidelines for the safe installation, operation and use of imaging equipment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Incorporate appropriate and site specific immobilization devices&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Incase CT simulator is not available, a conventional simulator must be available.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. Radiation Oncology Considerations</strong><br />\r\nThe radiotherapy centre shall:<br />\r\na) Provide radiation oncology services in adherence to IAEA and local regulatory body guidelines including radiation safety protection.<br />\r\nb) Fully document all ionizing radiation therapeutic applications and maintain proper records for treatment planning simulation, isodose distribution plan, dosimetry, brachytherapy and physics documentation.<br />\r\nc) Deliver the most novel and advanced technologies available for radiation oncology. These technologies should be cost-eﬀective, efficient, upgradable and practical.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d) Provide adequate information to patients receiving radiotherapy regarding the procedure to be done.<br />\r\n<br />\r\ne) For brachytherapy source, acquire relevant licenses from KNRA that guides source shipping, handling, storage and disposal upon depletion of radioisotopes including radiation safety program designed for the practice.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</p>','2022-07-21 09:26:02','2022-07-21 09:26:02'),(175,84,'Occupational health and safety considerations','<p>The radiotherapy central shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Be subject to an annual inspection by the local regulatory body and adhere to the basic safety standards as set by the regulatory body.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disclose labeling laws for identification and classification of radiation by types of hazards, including radiation labels and safety data sheets.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish a system for identification and surveillance of exposure: estimating the number of workers who come into contact with substances and are employed in occupations with increased carcinogenic risk, and reducing to a minimum the number of workers exposed, the duration of exposure and the degree of exposure, and establishing an appropriate system of records.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ensure medical surveillance applies to all healthcare workers in the radiotherapy unit and includes assessment and documentation of symptom complaints, physical findings &amp; laboratory values</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide personal protective equipment for workers and decontamination facilities in the workplace.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish/develop guidelines and recommendations for the proper use and handling of radioactive substances and training packages for healthcare workers.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a system of monitoring services at the workplace and assess occupational exposures.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Empower workers by providing them with access to information about their exposures and risks.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have programs to monitor employee performance, mental health, work-life balance and put in place debriefing programs.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 09:26:02','2022-07-21 09:26:02'),(176,84,'Waste Management','<p>The Radiotherapy cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dispose of radioactive waste produced in the process of the diagnosis and treatment of cancer in accordance with international and relevant local guidelines.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have written policies and SOPs for hazardous waste describing requirements for the segregation, packaging, labeling, collection, transportation, and storage of waste within the facility.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide waste disposal amenities and commodities.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Conduct regular capacity building on waste disposal for all healthcare providers including support staff.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide appropriate PPEs for handling hazardous waste.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Minimize the risk of contaminating the local water supply and/or soil with radio-active waste. Hazardous materials shall never be discarded into waste water (sink or toilet) or into a landfill.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 09:26:02','2022-07-21 09:26:02'),(177,84,'Emergency Medical Care','<p>The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have facilities and human resources to handle oncologic and palliative care emergencies.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Develop and display SOPs on emergency care.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ensure medical staffs are trained in BLS/ACLS.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stabilize the patient and expeditiously refer for emergency management where applicable.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Be well equipped with resuscitation commodities and equipment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 09:26:02','2022-07-21 09:26:02'),(178,84,'Adverse Events','<p>The Radiotherapy cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The document, discuss internally, put in place mitigation measures and then reports to the relevant regulatory body any adverse event that occurs as a result of cancer diagnosis or treatment<em>.</em><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 09:26:02','2022-07-21 09:26:02'),(179,84,'Death of a Patient','<p>The Radiotherapy cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Document all deaths occurring whilst patients are undergoing treatment appropriately.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Offer bereavement support to the family.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have periodic mortality meetings where cancer deaths are discussed by a multidisciplinary team.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 09:26:02','2022-07-21 09:26:02'),(180,85,'Human Resource','<p>The human resource requirements for the chemotherapy centre are as follows with core staff and supportive staff</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:#9fceee; height:70.55pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Human resource category</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:#9fceee; height:70.55pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Minimum Qualifica- tions</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:#9fceee; height:70.55pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:#9fceee; height:70.55pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Staff Establishment</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:51.95pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Anesthesiologists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:51.95pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MMed in Anesthesis</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p>(Licensed to practice by&nbsp; KMPDB)</p>\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:51.95pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management; in charge of ICU/HDU</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:51.95pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:146.3pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Biomedical engineering officers (medical engineers or technologist)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:146.3pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or bachelors in medical engineering and trained on maintenance of cancer equipment.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered by the Association of Medical Engineers of Kenya (AMEK) or relevant international body</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:146.3pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Installation, maintaining service contracts and equipment documentation and regular maintenance of cancer equipment at the&nbsp; facility</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:146.3pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:158.3pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Cancer registrars</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:158.3pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Degree/diploma holder in Health Records &amp; information management (registered by AMRO-K or by an established HRIM Board)</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in cancer registration and notification by NCI-K or NCI-K approved provider.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:158.3pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Cancer data abstraction, notification/data entry and maintenance of cancer patients records and participation in cancer research.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Reception and registration, storage, filing and retrieval, clinic preparation, file tracing, report generation/sharing and editing files.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:158.3pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:76.85pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Clinical counselors</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:76.85pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma/degree in psychological counseling.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice from relevant body</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:76.85pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Counseling of patients and their caregivers/ families on cancer; patient navigation; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:76.85pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:81.05pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Clinical Officer anesthetist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:81.05pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Higher Diploma in Anesthesia</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice by the Clinical Officers Council</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:81.05pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management in consultation with the&nbsp; anesthesiologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:81.05pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:234.05pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Clinically qualified Medical Physicists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:234.05pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Bsc in physics with postgraduate training in medical physics or Msc Medical Physics with clinical training in radiotherapy physics</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:234.05pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Responsible for equipment selection, specifications, acceptance, delivery, design of installations and shielding requirements, com- missioning and management for radiotherapy, diagnostics and nuclear medicine; Treatment planning in collaboration with the radiation oncologist; safety assessment, establishment, measurement and supervision of QA for radiotherapy and nuclear medicine devices; radiation protection and safety; dose calibration and instrumentation; technical supervision of maintenance; research and innovation of new medical devices; teaching &ndash; radiation protection &amp; users of equipment.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:234.05pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:86pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Housekeeping staff</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:86pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Relevant training in housekeeping</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Training in safe handling of hazardous products</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:86pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Handling of waste and cleaning</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:86pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:86pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Medical Officers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:86pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MBCHB</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice by&nbsp; KMPDB&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - Training and certification in chemotherapy handling and administration</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:86pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Health education; screening activities; assess, prescribe, administer subsequent cancer treatment under supervision of an oncologist; participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:86pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:86pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Medical social worker</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:86pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or&nbsp; bachelors in social Sciences</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:86pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Assessment of socio-economic background of patients; Contact tracing; patient navigation; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:86pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:86pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Patient navigators</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:86pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Training in customer service</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Training in basic life support for non-medical providers</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:86pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Receiving and guiding patients</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:86pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:44.9pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Nurse anesthetist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:44.9pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Higher diploma in anesthesia</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed by NCK</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:44.9pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management in consultation with the&nbsp; anesthesiologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:44.9pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:152.9pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Oncology nurse&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:152.9pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MSc Nursing or equivalent focused in oncology Nursing or HND oncology nursing&nbsp;</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya (NCK)</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:152.9pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; providing nursing care to cancer patients; health education; screening activities; part of the MDT; comprehensive patient assessments; symptom management; treatment side effects management; patient navigation activities; clinical research in oncology; advocacy; mentorship and teaching; policy formulation and implementation; screening&nbsp; activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:152.9pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:184.4pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>General nurse</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:184.4pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or Degree in Nursing</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Certification in chemotherapy handling and administration (those working in chemotherapy units)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Undergone an appropriate induction pro- gram in cancer management</p>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:184.4pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Providing nursing care to cancer patients in collaboration with other members of the MDT, in all areas of cancer treatment; health education; screening activities; participate in clinical research in oncology; screening&nbsp; activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:184.4pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:151.7pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Nurse Manager</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:151.7pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>BSc Nursing with Specialized oncology nursing training,</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Additional qualification in admin and MSc is an added advantage</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>&nbsp;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:151.7pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Head of Nursing oncology services; Coordination, Directing and organization of patient care activities in the unit; Resource management and Budgeting; Staffing activities; Quality management; Reporting participate in MDTs meetings; Participate in clinical research; policy formulation, implementation and&nbsp; monitoring</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:151.7pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:68.9pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Nutritionists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:68.9pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or degree in Nutrition</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>License to practice from Nutritionists &amp; Dieticians Council</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:68.9pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Provision of nutritional counseling and support to patients and their families/caregivers; re- search; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:68.9pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:58.55pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Radiation Safety Officer (RSO)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:58.55pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Advanced degree in Medical Physics, Health Physics, radiation physics or equivalent</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:58.55pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Supervised training for 6 months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Radiation Protection and Safety</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:58.55pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:54.5pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Psychologists (both adult and pediatric)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:54.5pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Degree in psychology.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>License to practice from relevant body</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:54.5pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Counseling of patients and their caregivers/ families on cancer; patient navigation; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:54.5pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:102.05pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Quality Assurance Officer/ Safety health officer</p>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Quality assurance officers</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Radiation Safety Officers</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Patient Safety officer</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p>Occupational safe- ty &amp; health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:102.05pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>A designated Quality Assurance Officer/ Safety health officer</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:102.05pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Liaise with all departments to ensure safety &amp; quality assurance is embedded in their processes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:102.05pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:121.85pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Radiation oncologists/clinical oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:121.85pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MMED/Fellowship in radiation oncology/ Clinical oncology</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice as an oncologist by KMPDB</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:121.85pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; in charge of radiotherapy treatment; assessment, initiation, review of patients cancer treatment and patient follow up; treatment planning; chair MDTs meetings; participate in clinical research in oncology; participates in equipment procurement</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:121.85pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:85.85pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Paediatric Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:85.85pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MMED Paediatrics with fellowship in paediatric oncology</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice by&nbsp; KMPDB</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:85.85pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; cancer diagnosis; assessment, initiation, review of paediatric patients cancer treatment; chair MDTs meetings; participate in clinical research in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:85.85pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:85.85pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Radiation Therapists (RTT) /Therapy radiographers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:85.85pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>-Diploma or higher diploma in radiation therapy</p>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>-&nbsp; Trained in BLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:85.85pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Participate in treatment planning; administer radiotherapy&nbsp; treatment&nbsp; under&nbsp; supervision&nbsp; of the radio-oncologist; participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:85.85pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:85.85pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Radiotherapy Services Manager</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:85.85pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>The officer in charge to hold at least a bachelor&rsquo;s degree in therapy radiography</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:85.85pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>To head and coordinate radiotherapy services in the centre</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:85.85pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>','2022-07-21 09:27:47','2022-07-21 09:27:47'),(181,86,'Equipment','<p>Equipment must have service contracts and appropriate measures for plans for preventive maintenance purposes and provide service stickers showing dates for last service and next service due dates. Elements that are important for the life of the equipment and for safety shall be addressed early in the planning stage and should be included in contractual forms, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Compliance with quality and safety standards</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Acceptance tests and conditions to correct deficiencies revealed during acceptance</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Warranty conditions</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Enforceable assurances on availability of maintenance support (technical and financial), manufacturer support, manuals and spare parts</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Training of all users and keeping documentation of the same</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 09:35:17','2022-07-21 09:35:17'),(182,86,'Acceptance testing and commissioning','<p>Radiation sources need to be safely received, registered, and stored; radiation measurement equipment tested and calibrated; shielding properties of special rooms measured, and the radiation sources tested and calibrated. All major equipment will require commissioning including teletherapy machines, imaging machines (simulators), brachytherapy units, and TPSs. A record-keeping system should also be in place. After commissioning has been completed, the specific tests needed for ongoing quality control and safety assurance will need to be carried out.</p>','2022-07-21 09:35:17','2022-07-21 09:35:17'),(183,86,'Commissioning Requirements','<p>The process of Commissioning involves Pre-Commissioning and Trial run permission.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After completion of construction and installation, the applicant should approach the regulatory body for permission to carry out a trial run for commissioning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For this purpose, the applicant should submit the following to the regulatory body:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Acceptance Tests were conducted on the following equipment;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation Protection Program (RPP).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Details regarding availability of qualified and trained manpower &ndash; operator(s), radio pharmacist(s)/radio-chemist(s) and a Board approved Radiological Safety Officer (RSO).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Personnel monitoring services for all radiation workers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Appropriate radiation measuring and monitoring Instruments</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Operational procedure manual</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safe handling tools and devices required for operation and maintenance of the medical cyclotron and auxiliary equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Security Plan</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Submit the Commissioning Test Report&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>After successful trial runs, the applicant becomes eligible for obtaining consent for trial operations.</p>','2022-07-21 09:35:17','2022-07-21 09:35:17'),(184,86,'Decommissioning Requirements','<p>When the medical cyclotron is no longer to be used, permission for decommissioning shall be obtained from the Radiation Protection Board. The licensee should apply for the decommissioning license and supply the Authority with the following;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safety assessment survey report of the radiological and non-radiological hazards involved during decommissioning exercise.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Decommissioning Plan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation Protection considerations for the decommissioning workers.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Public radiation protection consideration at the vicinity.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Qualified Radiation safety supervisor designated for the exercise.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation safety equipment to be used for decommissioning.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radioactive waste management, transport and disposal plan for the decommissioning.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Site radiation decontamination and final radiation survey.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>The licensee shall submit a report on the completion of decommissioning, which includes among others; safe disposal of sources and personnel exposures received during decommissioning.</p>','2022-07-21 09:35:17','2022-07-21 09:35:17'),(185,86,'List of Equipment','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>External Beam Radiation Therapy.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Electronic Portal Imaging Device (EPID) photo imaging device for verification</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>High dose rate (HDR) brachytherapy machine (afterloader)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>CT/Conventional treatment planning simulator complete with accessories</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dosimetry quality assurance equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation Safety monitoring devices and radiation safety checklists and reporting.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>ICT infrastructure and support</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Treatment planning system</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Standardized rulers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Two-way video cameras, with audio capability</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Appropriate shielding requirements of radiation sources</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>3-D water scan phantom</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Range of radiation dosimeters for measuring radiation doses</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Immobilization devices</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mould room equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provision for anaesthesia space and recovery if facility is to offer pediatric radiation therapy</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 09:35:17','2022-07-21 09:35:17'),(186,87,'Physical Infrastructure','<p>The following section outlines the infrastructural considerations for different units. The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall ensure the physical infrastructure meets the following requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>A standard bunker for Linac</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Brachytherapy suite with a theatre</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>CT simulator room/conventional simulator room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Control room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Physics room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mould room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Administration area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Capacity for electricity, water, power backup, space</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safety considerations &ndash; fire</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disability friendly infrastructure in all areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Maintenance considerations</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Treatment planning room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Recovery area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waiting area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient Reception area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Triage area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nursing station</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Consultation room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Procedure room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Emergency room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nutrition and counselling room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate staff and patient changing rooms</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate male and female toilets for staff and patients</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Sluice room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Registry</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hand wash area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Storage area&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Conference room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Staff room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Laundry</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Holding area in case of a death</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 09:38:11','2022-07-21 09:38:11'),(187,87,'Special considerations','<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>For a radiotherapy with in-patient services, separate adult from pediatric unit.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>For pediatric services,</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 09:38:11','2022-07-21 09:38:11'),(188,88,'Human Resource','<p>The human resource requirements for the chemotherapy centre are as follows with core staff and supportive staff</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:#5b9bd5; height:39.45pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Human Resource Category</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:#5b9bd5; height:39.45pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Minimum Education</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:#5b9bd5; height:39.45pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Specialized Training &amp; Role</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:#5b9bd5; height:39.45pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Staff Establishment</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:90.75pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Cyclotron Operator(s)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:90.75pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Technical degree or equivalent e.g. BSc in Electrical/Mechanical/Instrumentation/ Bio-medical/Physics</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:90.75pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Supervised training for 6 months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>On the job training</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Radiation Protection and Safety</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Electrical and mechanical repairs</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:90.75pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:58.8pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Production Chemist (s)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:58.8pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Diploma or BSc in Chemistry or equivalent</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:58.8pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>On the job training</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Supervised training for 6 months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Radiation Protection and Safety</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:58.8pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:130.8pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Quality Control Chemist (s)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:130.8pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Diploma or BSc in Chemistry, biochemistry, pharmacy or equivalent</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:130.8pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>On the job training</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Supervised training for 6 months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Radiation Protection and Safety</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Experience in GMP</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Experience in target preparation</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Synthesis of radiotracers</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Training in laboratory operations</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:130.8pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:47.5pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Radiation Safety Officer (RSO)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:47.5pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Advanced degree in Medical Physics, Health Physics, radiation physics or equivalent</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:47.5pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Supervised training for 6 months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Radiation Protection and Safety</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:47.5pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:114.15pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Radio-pharmacist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:114.15pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Degree in pharmacy with post graduate training in radiation physics/radiopharmaceutical sciences</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:114.15pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Preparation &amp; dispensing of radio- pharmaceuticals</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Skills in aseptic manipulation &amp; safe handling of radioactive products</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Knowledge on analytical techniques for quality control</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Trained in GMP</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:114.15pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:96pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Nuclear medicine physician</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:96pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MMed or equivalent in Nuclear medicine.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p>Licensed to practice by&nbsp; KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:96pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>In-charge of nuclear medicine department; supervision; allocation of duties; assess, prescribe, prepare &amp; administer radioisotopes ; diagnosis; interpretation &amp; reporting of tests; enforce radiation protection standards for patients &amp; staff; quality control of nuclear medicine services; training; research; waste management; equip- ment selection; MDT member</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:96pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:140.25pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Nuclear medicine technologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:140.25pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>- Degree/diploma in nuclear medicine</p>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>- Trained in BLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:140.25pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Obtains patient history &amp; describe procedure to patient; administer nuclear medicine treatment; prepare &amp; administer radiopharmaceuticals; monitors patient&rsquo;s condition during procedure; perform imaging procedures for diagnosis; analyze biological specimens in the lab; nuclear waste disposal; equipment&nbsp; calibration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:140.25pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:286.5pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Clinically qualified Medical Physicists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:286.5pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Bsc in physics with postgraduate training in medical physics or Msc Medical Physics with clinical training in radiotherapy physics</p>\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:286.5pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Responsible for equipment selection, specifications, acceptance, delivery, design of installations and shielding requirements, com- missioning and management for radiotherapy, diagnostics and nuclear medicine; Treatment planning in collaboration with the radiation oncologist; safety assessment, establishment, measurement and supervision of QA for radiotherapy and nuclear medicine devices; radiation protection and safety; dose calibration and instrumentation; technical supervision of maintenance; research and innovation of new medical devices; teaching &ndash; radiation</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;protection &amp; users of equipment.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:286.5pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:167.25pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Cancer registrars</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:167.25pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Degree/diploma holder in Health Records &amp; information management (registered by AMRO-K or by an established HRIM Board)</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in cancer registration and notification by NCI-K or NCI-K approved provider.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:167.25pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Cancer data abstraction, notification/data entry and maintenance of cancer patients&rsquo; records and participation in cancer research.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Reception and registration, storage, filing and retrieval, clinic preparation, file tracing, report generation/sharing and editing files.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:167.25pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:49.35pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Qualified customer care</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:49.35pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Certificate in customer care</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:49.35pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Receiving and guiding patients</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:49.35pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:225.75pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>General nurse</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:225.75pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or Degree in Nursing</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Certification in chemotherapy handling and administration (those working in chemotherapy units)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Undergone an appropriate induction program in cancer management/ OJT on nuclear medicine.</p>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:225.75pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Providing nursing care to cancer patients in collaboration with other members of the MDT, in all areas of cancer treatment; health education; screening activities; participate in clinical research in oncology; screening activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:225.75pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:40.8pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Patient navigators</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:40.8pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>&nbsp;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:40.8pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Receiving and guiding patients</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:40.8pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:95.25pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Housekeeping staff</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:95.25pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Relevant training in housekeeping</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Training in safe handling of hazardous products</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:95.25pt; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Handling of waste and cleaning</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:95.25pt; vertical-align:top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 09:40:07','2022-07-21 09:40:40'),(189,89,'Equipment','<p>Equipment must have service contracts and appropriate measures for plans for preventive maintenance purposes and provide service stickers showing dates for last service and next service due dates. Elements that are important for the life of the equipment and for safety shall be addressed early in the planning stage and should be included in contractual forms, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Compliance with quality and safety standards</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Acceptance tests and conditions to correct deficiencies revealed during acceptance</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Warranty conditions</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Enforceable assurances on availability of maintenance support (technical and financial), manufacturer support, manuals and spare parts</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Training of all users and keep documentation of the same</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>List of Equipment for Nuclear medicine Unit</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>PET/CT&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>SPECT</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dose calibrator</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hot cell</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Barcode generator</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>UPS</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stand by generator</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>HVAC</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chiller</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dosimetry and radiation safety equipment (dosimeters, isotope dose calibrators, scintillation counter, Portable contamination monitor/survey meter)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>ICT infrastructure and support</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Standardized rulers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Two-way video cameras, with audio capability</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Appropriate shielding requirements of radiation sources</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Range of radiation dosimeters for measuring radiation doses</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Immobilization devices</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provision for anaesthesia space and recovery for pediatric patients</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computer systems</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 09:41:59','2022-07-21 09:44:35'),(190,89,'PET Equipment PET/CT Scanners','<p>The basic components of a PET system include the scintillator, detector, photomultiplier tubes (PMT), electronics, and reconstruction software. Each of these components contributes to the overall performance of the PET system.</p>','2022-07-21 09:44:35','2022-07-21 09:44:35'),(191,89,'Radionuclide Activity Calibrator','<p>A radionuclide activity calibrator is a fundamental requirement for the operation of a PET center. It allows accurately measured radiopharmaceutical doses to be administered to patients, and is also used for other laboratory tasks like measuring time-activity curves. A PET center will thus be equipped with one or more radionuclide activity calibrators, depending on the type of installation.</p>','2022-07-21 09:44:35','2022-07-21 09:44:35'),(192,89,'Radio analytical equipment','<p>Appropriate quality management systems for validation and the appropriate radio-analytical equipment for radio-analytical testing should be duly considered to ensure safety of drugs administered. HPLC, TLC, and gamma spectroscopy are used for this purpose.</p>','2022-07-21 09:44:35','2022-07-21 09:44:35'),(193,90,'Physical Infrastructure service areas','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient registration and reception area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Designated waiting area for patients and caregivers (clearly demarcated as cold area)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clearly demarcated Hot areas including:</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hot cell area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>QC Lab with calibration probes</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hot lab for preparation of radiopharmaceuticals</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Injection room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Uptake room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Scanning room (PET/CT or SPECT)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hot toilet</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waste management facilities as specified by IAEA for example a Decay tank</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stress room to increase cardiac imaging&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient holding, observation and recovery areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radioactive waste store</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Specially designated room with toilet and bathroom facilities for patients&rsquo; exclusive use to minimize contamination</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Imaging, viewing &amp; scan reporting area (with requisite infrastructure)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Iodine wards for inpatients</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ventilation of the radiopharmaceutical production facility should meet the requirements as per IAEA guidelines to prevent contamination of products and exposure of personnel to radioactivity. The production of sterile radioactive products should be carried out under negative pressure surrounded by a positive pressure zone ensuring that appropriate air quality requirements are met.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 09:45:41','2022-07-21 09:49:15'),(196,93,'Service Norms','<p>The National Guidelines for Cancer Management shall form the basis for clinical management at the facility.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. The centre or unit must have NCI-K approved protocols for diagnosis and treatment of all malignancies they manage founded on sound scientific principles and evidence-based medicine which must be accessible to the prescribers, pharmacists and nurses at the center at all times.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. The protocols must be updated as appropriate and be readily available for inspection when needed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. The center or unit shall also commit to quality improvement, supporting cancer research and improving the training and mentoring of health care e. The center or unit shall have the infrastructure in place to be able to carry out cancer registration and report to the National Cancer Registry and DHIS.</p>','2022-07-21 10:34:44','2022-07-22 15:20:48'),(197,93,'Service Delivery Considerations','<p>Service Delivery Considerations Every cancer centre shall:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Formulate and prominently display a service charter that details the roles and responsibilities of both the patient and the centre.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Provide integrated and multidisciplinary care&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Prioritize coordination and planning for professionals to help facilitate access to care at other levels of care, including awareness creation, screening/early detection, case management and appropriate downward referrals.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Have a reasonable time frame &ndash; definitive/tissue diagnosis should be done preferably within 2 weeks and the initiation of appropriate treatment within a month of diagnosis.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Follow evidence-based protocols and guidelines.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Have informed consent obtained prior to all procedures including treatments. In case of a minor, a parent/guardian shall give consent. The information prior to consenting shall be provided in a manner easily understandable by the patient. The rights of the child should be prioritized.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Establish clear navigation systems to enable patients&rsquo; access to services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;h. Design patient-tracking systems for patient follow-up throughout the continuum of care. i. Develop standard operating procedures for every service being provided</p>','2022-07-21 10:34:44','2022-07-22 15:20:48'),(198,93,'Clinical considerations','<p>Provide cancer management that is holistic and patient-centered for best care outcomes b. Before initiation of treatment, clearly define and communicate the goals of care to the patient in accordance with a patient care plan c. Provide the patient the right to detailed information on his/her condition, and treatment options including clinical trials, side effects, expected outcome and prognosis. d. Allow the patient the right to seek a second or additional opinion before consenting to initiation of treatment. e. Have all aspects of carefully documented, stored, and easily retrievable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Allow access of patients to their records as well as laboratory samples when needed g. Comprehensively document patient history</p>','2022-07-21 10:34:44','2022-07-22 15:20:48'),(199,93,'Multi-disciplinary Tumor Boards','<p>Definition; the multidisciplinary expert team that should manage cancer patients in a consultative approach</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;The cancer center shall: a. Establish multidisciplinary teams (MDTs)/tumor boards which shall guide and direct cancer management b. Have MDTs meet regularly and have participation from all relevant disciplines depending on the cancer case and the level of care c. Have all complex cases discussed by a multidisciplinary team d. Have an MDT coordinator who will organize for meetings, keep records of discussions and provide reports on cancer patient management e. Utilize technology to convene virtual MDT discussions with proper documentation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It consists of different experts including &ndash; medical oncologists, radiation/clinical oncologist, surgeon, pathologist, palliative physicians and specialists, oncology pharmacists, oncology nurse, radiologists, interventional radiologists, hematologists, medical physicists, radiation therapists/therapy radiographers, medical laboratory technologists specialized in different laboratory disciplines.</p>','2022-07-21 10:34:44','2022-07-22 15:20:48'),(200,93,'Diagnostic Imaging','<p>&nbsp;The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Incorporate clinical findings in conducting diagnostic imaging modalities&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Consider image-guided diagnostics where applicable</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use a standard protocol for conducting imaging procedures or an MOU with a facility with that has standard protocol for conducting imaging procedures.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use internationally and locally recognized standards and guidelines for the safe installation, operation and use of imaging equipment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use a standard imaging diagnostic reporting protocol&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Outsource/provide access to an accredited imaging diagnostic facility</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 10:34:44','2022-07-22 15:20:48'),(201,93,'Nursing Considerations','<p>The cancer center shall:-</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide oncology and palliative nursing care for the entire continuum of care (Prevention, Awareness, screening, early detection, diagnosis, treatment, survivorship and end of life care, and bereavement).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Support the coordinating role of oncology and palliative care nurses in the care team and community linkage for cancer patients</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 10:34:44','2022-07-22 15:20:48'),(202,93,'Chemotherapy Considerations','<p>Definition of Chemotherapy</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Have only appropriately qualified oncologists to initiate cancer patients on chemotherapy and biotherapies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;b. Have chemotherapy medications prepared by a pharmacist or pharmaceutical technologist in a bio-safety cabinet class 2B2 vented to the outside.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Provide personal protective equipment to all members of the health care team who prepare, mix, administer and transport hazardous chemotherapy drugs.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Have a program that monitors exposure to hazardous chemotherapy drugs for all health workers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Ensure pregnant and lactating health workers are not assigned to an area where chemotherapy drugs are present/being administered</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Provide education and training for safe handling of these drugs to health workers exposed to hazardous chemotherapy drugs prior to their being assigned to an area where chemotherapy agents are present. Training must be done for all staff in the facility, annually, with the educational content being specific to the activities for which the health worker is responsible.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Prior to administration of chemotherapy ensure there is a system in place to confirm that the correct medication and dosage is administered to the correct patient.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>h. Chemotherapy medicines especially vesicants like vinca alkaloids shall be whenever possible be administered via a central line e.g. using chemoports. Chemotherapy shall be administered through infusion pumps for accuracy and safety.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Have the facility ensure provision for management of extravasations and spills.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>j. Provide patients and caregivers involved in the delivery of chemotherapy at home receive some basic education and training on the principles of safe handling, dealing with spills, waste disposal and patients&rsquo; excreta. Written instructions shall be given to the patient and/or caregiver, including information on the use of oral chemotherapeutic agents.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>k. Document the process for handling hazardous drugs waste generated during compounding and administration or during spills, as well as waste (bulk) products for chemotherapy.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>l. Store chemotherapy medicines separately from other medicines &ndash; both storage area and refrigerator&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>m. Transport of chemotherapy medicines should maintain the integrity of the drug to avoid breakage or leakage that leads to spillages, contamination and exposure to the hazardous drug&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>n. Ensure labelling of chemotherapeutic agents includes storage, handling and disposal instructions&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>o. Develop facility SOPs for &ndash; designation of HD areas; receipt of HDs; storage of HDs; compounding of HDs; use and maintenance of proper engineering controls; hand hygiene and use of PPEs; deactivation, decontamination, cleaning &amp; disinfection; dispensing of HDs; transport of HDs; administering HDs, environmental monitoring; disposal of HDs; spill control and medical surveillance.</p>','2022-07-21 10:34:44','2022-07-22 15:20:48'),(203,93,'Health Information and Records & Cancer Registry Office Considerations','<p>The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Designate an office for the Cancer registry- the office should be lockable, with lockable cabinets and a computer with internet access.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Establish a health records department that will maintain all patient records in a system that is secure, confidential and easy to retrieve.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Capture data for all cancer cases comprehensively.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Notify the National Cancer Registry all new cancer cases using the cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>abstract form <a href=\"about:blank\">National Cancer Notification Form_FINAL copy.pdf</a>(NACARE) as provided for by the Cancer Control Act 2012.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Ensure that the health records department sends reports to the National&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cancer Registry and MoH-KHIS monthly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Permanently archive cancer patient records.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Respect patients&rsquo; rights to access their records at any point in their lifetime.</p>','2022-07-21 10:34:44','2022-07-22 15:20:48'),(204,93,'Palliative Care and Survivorship Considerations','<p>&nbsp;The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Provide palliative care from the point of cancer diagnosis and at all times throughout the course of illness.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Integrate palliative care with other health services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Prioritize and provide effective relief of pain and other distressing symptoms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Provide timely rehabilitative and supportive services.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Facilitate formation of patient support groups.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Establish survivorship programs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Adhere to the National Palliative Care Policy and the National Palliative Care Guideline.</p>','2022-07-21 10:34:44','2022-07-22 15:20:48'),(205,93,'Equipment Considerations','<p>The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Have all the facilities and equipment registered and licensed for the safe and effective conduct of its services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have access to a qualified biomedical engineer, who is ultimately responsible for ensuring that all equipment are in proper working condition and that the necessary safety devices are fitted and in working order.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Maintain service contracts and schedules of service with the contracted service providers to ensure regular servicing as per the manufacturer&rsquo;s instructions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Ensure equipment compliance with relevant regulations according to the appropriate governing regulatory body. Equipment more than 7 years old should not be acquired for cancer treatment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Ensure safe disposal of obsolete or unserviceable equipment as guided by the relevant regulatory body.&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 10:34:44','2022-07-22 15:20:48'),(206,93,'Referral Considerations','<p>The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Develop patient referral SOPs (<a href=\"about:blank\">ministry-of-health-referral-guidelines-37-40.pdf</a> ) which conform to the national referral guidelines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Properly document referrals to and away from the facility.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Promote upward, downward and horizontal referral where appropriate.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Facilitate referrals for specialized services that are unavailable at the centre to facilities that are accessible and are accredited by the relevant regulatory body.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Assess patients for fitness to travel and provide necessary supportive&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>mechanisms (ambulance, nurse, oxygen supply) before referral.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Provide proper patient counseling on cancer, tests to be done, costs implications and expected treatment before referral.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Refer a patient to the right specialist for further management if a service outside oncology services is required</p>','2022-07-21 10:34:44','2022-07-22 15:20:48'),(207,93,'Quality Assurance','<p>The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish a Quality Assurance Programme (QAP) that is adequately supervised and provides reports to NCI Kenya as required.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have risk assessment measures in place with objectives and systematic monitoring and evaluation so as to identify problems and system failures and guide the necessary action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Have regular morbidity and mortality meetings to identify specific clinical performance indicators.&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 10:34:44','2022-07-22 15:20:48'),(208,93,'Infection Prevention and Control','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oncology patients are at increased infection risk due to immunosuppression and frequent exposure to healthcare settings.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Have a hospital&rsquo;s infection prevention and control program must be in accordance with the WHO Practical Guidelines for Infection Control<a href=\"about:blank\">.File571.pdf</a>.</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Have hand-washing facilities for staff readily available. Hand sanitizers should be provided at every work station.</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have eyewash facilities for staff in Chemo mixing and administration areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide a designated sluicing area for linen generated in the chemo area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have isolation rooms and practice barrier nursing by ensuring PPEs are&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>available and easily accessible.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 10:34:44','2022-07-22 15:20:48'),(209,93,'Occupational health and safety','<p>The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Implement the Occupational, Health &amp; Safety (OSH) Act in the workplace.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Provide safety and health training at least once every 3 years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Be subject to annual inspection by the local regulatory body and adhere to the basic safety standards as set by the regulatory body.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Disclose labeling laws for identification and classification of chemicals by types of hazards, including medication labels and safety data sheets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Establish a system for identification and surveillance of exposure: estimating the number of workers who come into contact with substances and are employed in occupations with increased carcinogenic risk, and reducing to minimum the number of workers exposed, the duration of exposure and the degree of exposure, and establishing an appropriate system of records.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Ensure medical surveillance applies to all healthcare workers handling hazardous drugs and includes assessment and documentation of symptom complaints, physical findings &amp; laboratory values</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Provide personal protective equipment i.e N95 masks, powder-free Nitrile gloves, shoe covers, head net, goggles, non-absorbent gown, face shield for health workers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>h. Establish/develop guidelines and recommendations for proper use and handling of carcinogenic chemicals and training packages for healthcare workers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>i. Have a system for incidents monitoring and management at the workplace.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>j. Empower workers by providing them with access to information about their exposures and risks.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>k. Have programs to monitor and support employee performance, mental health, work-life balance and put in place debriefing programs.</p>','2022-07-21 10:34:44','2022-07-22 15:20:48'),(210,93,'Waste Management','<p>The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Dispose of cytotoxic waste produced in the process of the diagnosis and treatment of cancer in accordance to international and relevant local guidelines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have written policies and SOPs for hazardous waste describing requirements for the segregation, packaging, labeling, collection, transportation storage and on site treatment of waste within the facility.<a href=\"about:blank\">National-Guidelines-for-Safe-management-of-health-care-waste-Final1.pdf</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Provide waste disposal amenities and commodities.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Conduct regular capacity building on waste disposal for all healthcare providers including support staff.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Provide appropriate PPEs for handling hazardous waste.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Incinerate hazardous waste using special incinerators that can combust at 1200&deg;Centigrade and maintain documentation on the same.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Minimize the risk of contaminating the local water supply and/or soil with hazardous drugs. Hazardous drug waste shall never be discarded into waste water (sink or toilet) or into a landfill.</p>','2022-07-21 10:34:44','2022-07-22 15:20:48'),(211,93,'Emergency Medical Care','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Have facilities and human resources to handle oncologic and palliative care emergencies.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Ensure medical staffs are trained in BLS/ACLS.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Stabilize the patient and expeditiously refer for emergency management where applicable.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Be well equipped with resuscitation commodities and equipment.</p>','2022-07-21 10:34:44','2022-07-22 15:20:48'),(212,93,'Adverse Events','<p>Any adverse event that occurs as a result of cancer diagnosis or treatment must be documented, discussed internally and reported to the relevant regulatory bodies such as the Pharmacy and Poisons Board, relevant regulatory body and the NCI-K.&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 10:34:44','2022-07-22 15:20:48'),(213,93,'Death of a Patient','<p>The cancer center shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Document all deaths occurring whilst patients are undergoing treatment appropriately.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Offer bereavement support to the family.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Have periodic mortality meetings where cancer deaths are discussed by a multidisciplinary team</p>','2022-07-21 10:34:44','2022-07-22 15:20:48'),(214,94,'Core Human Resource','<p>The human resource requirements for the chemotherapy centre are as follows with core staff and supportive staff</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oncologist (Medical, Clinical)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oncology Nurse</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical Pharmacist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Cancer Registrar</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical Counsellor&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nutritionist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical social worker</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Infection Prevention and Control Expert&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Quality Assurance Expert</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient navigators</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Core Human Resource</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Human resource category&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Minimum Qualifications&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Required staff establishment (number)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation oncologist/ Medical oncologist/clinical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED/Fellowship in&nbsp;radiation oncology/Clinical oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;as an oncologist by&nbsp;KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; in charge of radiotherapy treatment;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>assessment, initiation, review of patients cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>treatment and patient follow up; treatment&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>planning; chair MDTs meetings; participate in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>clinical research in oncology; participates in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>equipment procurement&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse - Specialized oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma or BSc&nbsp;Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Specialized oncology nursing training&nbsp;at Higher Diploma,&nbsp;MSc Nursing or an&nbsp;accredited oncology program&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with&nbsp;Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provide nursing care to cancer patients in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>collaboration with other members of the MDT;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>health education; screening activities; comprehensive patient assessments; symptom&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>management; management of treatment side&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>effects; patient navigation activities; clinical research in oncology; advocacy; mentorship and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>teaching; policy formulation and implementation; screening activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer registrars</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Degree/diploma&nbsp;holder in Health Records &amp; information.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in cancer&nbsp;registration from&nbsp;African Cancer Registry Network (AFCRN)&nbsp;approved provider</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer data abstraction, maintenance of cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>patients records and participation in cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical pharmacist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Masters in clinical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>pharmacy or equivalent&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to Practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by PPB.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;- Training and certification in chemotherapy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>handling and administration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Head of pharmaceutical oncology services; allocation of duties; supervision; member of MDT;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research; in charge of supply chain of oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>commodities; in-charge of preparation of chemotherapy medications</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical counselors&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma/degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Psychological counseling.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- License to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>from relevant body</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Counseling of patients and their caregivers/</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>families on cancer; patient navigation; research;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Housekeeping&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Staff</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Relevant training in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>housekeeping</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training in safe handling of hazardous&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Products</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Handling of waste and cleaning</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical social&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Worker</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma or bachelors&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in social Sciences</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Assessment of socio-economic background of&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>patients; Contact tracing; patient navigation;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse - General&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(adult care and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>pediatric care)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Certification in chemotherapy handling and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>administration (those&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>working in chemotherapy units)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Undergone an appropriate preceptorship/mentorship program in cancer management for at least 3 or 6&nbsp; months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Providing nursing care to cancer patients in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>collaboration with other members of the MDT,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in all areas of cancer treatment; health education; screening activities; participate in clinical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research in oncology; screening activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nutritionists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nutrition or Masters</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- License to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>from Nutritionists &amp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Dieticians Council</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provision of nutritional counseling and support&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>to patients and their families/caregivers; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Porters/patient navigators</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>-KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training in customer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>service&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- First aid Training&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Ferrying of patients between service points&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>within the facility</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Quality Assurance&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Officer/ Safety&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>A designated Quality&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Assurance Officer/&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Safety health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Liaise with all departments to ensure safety &amp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>quality assurance is embedded in their processes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Infection Prevention and Control</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>-Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and Certification in IPC</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>-Monitor the rate of infections</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure proper waste management</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure proper use of PPE</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure hand hygiene compliance</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 15:29:52','2022-07-21 15:31:25'),(215,94,'Supportive Human Resource','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Human resource category&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Minimum Qualifications&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Required staff establishment (number)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical Officers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MBCHB</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by KMPDB - Training&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>and certification in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>chemotherapy handling and administration</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Health education; screening activities; assess,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>prescribe, administer subsequent cancer treatment under supervision of an oncologist; participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical Officers in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Higher National&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Diploma in Clinical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Medicine Oncology.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by the Clinical Officers&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Council</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Health education; screening activities; assess,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>prescribe and administer subsequent cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>treatment under supervision of an oncologist;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurses - Palliative&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>care</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Specialized Palliative&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>care nursing - Higher&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Diploma, MSc Nursing&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>or an accredited Palliative program&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of K</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the palliative&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>care services in the facility; nursing care to cancer patients in the MDT; comprehensive patient&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>assessments; Pain and Symptom management;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Management of treatment side effects; Patient&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>navigation activities; initiating , organizing and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>facilitating family conferences and advance care&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>planning; end of life and bereavement care;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>clinical research in palliative care; advocacy;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>mentorship and teaching; policy formulation&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>and implementation</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Pharmaceutical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>technologists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma/Higher&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>National diploma in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Pharmacy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Enrolled to Practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by PPB&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and certification in chemotherapy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>handling and administration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Preparation of chemotherapy medications&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>under supervision of a clinical pharmacist; research; supply chain management of oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>commodities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Pharmacists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Degree in pharmacy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to Practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by PPB&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and certification in chemotherapy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>handling and administration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Preparation of chemotherapy medications under supervision of a clinical pharmacist; member of MDT; research; supply chain management&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>of oncology commodities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>','2022-07-21 15:30:58','2022-07-21 15:31:25'),(216,95,'Chemotherapy Equipment','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Equipment must have service contracts and appropriate measures for plans for preventive maintenance purposes and provide service stickers showing dates for last service and next service due dates. Elements that are important for the life of the equipment and for safety shall be addressed early in the planning stage and should be included in contractual forms, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Compliance with quality and safety standards</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Acceptance tests and conditions to correct deficiencies revealed during acceptance</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Warranty conditions</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Enforceable assurances on availability of maintenance support (technical and financial), manufacturer support, manuals and spare parts</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Training of all users and keep documentation of the same</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Acceptance testing and commissioning</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Commissioning is done by the manufacturer or his representative, Biomedical Engineer and the Clinical Pharmacist. A record keeping system should also be in place. After commissioning has been completed, the specific tests needed for ongoing quality control and safety assurance will need to be carried out.</p>','2022-07-21 15:46:08','2022-07-21 15:47:17'),(217,95,'Chemotherapy administration area','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chemotherapy chairs</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Assorted hospital beds&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bedside cabinets&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Wheelchairs</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hazardous drug spill kit&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Infusion pumps</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>4-hooked mobile drip stands&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Lockable cabinets&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Crash cart for emergency/resuscitation including ambu-bags and masks for appropriate ages</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Suction machine&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oxygen &amp; oxygen masks</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Weighing scale</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Heightometer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Vital signs monitor including sphygmomanometer, thermometer, pulse oximeter Measuring Cylinders</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stretchers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Procedure trolleys</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Portable examination lamps</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Audio-visual equipment &ndash;Television</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clock</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>ICT equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 15:46:08','2022-07-21 15:47:17'),(218,95,'Chemotherapy reconstitution area-needs to be lockable','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>A biosafety cabinet, class 2B2 and above (must have a exhauster fitted 2 meters above the building roof)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hazardous drug spill kit&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Lockable cabinets&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Steel / granite working surface area&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>An eye wash area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Air conditioner&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 15:46:08','2022-07-21 15:47:17'),(219,95,'Oncology Pharmacy','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pharmaceutical Refrigerator with temperature monitors for oncology medicines</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Lockable cabinets</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Weighing balance</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Measuring Cylinders</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Secure storage</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Steel / granite working surface</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Reference books (e.g. Martindale, other Pharmacopoeias)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 15:46:08','2022-07-21 15:47:17'),(220,95,'Pharmacy consultation room','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Furniture</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chairs</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Desk</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Screening</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>HPV test machines and kits</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>PAP smear kits</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>VIA/VILI reagents and commodities,&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical breast exams</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Fecal occult blood test</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Digital rectal exam</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Cryotherapy and thermal ablation with the appropriate staff</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Consultation room</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Equipment to take vital signs &ndash; BP machine, thermometer,&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Examination table</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Furniture:</p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Desk</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Chair</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Shelves</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Availability of</p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Computer</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Printer</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Scanner</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Health Management Information Service</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chaplaincy and Counseling</p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>IEC materials</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Information on nutrition, sexual dysfunction and healthy lifestyle</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 15:46:08','2022-07-21 15:47:17'),(221,95,'Palliative Care & survivorship Unit','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Furniture&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Examination couch</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Storage cabinets and desks</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chairs</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dressing trolleys</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Drip stands</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>BP machine</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Thermometers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Weighing scales</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Infusion/syringe pumps</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Electronics</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Printer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 15:46:08','2022-07-21 15:47:17'),(222,95,'Rehabilitation unit','<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Appropriate rehabilitation equipment and commodities e.g. Lymphedema stockings, stoma bags, prostheses etc</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 15:46:08','2022-07-21 15:47:17'),(223,95,'Cancer registry office','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Lockable designated Office space</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Filing shelves&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computer with internet connectivity</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Furniture</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Working top</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Notice board</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 15:46:08','2022-07-21 15:47:17'),(224,96,'Chemotherapy Physical Infrastructure','<p>The cancer centre shall ensure the physical infrastructure meets the following requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient flow</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Capacity for electricity, water, power backup, space</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safety considerations &ndash; fire</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separation of adult from paediatric management areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disability infrastructure in all areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Maintenance considerations</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 15:50:15','2022-07-21 15:50:15'),(225,96,'Chemotherapy Unit Services Areas','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient registration and reception area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Triage room/observation room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Procedure rooms&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Counselling room&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waiting area for patients/caregivers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Designated Consultation room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chemotherapy administration area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oncology pharmacy</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chemo holding/receiving station in close proximity to the chemo administration area-with shelves, work tops, a hand washing area and hooks</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>At least one isolation room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Emergency room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Storage area for hazardous chemotherapy drugs with appropriate ventilation. Ideally, storage areas should have negative air pressure in relation to surrounding areas and have 12 air changes per hour</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chemotherapy reconstitution area should be large enough to contain a bio-safety cabinet</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Staff changing area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Staff room/conference room&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pantry room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate staff and patients rest rooms&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Sluice room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Storage facility for cytotoxic waste and other wastes</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disposal facilities for cytotoxic and other wastes Eye wash station/shower</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 15:50:15','2022-07-21 15:50:15'),(226,96,'Waste Management','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Modern incinerator with combustion capacity above 1200oC</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waste Holding Area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 15:50:15','2022-07-21 15:50:15'),(227,97,'Service Norms','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The National Guidelines for Cancer Management shall form the basis for clinical management at the facility.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The centre or unit must have NCI-K approved protocols for diagnosis and treatment of all malignancies they manage founded on sound scientific principles and evidence-based medicine which must be accessible to the prescribers, pharmacists and nurses at the centre at all times.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The protocols must be updated as appropriate and be readily available for inspection when needed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The centre or unit shall also commit to quality improvement, supporting cancer research and improving the training and mentoring of health care e. The centre or unit shall have infrastructure in place to be able to carry out cancer registration and reporting to the National Cancer Registry and KHIS.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 16:01:44','2022-07-21 16:01:44'),(228,97,'Service Delivery Considerations','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Every cancer centre shall:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Formulate and prominently display a service charter that details the roles and responsibilities of both the patient and the centre.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide integrated and multidisciplinary care&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Prioritize coordination and planning for professionals to help facilitate access to care at other levels of care, including awareness creation, screening/early detection, case management and appropriate downward referrals.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a reasonable time frame &ndash; definitive/tissue diagnosis should be done preferably within 2 weeks and the initiation of appropriate treatment within a month of diagnosis.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The recommended time frame between diagnosis and Surgery should be at least 120 days.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Follow evidence-based protocols and guidelines.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have informed consent obtained prior to all procedures including treatments. In case of a minor, a parent/guardian shall give consent. The information prior to consenting shall be provided in a manner easily understandable by the patient. The rights of the child should be prioritized.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish clear navigation systems to enable patients&rsquo; access to services.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Design patient-tracking systems for patient follow-up throughout the continuum of care.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Develop standard operating procedures for every service being provided</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 16:01:44','2022-07-21 16:01:44'),(229,97,'Clinical considerations','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide cancer management that is holistic and patient-centred for best care outcomes.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Before initiation of treatment, clearly define and communicate the goals of care to the patient in accordance with a patient care plan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide the patient the right to detailed information on his/her condition, treatment options including clinical trials, side effects, expected outcome and prognosis.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow the patient the right to seek a second or additional opinion before consenting to initiation of treatment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all aspects of carefully documented, stored and easily retrievable.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow access of patients to their records as well as laboratory samples when needed&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Comprehensively document patient history</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 16:01:44','2022-07-21 16:01:44'),(230,97,'Multi-disciplinary Tumor Boards','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Definition; the multidisciplinary expert team that should manage cancer patients in a consultative approach</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;The cancer centre shall:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish multidisciplinary teams (MDTs)/tumor boards which shall guide and direct cancer management&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have MDTs meet regularly and have participation from all relevant disciplines depending on the cancer case and the level of care&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all complex cases discussed by a multidisciplinary team&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have an MDT coordinator who will organize for meetings, keep records of discussions and provide reports on cancer patient management&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Utilize technology to convene virtual MDT discussions with proper documentation</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>It consists of different experts including &ndash; medical oncologist, radiation/clinical oncologist, surgeon, pathologist, palliative physician and specialists, oncology pharmacist, oncology nurse, radiologist, interventional radiologist, haematologist, medical physicist, radiation therapist/therapy radiographer, medical laboratory technologists specialized in different laboratory disciplines.</p>','2022-07-21 16:01:44','2022-07-21 16:01:44'),(231,97,'Diagnostic imaging','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(i) Incorporate clinical findings in conducting diagnostic imaging modalities&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(ii) Consider image-guided diagnostics where applicable</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(iii) Use a standard protocol for conducting imaging procedures</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(iv) Use internationally and locally recognized standards and guidelines for the safe installation, operation and use of imaging equipment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(v) Use a standard imaging diagnostic reporting protocol&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(vi) Outsource/provide access to an accredited imaging diagnostic facility</p>','2022-07-21 16:01:44','2022-07-21 16:01:44'),(232,97,'Nursing Considerations','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:-</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Provide oncology and palliative nursing care for the entire continuum of care(Prevention, Awareness, screening, early detection, diagnosis, treatment, survivorship and end of life care, bereavement).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Support the coordinating role of oncology and palliative care nurses in the&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>care team and community linkage for cancer patients</p>','2022-07-21 16:01:44','2022-07-21 16:01:44'),(233,97,'Surgical Considerations','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:-</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have Surgical site marking protocol implemented (standard site identification process, patient involved in marking, and marking done by the one doing procedure.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a Safe surgery checklist (evidence of use for verifying correct site, correct procedure, correct patient; availability of informed consent; and equipment needed are on hand, correct, and functional) See checklist <a href=\"about:blank\">Resources\\Safe surgery checklist.pdf</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide Evidence that facility has an active process of monitoring safe surgical checklist compliance.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ensure the organization uses a &ldquo;time-out&rdquo; procedure just before starting a surgical procedure.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Facilitate patients to access surgical diagnosis and treatment for solid malignancies through a multidisciplinary team approach.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Where tissue is obtained for histological examination, have the surgeon observe the SOP for histology specimen handling, storage and transport.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have surgical treatment offered conforming to internationally recognized, evidence-based surgical-oncological practices</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 16:01:44','2022-07-21 16:01:44'),(234,97,'Palliative Care and Survivorship Considerations','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Provide palliative care from the point of cancer diagnosis and at all times throughout the course of illness.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Integrate palliative care with other health services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Prioritize and provide effective relief of pain and other distressing symptoms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Provide timely rehabilitative and supportive services.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Facilitate formation of patient support groups.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Establish survivorship programs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Adhere to the National Palliative Care Policy and the National Palliative Care Guideline</p>','2022-07-21 16:01:44','2022-07-21 16:01:44'),(235,97,'Equipment Considerations','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Have all the facilities and equipment registered and licensed for safe and effective conduct of its services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have access to a qualified biomedical engineer, who is ultimately responsible for ensuring that all equipment are in proper working condition and that the necessary safety devices are fitted and in working order.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Maintain service contracts and schedules of service with the contracted service providers to ensure regular servicing as per the manufacturer&rsquo;s instructions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Ensure equipment compliance with relevant regulations according to the appropriate governing regulatory body.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Ensure safe disposal of obsolete or unserviceable equipment as guided by the relevant regulatory body.&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 16:01:44','2022-07-21 16:01:44'),(236,97,'Referral Considerations','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Develop patient referral SOPs which conform to the national referral guidelines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Properly document referrals to and away from the facility.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Promote upward, downward and horizontal referral where appropriate.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Facilitate referrals for specialized services that are unavailable at the centre to facilities that are accessible and are accredited by the relevant regulatory body.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Assess patients for fitness to travel and provide necessary supportive mechanisms (ambulance, nurse, oxygen supply) before referral.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Provide proper patient counseling on cancer, tests to be done, costs implications and expected treatment before referral.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Refer a patient to the right specialist for further management if a service outside oncology services is required</p>','2022-07-21 16:01:44','2022-07-21 16:01:44'),(237,97,'Quality Assurance','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish a Quality Assurance Programme (QAP) that is adequately supervised and provides reports to NCI Kenya as required.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have risk assessment measures in place with objectives and systematic monitoring and evaluation so as to identify problems and system failures and guide the necessary action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Have regular morbidity and mortality meetings to identify specific clinical performance indicators.</p>','2022-07-21 16:01:44','2022-07-21 16:01:44'),(238,97,'Infection Prevention and Control','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Oncology patients are at increased infection risk due to immunosuppression and frequent exposure to healthcare settings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a hospital&rsquo;s infection prevention and control program must be in accordance with the WHO Practical Guidelines for Infection Control.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have hand-washing facilities for staff readily available. Hand sanitizers should be provided at every work station.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide a designated sluicing area for linen generated in the Surgical area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have isolation rooms and practice barrier nursing by ensuring PPEs are available and easily accessible.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide decontamination and sterilization areas. (The decontaminant, sodium hypochlorite 5%)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 16:01:44','2022-07-21 16:01:44'),(239,97,'Occupational health and safety','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Implement the Occupational, Health &amp; Safety (OSH) Act in the workplace.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide safety and health training at least once every 3 years.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Be subject to annual inspection by the local regulatory body and adhere to the basic safety standards as set by the regulatory body.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disclose labeling laws for identification and classification of chemicals by types of hazards, including medication labels and safety data sheets.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a system for incidents monitoring and management at the workplace.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have programs to monitor and support employee performance, mental health, work-life balance and put in place debriefing programs.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 16:01:44','2022-07-21 16:01:44'),(240,97,'Waste Management','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide waste segregation and disposal amenities.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Conduct regular capacity building on waste disposal for all healthcare providers including support staff.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide appropriate PPEs for handling clinical waste</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 16:01:44','2022-07-21 16:01:44'),(241,97,'Emergency Medical Care','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have facilities and human resources to handle Surgical Oncology emergencies.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ensure medical staffs are trained in BLS/ACLS.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stabilize the patient and expeditiously refer for emergency management where applicable.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Be well equipped with resuscitation commodities and equipment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 16:01:44','2022-07-21 16:01:44'),(242,97,'Adverse Events','<p>Any adverse event that occurs as a result of the surgery must be documented, discussed internally and reported to the relevant regulatory bodies such as the Pharmacy and Poisons Board, relevant regulatory body and the NCI-K.</p>','2022-07-21 16:01:44','2022-07-21 16:01:44'),(243,97,'Death of a Patient','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Document all deaths occurring whilst patients are undergoing treatment appropriately.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Offer bereavement support to the family.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Have periodic mortality meetings where cancer deaths are discussed by a multidisciplinary team</p>','2022-07-21 16:01:44','2022-07-21 16:01:44'),(244,98,'Surgical Unit Physical Infrastructure','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall ensure the physical infrastructure meets the following requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient flow</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Capacity for electricity, water, power backup, space</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safety considerations &ndash; fire</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separation of adult from pediatric management areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disability infrastructure in all areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Maintenance considerations</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 16:12:15','2022-07-22 05:10:17'),(245,98,'All departments and units','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For centres operating within the precincts of a hospital, it can utilize similar facilities within the hospital. For stand-alone centres, these services must be provided for:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Appropriate space for the following administrative services:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Administration</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Finance</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Transport</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iv. Supply chain management</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;v. Laundry</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;vi. Healthcare waste management, including hazardous drug waste, a Lockable holding area, proper segregation and disposal, MOUs with disposal companies</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;vii. Conference room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ix. Reception area</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Utilities</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate patient and staff changing rooms</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate staff and patients rest rooms</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Staff room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 16:12:15','2022-07-22 05:10:17'),(246,98,'Health records and information – registration area','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>i.&nbsp;Office space</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Filing room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Use of NACARE system for reporting is required using secure internet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Other supportive services</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Provision for day care services where applicable</p>','2022-07-21 16:12:15','2022-07-22 05:10:17'),(247,98,'Cancer registry office','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Office space</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Filing room</p>','2022-07-21 16:12:15','2022-07-22 05:10:17'),(248,98,'Surgical Oncology Unit','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Patient registration and reception area</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Waiting area for patients and caregivers</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Consultation room&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Triage/observation room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Counseling room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Procedure room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Pharmacy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>h. Operating theatre capable of handling minor and major surgical procedures with a Patient receiving room and a patient recovery room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>i. Nutrition</p>\r\n\r\n<p>j. Palliative care</p>\r\n\r\n<p>k. Medical Laboratory Unit</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Support from;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Diagnostic radiology unit</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pathology unit</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Blood banking</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Critical care unit</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Rehabilitation centres&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Endoscopy services</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Morgue services</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 16:12:15','2022-07-22 05:10:17'),(249,98,'Inpatient oncology wards','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Separate female, male, adolescents, geriatric and pediatric wards&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Side room facilities for ward reviews of post-operative wounds, minor procedures, and emergency resuscitation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Isolation rooms for patients with infectious conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Waste management facilities</p>','2022-07-21 16:12:15','2022-07-22 05:10:17'),(250,98,'Palliative Care and Survivorship Unit','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Patient registration and reception area</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Waiting area for patients/caregivers</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Counseling room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Procedure room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Consultation room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Community room large enough to accommodate support groups</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Support services</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Pharmacy</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Nutrition</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Chaplaincy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iv. Counseling&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;v. Rehabilitative unit</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Pediatrics play area</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Nutrition counseling rooms</p>','2022-07-21 16:12:15','2022-07-22 05:10:17'),(251,98,'Design and construction requirements','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The design of any surgery department revolves around environmental control, traffic control, and the desire to prevent surgical site infection (SSI). <a href=\"about:blank\">Resources\\Surgical Operating Theatres Standards.docx</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Consult the Services of a registered Architectural and structural Engineering firms, with expertise in construction of health care facilities, for the design and construction.</p>','2022-07-21 16:12:15','2022-07-22 05:10:17'),(252,99,'Surgical Unit Equipment','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Equipment must have service contracts and appropriate measures for plans for preventive maintenance purposes and provide service stickers showing dates for last service and next service due dates.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Elements that are important for the life of the equipment and for safety shall be addressed early in the planning stage and should be included in contractual forms, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Compliance with quality and safety standards</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Acceptance tests and conditions to correct deficiencies revealed during acceptance</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Warranty conditions</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Enforceable assurances on availability of maintenance support</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;(technical and financial), manufacturer support, manuals and spare parts</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Training of all users and keep documentation of the same</p>','2022-07-21 16:16:25','2022-07-22 05:09:38'),(253,99,'Acceptance, testing and commissioning','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Commissioning is done by the manufacturer or his representative, Biomedical Engineer and the Surgeon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A record keeping system should also be in place. After commissioning has been completed, the specific tests needed for ongoing quality control and safety assurance will need to be carried out.</p>','2022-07-21 16:16:25','2022-07-22 05:09:38'),(254,99,'Equipment Donation','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The donations should be guided by the principles developed by the WHO.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There should be effective communication between the donor, the recipient authority and, whenever possible, the end-user, before, during and after the donation.</p>','2022-07-21 16:16:25','2022-07-22 05:09:38'),(255,99,'Surgical Oncology Unit Equipment','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Fully equipped major and minor theatres with standard anaesthetic, surgical and interventional equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Receiving area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pre-operative room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Post-operative room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Scrubbing room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Changing room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waiting area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Fully equipped endoscopy suite</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 16:16:25','2022-07-22 05:09:38'),(256,99,'In-patient Surgical Wards','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Wards</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Beds</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Wheelchairs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Trolleys</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iv. Consumable and reusable equipment for IV and medication equipment</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Phlebotomy equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bedside Cabinets</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurses&rsquo; station with cabinets/shelves</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>BP Monitors</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Thermometers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Weighing scale</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Heightometer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Crash cart</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waste segregation bins</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medicine Cabinets&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Consumables cabinets</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 16:16:25','2022-07-22 05:09:38'),(257,99,'Decommissioning requirements','<p>Safety assessment survey report of the hazards involved during decommissioning exercise. Have a Decommissioning Plan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Have a hazardous waste management, transport and disposal plan for the decommissioning.</p>','2022-07-21 16:16:25','2022-07-22 05:09:38'),(258,100,'Human Resource','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Anesthesiologists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Biomedical engineer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical Lab personnel&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Cancer Registrar</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical Officer anesthetist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurse anesthetist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Gynaecology Oncologist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Housekeeping staff</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Interventional radiologists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical Officers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical social worker</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurse &ndash; General with theatre experience</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nutritionist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical/ hemato-onco, Pediatric, Radiation Oncologists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Surgeons</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Q/A</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>IPC</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical Counsellors</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Physiotherapists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pharmacists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurse-palliative care</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Occupational therapists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 16:19:50','2022-07-22 05:10:44'),(259,100,'Core human resource','<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Human resource category&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Minimum Qualifications&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Anesthesiologists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMed in Anesthesia&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in charge of ICU/HDU</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED and a fellowship in medical oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>as an oncologist by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>centre/facility; assessment, initiation, review of&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>patients cancer treatment; chair MDTs meetings;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>participate in clinical research in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Pediatric Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MMED Paediatrics&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>with fellowship in paediatric oncology</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>centre/facility; cancer diagnosis; assessment,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>initiation, review of paediatric patients cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>treatment; chair MDTs meetings; participate in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>clinical research in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Gynaecology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MMED Obs/Gyne with&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>a fellowship in Gynae&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Oncology.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>as a Gynae oncologist&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>centre/facility; assessment, initiation, surgical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>management and review of gynaecological&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>cancer patients; participate in MDTs meetings;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>participate in clinical research in oncology;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>screening for gynae cancers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation oncologists/clinical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED/Fellowship in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>radiation oncology/</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Clinical oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>as an oncologist by&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; in charge of radiotherapy treatment;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>assessment, initiation, review of patients cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>treatment and patient follow up; treatment&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>planning; chair MDTs meetings; participate in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>clinical research in oncology; participates in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>equipment procurement&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Haemato-oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED/Fellowship&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>with specialization in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>hemato-oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; cancer diagnosis; assessment, initiation, review of patients cancer treatment; chair&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>MDTs meetings; participate in clinical research&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical Officer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>anesthetist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Higher Diploma in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Anesthesia&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by the Clinical Officers Council</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in consultation with the anesthesiologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer registrars</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Degree/diploma&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>holder in Health Records &amp; information.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>registration from&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>African Cancer Registry Network (AFCRN)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>approved provider</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer data abstraction, maintenance of cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>patients records and participation in cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical counselors&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma/degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>psychological counseling.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- License to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>from relevant body</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Counseling of patients and their caregivers/</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>families on cancer; patient navigation; research;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Housekeeping&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>staff</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Relevant training in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>housekeeping</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training in safe handling of hazardous&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>products</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Handling of waste and cleaning</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical social&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>worker</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma or bachelors&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in social Sciences</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Assessment of socio-economic background of&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>patients; Contact tracing; patient navigation;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse - General&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(adult care and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>pediatric care)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Have Theatre experience/Training in Theatre Nurs</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Providing nursing care to cancer patients in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>collaboration with other members of the MDT,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in all areas of cancer treatment; health education; screening activities; participate in clinical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research in oncology; screening activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nutritionists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nutrition&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- License to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>from Nutritionists &amp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Dieticians Council</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provision of nutritional counseling and support&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>to patients and their families/caregivers; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Quality Assurance&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Officer/ Safety&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>A designated Quality&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Assurance Officer/&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Safety health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Liaise with all departments to ensure safety &amp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>quality assurance is embedded in their processes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Infection Prevention and Control</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>-Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and Certification in IPC</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>-Monitor the rate of infections</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure proper waste management</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure proper use of PPE</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Ensure hand hygiene compliance</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Biomedical engineering officers&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(medical engineers or technologist)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Diploma or bachelors&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in medical engineering&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>and trained on maintenance of cancer equipment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered by the&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Association of Medical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Engineers of Kenya&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(AMEK) or relevant&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>international body</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Installation, maintaining service contracts and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>equipment documentation and regular maintenance of cancer equipment at t</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Pharmacists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Degree in pharmacy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to Practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by PPB&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Training and certification in chemotherapy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>handling and administration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Preparation of chemotherapy medications under supervision of a clinical pharmacist; member of MDT; research; supply chain management&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>of oncology commodities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Surgeons</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MMED Surgery or&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>equivalent and/or specialization in Oncology.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of a surgical cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>facility; assessment, conduct surgery and review&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>of cancer patients after surgery; participate in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research and MDT activities; patient referrals</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical Laboratory technologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma or degree&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in Medical Laboratory&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(Bsc) or related discipline&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;- Registered and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>licensed by KMLTTB&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Each section of the&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>laboratory to be headed by a medical laboratory technologist with&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>a diploma in Medical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Laboratory Sciences in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>the disciplines</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;- Clinical Cytology/</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Histopathology, Biochemistry, Microbiology, Immunology,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Molecular Sciences,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Blood Transfusion/</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Haematology Sciences,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Epidemiology, public&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>health or virology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provide lab services, research; sample collection;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>safe waste disposal; relay of results</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 16:19:50','2022-07-22 05:10:44'),(260,100,'Supportive Human Resource/Auxilliary/Adjunct','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Human resource category&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Minimum Qualifications&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical Officers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MBCHB</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by KMPDB - Training&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>and certification in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>chemotherapy handling and administration</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Health education; screening activities; assess,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>prescribe, administer subsequent cancer treatment under supervision of an oncologist; participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurses - Palliative&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>care</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma or Degree in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Nursing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Specialized Palliative&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>care nursing - Higher&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Diploma, MSc Nursing&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>or an accredited Palliative program&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the palliative&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>care services in the facility; nursing care to cancer patients in the MDT; comprehensive patient&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>assessments; Pain and Symptom management;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Management of treatment side effects; Patient&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>navigation activities; initiating , organizing and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>facilitating family conferences and advance care&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>planning; end of life and bereavement care;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>clinical research in palliative care; advocacy;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>mentorship and teaching; policy formulation&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>and implementation</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse anesthetist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Higher diploma in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>anesthesia</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed by NCK</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in consultation with the anesthesiologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Interventional&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>radiologists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED in radiology</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Fellowship in interventional Radiology</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by KMDPB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>In-charge of interventional diagnostic radiology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>activities including biopsy collection; research;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Occupational&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>therapists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma, higher diploma or bachelors in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>occupational therapy</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provision of rehabilitative services to patients;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Physiotherapists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma, higher diploma or bachelors in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>physiotherapy</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provision of rehabilitative services to patients;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>','2022-07-21 16:19:50','2022-07-22 05:10:44'),(261,101,'Procedure for designation as a radiotherapy Cancer Centre','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A facility that plans to offer radiotherapy cancer service must apply for designation to NCI Kenya and should adhere to the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The proposal for the radiotherapy Cancer Centre designation shall specify the objectives of the cancer management program, the range of services to be provided, the approximate number of patients to be treated, and the physical infrastructure, equipment, human resources and operational management resources, as laid out in this document.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The facility will be issued with a comprehensive checklist of the components required for a radiotherapy Cancer Centre before it submits the application for designation.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Proposals for a radiotherapy Cancer Centre designation shall be submitted to the Chief Executive Officer National Cancer Institute Kenya (NCI-K), together with the application form for approval not less than 90 days before the intended commencement of operations of the cancer center.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Only upon final approval by the NCI-K will a facility be designated as a radiotherapy Cancer Centre. NCI-K will ensure that the Centre maintains the services and standards outlined in these Guidelines in order to retain this designation. The certificate of radiotherapy Cancer Management Centre designation (based on the service (s) to be offered) will be issued by NCI-K and shall be displayed at the facility.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>NCI-K will conduct inspections and accreditation after every two years to ensure compliance to the guideline, however NCI-K can conduct adhoc inspections to ensure standards are maintained.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 16:45:30','2022-07-21 16:45:30'),(262,101,'Service Norms for Radiotherapy Cancer Centres','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The National Guidelines for radiotherapy Cancer Management shall form the basis for clinical management at the facility.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The radiotherapy centre or unit must have NCI-K approved protocols for treatment of all malignancies they manage founded on sound scientific principles and evidence-based medicine which must be accessible to the radiotherapy clinical team at the centre at all times.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The protocols must be updated as appropriate, readily available and displayed.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The radiotherapy centre or unit shall also commit to quality improvement, supporting cancer research and improving the training and mentoring of health care&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The radiotherapy centre or unit shall have infrastructure in place to be able to carry out cancer registration and notification to the National Cancer Registry.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 16:45:30','2022-07-21 16:45:30'),(263,101,'Service Delivery Considerations','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Every radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Formulate and prominently display a service charter that details the roles and responsibilities of both the patient and the centre.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide integrated and multidisciplinary care</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Prioritize coordination and planning for professionals to help facilitate access to care at other levels of care, including awareness creation,screening/early detection, case management and appropriate referrals.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a reasonable time frame &ndash; Radiotherapy treatments should commence &nbsp; within 2 weeks post treatment planning completion.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Follow evidence-based protocols and guidelines.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have informed consent obtained prior to all radiotherapy treatments. In case of a minor, a parent/guardian shall give consent. The information prior to consenting shall be provided in a manner easily understandable&nbsp;by the patient. The rights of the child should be prioritized.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish clear navigation systems to enable patients&rsquo; access to services.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Design patient-tracking systems for patient follow-up throughout the continuum of care.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Develop standard operating procedures for every service being provided.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 16:45:30','2022-07-21 16:45:30'),(264,101,'Clinical Radiotherapy Management Considerations','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide cancer management that is holistic and patient-centred for best care outcomes&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Before initiation of treatment, clearly define and communicate the goals of care to the patient in accordance with a patient care plan</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide the patient the right to detailed information on his/her condition, treatment options including clinical trials, side effects, expected outcome and prognosis.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow the patient the right to seek a second or additional opinion before consenting to initiation of treatment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all aspects of carefully documented, stored and easily retrievable.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow access of patients to their records as well as medical reports when needed</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Comprehensively document patient history</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 16:45:30','2022-07-21 16:45:30'),(265,101,'Multi-disciplinary Tumor Boards','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish multidisciplinary teams (MDTs)/tumour boards which shall guide and direct cancer management</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have MDTs meet regularly and have participation from all relevant disciplines depending on the cancer case and the level of care</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all complex cases discussed by a multidisciplinary team</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have an MDT coordinator who will organize for meetings, keep records of discussions and&nbsp; provide reports on cancer patient management</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The outcomes of the MDT&rsquo;s discussion must be documented in the patient file.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Utilize technology to convene virtual MDT discussions with proper documentation of the same&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 16:45:30','2022-07-21 16:45:30'),(266,101,'CT Simulation Capacity Considerations','<p><strong>Pretreatment&nbsp; imaging</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Incorporate clinical findings in conducting pretreatment imaging modalities</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use a dedicated wide bore CT simulator with aperture of not less than 70cm preferably 80cm</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Reference room lasers should be installed&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use a standard&nbsp; simulation protocol for pretreatment Imaging</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use internationally and locally recognized standards and guidelines for the safe installation, operation and use of imaging equipment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Incorporate appropriate and site specific immobilization devices&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Incase CT simulator is not available, a conventional simulator must be available.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Radiation Oncology Considerations</strong><br />\r\nThe radiotherapy centre shall:<br />\r\na) Provide radiation oncology services in adherence to IAEA and local regulatory body guidelines including radiation safety protection.<br />\r\nb) Fully document all ionizing radiation therapeutic applications and maintain proper records for treatment planning simulation, isodose distribution plan, dosimetry, brachytherapy and physics documentation.<br />\r\nc) Deliver the most novel and advanced technologies available for radiation oncology. These technologies should be cost-eﬀective, efficient, upgradable and practical.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d) Provide adequate information to patients receiving radiotherapy regarding the procedure to be done.<br />\r\ne) For brachytherapy source, acquire relevant licenses from KNRA that guides source shipping, handling, storage and disposal upon depletion of radioisotopes including radiation safety program designed for the practice.</p>','2022-07-21 16:45:30','2022-07-21 16:45:30'),(267,101,'Occupational health and safety considerations:','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy central shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Be subject to annual inspection by the local regulatory body and adhere to the basic safety standards as set by the regulatory body.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disclose labeling laws for identification and classification of radiation by types of hazards, including radiation labels and safety data sheets.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish a system for identification and surveillance of exposure: estimating the number of workers who come into contact with substances and are employed in occupations with increased carcinogenic risk, and reducing to minimum the number of workers exposed, the duration of exposure and the degree of exposure, and establishing an appropriate system of records.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ensure medical surveillance applies to all healthcare workers in the radiotherapy unit and includes assessment and documentation of symptom complaints, physical findings &amp; laboratory values</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide personal protective equipment for workers and decontamination facilities in the workplace.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish/develop guidelines and recommendations for proper use and handling of radio-active substances and training packages for healthcare workers.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a system of monitoring services at the workplace and assess occupational exposures.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Empower workers by providing them with access to information about their exposures and risks.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have programs to monitor employee performance, mental health, work-life balance and put in place debriefing programs.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 16:45:30','2022-07-21 16:45:30'),(268,101,'Waste Management','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dispose radioactive waste produced in the process of the diagnosis and treatment of cancer in accordance to international and relevant local guidelines.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have written policies and SOPs for hazardous waste describing requirements for the segregation, packaging, labeling, collection, transportation and storage of waste within the facility.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide waste disposal amenities and commodities.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Conduct regular capacity building on waste disposal for all healthcare providers including support staff.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide appropriate PPEs for handling hazardous waste.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Minimize the risk of contaminating the local water supply and/or soil with radio-active waste. Hazardous materials shall never be discarded into waste water (sink or toilet) or into a landfill.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 16:45:30','2022-07-21 16:45:30'),(269,101,'Emergency Medical Care','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have facilities and human resources to handle oncologic and palliative care emergencies.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Develop and display SOPs on emergency care.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ensure medical staffs are trained in BLS/ACLS.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stabilize the patient and expeditiously refer for emergency management where applicable.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Be well equipped with resuscitation commodities and equipment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 16:45:30','2022-07-21 16:45:30'),(270,101,'Adverse Events','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Document, discuss internally, put in place mitigation measures then report to the relevant regulatory body any adverse event that occurs as a result of cancer diagnosis or treatment.</p>','2022-07-21 16:45:30','2022-07-21 16:45:30'),(271,101,'Death of a Patient','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Document all deaths occurring whilst patients are undergoing treatment appropriately.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Offer bereavement support to the family.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have periodic mortality meetings where cancer deaths are discussed by a multidisciplinary team.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 16:45:30','2022-07-21 16:45:30'),(272,102,'Human Resource','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The human resource requirements for the chemotherapy centre are as follows with core staff and supportive staff</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Human resource category</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Minimum Qualifica- tions</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Staff Establishment</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Anesthesiologists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MMed in Anesthesis</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p>(Licensed to practice by&nbsp; KMPDB)</p>\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management; in charge of ICU/HDU</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Biomedical engineering officers (medical engineers or technologist)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or bachelors in medical engineering and trained on maintenance of cancer equipment.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered by the Association of Medical Engineers of Kenya (AMEK) or relevant international body</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Installation, maintaining service contracts and equipment documentation and regular maintenance of cancer equipment at the&nbsp; facility</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer registrars</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Degree/diploma holder in Health Records &amp; information management (registered by AMRO-K or by an established HRIM Board)</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in cancer registration and notification by NCI-K or NCI-K approved provider.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer data abstraction, notification/data entry and maintenance of cancer patients records and participation in cancer research.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Reception and registration, storage, filing and retrieval, clinic preparation, file tracing, report generation/sharing and editing files.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical counselors</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma/degree in psychological counseling.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice from relevant body</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Counseling of patients and their caregivers/ families on cancer; patient navigation; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical Officer anesthetist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Higher Diploma in Anesthesia</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice by the Clinical Officers Council</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management in consultation with the&nbsp; anesthesiologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinically qualified Medical Physicists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Bsc in physics with postgraduate training in medical physics or Msc Medical Physics with clinical training in radiotherapy physics</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Responsible for equipment selection, specifications, acceptance, delivery, design of installations and shielding requirements, com- missioning and management for radiotherapy, diagnostics and nuclear medicine; Treatment planning in collaboration with the radiation oncologist; safety assessment, establishment, measurement and supervision of QA for radiotherapy and nuclear medicine devices; radiation protection and safety; dose calibration and instrumentation; technical supervision of maintenance; research and innovation of new medical devices; teaching &ndash; radiation protection &amp; users of equipment.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Housekeeping staff</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Relevant training in housekeeping</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Training in safe handling of hazardous products</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Handling of waste and cleaning</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical Officers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MBCHB</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice by&nbsp; KMPDB - Training and certification in chemotherapy handling and administration</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Health education; screening activities; assess, prescribe, administer subsequent cancer treatment under supervision of an oncologist; participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical social worker</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or&nbsp; bachelors in social Sciences</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Assessment of socio-economic background of patients; Contact tracing; patient navigation; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Patient navigators</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Training in customer service</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Training in basic life support for non-medical providers</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Receiving and guiding patients</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse anesthetist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Higher diploma in anesthesia</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed by NCK</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management in consultation with the&nbsp; anesthesiologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Oncology nurse&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MSc Nursing or equivalent focused in oncology Nursing or HND oncology nursing&nbsp;</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya (NCK)</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; providing nursing care to cancer patients; health education; screening activities; part of the MDT; comprehensive patient assessments; symptom management; treatment side effects management; patient navigation activities; clinical research in oncology; advocacy; mentorship and teaching; policy formulation and implementation; screening&nbsp; activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>General nurse</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or Degree in Nursing</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Certification in chemotherapy handling and administration (those working in chemotherapy units)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Undergone an appropriate induction pro- gram in cancer management</p>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Providing nursing care to cancer patients in collaboration with other members of the MDT, in all areas of cancer treatment; health education; screening activities; participate in clinical research in oncology; screening&nbsp; activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse Manager</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>BSc Nursing with Specialized oncology nursing training,</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Additional qualification in admin and MSc is an added advantage</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>&nbsp;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Head of Nursing oncology services; Coordination, Directing and organization of patient care activities in the unit; Resource management and Budgeting; Staffing activities; Quality management; Reporting participate in MDTs meetings; Participate in clinical research; policy formulation, implementation and&nbsp; monitoring</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nutritionists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or degree in Nutrition</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>License to practice from Nutritionists &amp; Dieticians Council</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provision of nutritional counseling and support to patients and their families/caregivers; re- search; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation Safety Officer (RSO)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Advanced degree in Medical Physics, Health Physics, radiation physics or equivalent</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Supervised training for 6 months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Radiation Protection and Safety</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Psychologists (both adult and pediatric)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Degree in psychology.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>License to practice from relevant body</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Counseling of patients and their caregivers/ families on cancer; patient navigation; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Quality Assurance Officer/ Safety health officer</p>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Quality assurance officers</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Radiation Safety Officers</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Patient Safety officer</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p>Occupational safe- ty &amp; health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>A designated Quality Assurance Officer/ Safety health officer</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Liaise with all departments to ensure safety &amp; quality assurance is embedded in their processes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation oncologists/clinical oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MMED/Fellowship in radiation oncology/ Clinical oncology</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice as an oncologist by KMPDB</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; in charge of radiotherapy treatment; assessment, initiation, review of patients cancer treatment and patient follow up; treatment planning; chair MDTs meetings; participate in clinical research in oncology; participates in equipment procurement</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Paediatric Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MMED Paediatrics with fellowship in paediatric oncology</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice by&nbsp; KMPDB</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; cancer diagnosis; assessment, initiation, review of paediatric patients cancer treatment; chair MDTs meetings; participate in clinical research in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation Therapists (RTT) /Therapy radiographers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>-Diploma or higher diploma in radiation therapy</p>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>-&nbsp; Trained in BLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Participate in treatment planning; administer radiotherapy&nbsp; treatment&nbsp; under&nbsp; supervision&nbsp; of the radio-oncologist; participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiotherapy Services Manager</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>The officer in charge to hold at least a bachelor&rsquo;s degree in therapy radiography</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>To head and coordinate radiotherapy services in the centre</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>','2022-07-21 16:46:55','2022-07-21 16:46:55'),(273,103,'Equipment','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Equipment must have service contracts and appropriate measures for plans for preventive maintenance purposes and provide service stickers showing dates for last service and next service due dates. Elements that are important for the life of the equipment and for safety shall be addressed early in the planning stage and should be included in contractual forms, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Compliance with quality and safety standards</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Acceptance tests and conditions to correct deficiencies revealed during acceptance</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Warranty conditions</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Enforceable assurances on availability of maintenance support (technical and financial), manufacturer support, manuals and spare parts</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Training of all users and keep documentation of the same</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 16:50:15','2022-07-21 16:50:15'),(274,103,'Acceptance testing and commissioning','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Radiation sources need to be safely received, registered and stored; radiation measurement equipment tested and calibrated; shielding properties of special rooms measured; and the radiation sources tested and calibrated. All major equipment will require commissioning including tele therapy machines, imaging machines (simulators), brachytherapy units and TPSs. A record keeping system should also be in place. After commissioning has been completed, the specific tests needed for ongoing quality control and safety assurance will need to be carried out.</p>','2022-07-21 16:50:15','2022-07-21 16:50:15'),(275,103,'Commissioning requirements for Radiotherapy unit','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The process of Commissioning involves Pre-Commissioning and Trial run permission.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After completion of construction and installation, the applicant should approach the regulatory body for permission to carry out a trial run for commissioning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For this purpose, the applicant should submit the following to the regulatory body:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Acceptance Tests conducted on the following equipment;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation Protection Program (RPP).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Details regarding availability of qualified and trained manpower &ndash; operator(s), radio pharmacist(s)/radio-chemist(s) and a Board approved Radiological Safety Officer (RSO).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Personnel monitoring services for all radiation workers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Appropriate radiation measuring and monitoring Instruments</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Operational procedure manual</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safe handling tools and devices required for operation and maintenance of the medical cyclotron and auxiliary equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Security Plan</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Submit the Commissioning Test Report&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>After successful trial runs, the applicant becomes eligible for obtaining consent for trial operations.</p>','2022-07-21 16:50:15','2022-07-21 16:50:15'),(276,103,'Decommissioning requirements','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When the medical cyclotron is no longer to be used, the permission for decommissioning shall be obtained from the Radiation Protection Board. The licensee should apply for the decommissioning license and supply the Authority with the following;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safety assessment survey report of the radiological and non-radiological hazards involved during decommissioning exercise.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Decommissioning Plan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation Protection considerations for the decommissioning workers.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Public radiation protection consideration at vicinity.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Qualified Radiation safety supervisor designated for the exercise.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation safety equipment to be used for decommissioning.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radioactive waste management, transport and disposal plan for the decommissioning.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Site radiation decontamination and final radiation survey.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>The licensee shall submit a report on the completion of decommissioning, which includes among others; safe disposal of sources and personnel exposures received during decommissioning.</p>','2022-07-21 16:50:15','2022-07-21 16:50:15'),(277,103,'List of Equipment','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>External Beam Radiation Therapy.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Electronic Portal Imaging Device (EPID) photo imaging device for verification</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>High dose Rate (HDR) brachytherapy machine (afterloader)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>CT/Conventional treatment planning simulator complete with accessories</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dosimetry quality assurance equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation Safety monitoring devices and radiation safety checklists and reporting.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>ICT infrastructure and support</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Treatment planning system</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Standardized rulers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Two-way video cameras, with audio capability</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Appropriate shielding requirements of radiation sources</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>3-D water scan phantom</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Range of radiation dosimeters for measuring radiation doses</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Immobilization devices</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mould room equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provision for anaesthesia space and recovery if facility is to offer pediatric radiation therapy</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 16:50:15','2022-07-21 16:50:15'),(278,104,'Physical Infrastructure','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The following section outlines the infrastructural considerations for different units. The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall ensure the physical infrastructure meets the following requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>A standard bunker for Linac</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Brachytherapy suite with a theatre</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>CT simulator room/conventional simulator room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Control room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Physics room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mould room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Administration area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Capacity for electricity, water, power backup, space</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safety considerations &ndash; fire</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disability friendly infrastructure in all areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Maintenance considerations</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Treatment planning room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Recovery area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waiting area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient Reception area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Triage area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nursing station</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Consultation room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Procedure room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Emergency room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nutrition and counselling room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate staff and patient changing rooms</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate male and female toilets for staff and patients</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Sluice room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Registry</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hand wash area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Storage area&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Conference room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Staff room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Laundry</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Holding area in case of a death</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Special considerations:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>For a radiotherapy with in-patient services, separate adult from pediatric unit.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>For pediatric services, dedicated child-friendly rooms should be provided.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 16:51:47','2022-07-21 16:51:47'),(279,105,'Human Resource','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The human resource requirements for the chemotherapy centre are as follows with core staff and supportive staff</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Human Resource Category</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Minimum Education</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Specialized Training &amp; Role</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Staff Establishment</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cyclotron Operator(s)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Technical degree or equivalent e.g. BSc in Electrical/Mechanical/Instrumentation/ Bio-medical/Physics</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Supervised training for 6 months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>On the job training</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Radiation Protection and Safety</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Electrical and mechanical repairs</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Production Chemist (s)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma or BSc in Chemistry or equivalent</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>On the job training</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Supervised training for 6 months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Radiation Protection and Safety</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Quality Control Chemist (s)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Diploma or BSc in Chemistry, biochemistry, pharmacy or equivalent</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>On the job training</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Supervised training for 6 months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Radiation Protection and Safety</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Experience in GMP</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Experience in target preparation</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Synthesis of radiotracers</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Training in laboratory operations</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation Safety Officer (RSO)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Advanced degree in Medical Physics, Health Physics, radiation physics or equivalent</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Supervised training for 6 months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Radiation Protection and Safety</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radio-pharmacist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Degree in pharmacy with post graduate training in radiation physics/radiopharmaceutical sciences</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Preparation &amp; dispensing of radio- pharmaceuticals</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Skills in aseptic manipulation &amp; safe handling of radioactive products</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Knowledge on analytical techniques for quality control</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Trained in GMP</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nuclear medicine physician</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MMed or equivalent in Nuclear medicine.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p>Licensed to practice by&nbsp; KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>In-charge of nuclear medicine department; supervision; allocation of duties; assess, prescribe, prepare &amp; administer radioisotopes ; diagnosis; interpretation &amp; reporting of tests; enforce radiation protection standards for patients &amp; staff; quality control of nuclear medicine services; training; research; waste management; equip- ment selection; MDT member</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nuclear medicine technologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- Degree/diploma in nuclear medicine</p>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>- Trained in BLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Obtains patient history &amp; describe procedure to patient; administer nuclear medicine treatment; prepare &amp; administer radiopharmaceuticals; monitors patient&rsquo;s condition during procedure; perform imaging procedures for diagnosis; analyze biological specimens in the lab; nuclear waste disposal; equipment&nbsp; calibration</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinically qualified Medical Physicists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Bsc in physics with postgraduate training in medical physics or Msc Medical Physics with clinical training in radiotherapy physics</p>\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Responsible for equipment selection, specifications, acceptance, delivery, design of installations and shielding requirements, com- missioning and management for radiotherapy, diagnostics and nuclear medicine; Treatment planning in collaboration with the radiation oncologist; safety assessment, establishment, measurement and supervision of QA for radiotherapy and nuclear medicine devices; radiation protection and safety; dose calibration and instrumentation; technical supervision of maintenance; research and innovation of new medical devices; teaching &ndash; radiation</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;protection &amp; users of equipment.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer registrars</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Degree/diploma holder in Health Records &amp; information management (registered by AMRO-K or by an established HRIM Board)</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in cancer registration and notification by NCI-K or NCI-K approved provider.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer data abstraction, notification/data entry and maintenance of cancer patients&rsquo; records and participation in cancer research.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Reception and registration, storage, filing and retrieval, clinic preparation, file tracing, report generation/sharing and editing files.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Qualified customer care</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Certificate in customer care</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Receiving and guiding patients</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>General nurse</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or Degree in Nursing</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Certification in chemotherapy handling and administration (those working in chemotherapy units)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Undergone an appropriate induction program in cancer management/ OJT on nuclear medicine.</p>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Providing nursing care to cancer patients in collaboration with other members of the MDT, in all areas of cancer treatment; health education; screening activities; participate in clinical research in oncology; screening activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Patient navigators</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>&nbsp;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Receiving and guiding patients</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Housekeeping staff</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Relevant training in housekeeping</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Training in safe handling of hazardous products</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Handling of waste and cleaning</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>','2022-07-21 16:52:58','2022-07-21 16:52:58'),(280,106,'Equipment','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Equipment must have service contracts and appropriate measures for plans for preventive maintenance purposes and provide service stickers showing dates for last service and next service due dates. Elements that are important for the life of the equipment and for safety shall be addressed early in the planning stage and should be included in contractual forms, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Compliance with quality and safety standards</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Acceptance tests and conditions to correct deficiencies revealed during acceptance</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Warranty conditions</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Enforceable assurances on availability of maintenance support (technical and financial), manufacturer support, manuals and spare parts</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Training of all users and keep documentation of the same</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>List of Equipment for Nuclear medicine Unit</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>PET/CT&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>SPECT</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dose calibrator</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hot cell</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Barcode generator</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>UPS</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stand by generator</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>HVAC</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chiller</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dosimetry and radiation safety equipment (dosimeters, isotope dose calibrators, scintillation counter, Portable contamination monitor/survey meter)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>ICT infrastructure and support</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Standardized rulers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Two-way video cameras, with audio capability</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Appropriate shielding requirements of radiation sources</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Range of radiation dosimeters for measuring radiation doses</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Immobilization devices</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provision for anaesthesia space and recovery for pediatric patients</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computer systems</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 16:57:15','2022-07-21 16:57:15'),(281,106,'PET Equipment PET/CT Scanners','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The basic components of a PET system include the scintillator, detector, photomultiplier tubes (PMT), electronics and reconstruction software. Each of these components contribute to the overall performance of the PET system.</p>','2022-07-21 16:57:15','2022-07-21 16:57:15'),(282,106,'Radionuclide Activity Calibrator','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A radionuclide activity calibrator is a fundamental requirement for the operation of a PET centre. It allows accurately measured radiopharmaceutical doses to be administered to patients, and is also used for other laboratory tasks like measuring time-activity curves. A PET centre will thus be equipped with one or more radionuclide activity calibrators, depending on the type of installation.</p>','2022-07-21 16:57:15','2022-07-21 16:57:15'),(283,106,'Radio analytical equipment','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Appropriate quality management systems for validation and the appropriate radio-analytical equipment for radio-analytical testing should be duly considered to ensure safety of drugs administered. HPLC, TLC and gamma spectroscopy are used for this purpose.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 16:57:15','2022-07-21 16:57:15'),(284,107,'Physical Infrastructure service areas','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient registration and reception area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Designated waiting area for patients and caregivers (clearly demarcated as cold area)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clearly demarcated Hot areas including:</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hot cell area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>QC Lab with calibration probes</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hot lab for preparation of radiopharmaceuticals</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Injection room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Uptake room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Scanning room (PET/CT or SPECT)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hot toilet</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waste management facilities as specified by IAEA for example a Decay tank</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stress room to increase cardiac imaging&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient holding, observation and recovery areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radioactive waste store</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Specially designated room with toilet and bathroom facilities for patients&rsquo; exclusive use to minimize contamination</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Imaging, viewing &amp; scan reporting area (with requisite infrastructure)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Iodine wards for inpatients</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ventilation of the radiopharmaceutical production facility should meet the requirements as per IAEA guidelines to prevent contamination of products and exposure of personnel to radioactivity. The production of sterile radioactive products should be carried out under negative pressure surrounded by a positive pressure zone ensuring that appropriate air quality requirements are met.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 16:58:08','2022-07-21 16:58:08'),(285,109,'Procedure for designation as a Radiotherapy Cancer Centre','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A facility that plans to offer radiotherapy cancer service must apply for designation to NCI Kenya and should adhere to the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The proposal for the radiotherapy Cancer Centre designation shall specify the objectives of the cancer management program, the range of services to be provided, the approximate number of patients to be treated, and the physical infrastructure, equipment, human resources and operational management resources, as laid out in this document.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The facility will be issued with a comprehensive checklist of the components required for a radiotherapy Cancer Centre before it submits the application for designation.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Proposals for a radiotherapy Cancer Centre designation shall be submitted to the Chief Executive Officer National Cancer Institute Kenya (NCI-K), together with the application form for approval not less than 90 days before the intended commencement of operations of the cancer center.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Only upon final approval by the NCI-K will a facility be designated as a radiotherapy Cancer Centre. NCI-K will ensure that the Centre maintains the services and standards outlined in these Guidelines in order to retain this designation. The certificate of radiotherapy Cancer Management Centre designation (based on the service (s) to be offered) will be issued by NCI-K and shall be displayed at the facility.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>NCI-K will conduct inspections and accreditation after every two years to ensure compliance to the guideline, however NCI-K can conduct adhoc inspections to ensure standards are maintained.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 17:09:05','2022-07-21 17:09:05'),(286,109,'Service Norms for Radiotherapy Cancer Centres','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The National Guidelines for radiotherapy Cancer Management shall form the basis for clinical management at the facility.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The radiotherapy centre or unit must have NCI-K approved protocols for treatment of all malignancies they manage founded on sound scientific principles and evidence-based medicine which must be accessible to the radiotherapy clinical team at the centre at all times.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The protocols must be updated as appropriate, readily available and displayed.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The radiotherapy centre or unit shall also commit to quality improvement, supporting cancer research and improving the training and mentoring of health care&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The radiotherapy centre or unit shall have infrastructure in place to be able to carry out cancer registration and notification to the National Cancer Registry.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 17:09:05','2022-07-21 17:09:05'),(287,109,'Service Delivery Considerations','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Every radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Formulate and prominently display a service charter that details the roles and responsibilities of both the patient and the centre.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide integrated and multidisciplinary care</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Prioritize coordination and planning for professionals to help facilitate access to care at other levels of care, including awareness creation,screening/early detection, case management and appropriate referrals.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a reasonable time frame &ndash; Radiotherapy treatments should commence &nbsp; within 2 weeks post treatment planning completion.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Follow evidence-based protocols and guidelines.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have informed consent obtained prior to all radiotherapy treatments. In case of a minor, a parent/guardian shall give consent. The information prior to consenting shall be provided in a manner easily understandable&nbsp;by the patient. The rights of the child should be prioritized.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish clear navigation systems to enable patients&rsquo; access to services.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Design patient-tracking systems for patient follow-up throughout the continuum of care.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Develop standard operating procedures for every service being provided.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 17:09:05','2022-07-21 17:09:05'),(288,109,'Clinical Radiotherapy Management Considerations','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide cancer management that is holistic and patient-centred for best care outcomes&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Before initiation of treatment, clearly define and communicate the goals of care to the patient in accordance with a patient care plan</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide the patient the right to detailed information on his/her condition, treatment options including clinical trials, side effects, expected outcome and prognosis.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow the patient the right to seek a second or additional opinion before consenting to initiation of treatment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all aspects of carefully documented, stored and easily retrievable.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow access of patients to their records as well as medical reports when needed</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Comprehensively document patient history</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 17:09:05','2022-07-21 17:09:05'),(289,109,'Multi-discpilinary Tumor Boards','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish multidisciplinary teams (MDTs)/tumour boards which shall guide and direct cancer management</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have MDTs meet regularly and have participation from all relevant disciplines depending on the cancer case and the level of care</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all complex cases discussed by a multidisciplinary team</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have an MDT coordinator who will organize for meetings, keep records of discussions and&nbsp; provide reports on cancer patient management</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The outcomes of the MDT&rsquo;s discussion must be documented in the patient file.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Utilize technology to convene virtual MDT discussions with proper documentation of the same&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 17:09:05','2022-07-21 17:09:05'),(290,109,'CT Simulation Capacity Considerations','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pretreatment&nbsp; imaging</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Incorporate clinical findings in conducting pretreatment imaging modalities</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use a dedicated wide bore CT simulator with aperture of not less than 70cm preferably 80cm</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Reference room lasers should be installed&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use a standard&nbsp; simulation protocol for pretreatment Imaging</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use internationally and locally recognized standards and guidelines for the safe installation, operation and use of imaging equipment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Incorporate appropriate and site specific immobilization devices&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Incase CT simulator is not available, a conventional simulator must be available.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Radiation Oncology Considerations</strong><br />\r\nThe radiotherapy centre shall:<br />\r\na) Provide radiation oncology services in adherence to IAEA and local regulatory body guidelines including radiation safety protection.<br />\r\nb) Fully document all ionizing radiation therapeutic applications and maintain proper records for treatment planning simulation, isodose distribution plan, dosimetry, brachytherapy and physics documentation.<br />\r\nc) Deliver the most novel and advanced technologies available for radiation oncology. These technologies should be cost-eﬀective, efficient, upgradable and practical.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d) Provide adequate information to patients receiving radiotherapy regarding the procedure to be done.<br />\r\ne) For brachytherapy source, acquire relevant licenses from KNRA that guides source shipping, handling, storage and disposal upon depletion of radioisotopes including radiation safety program designed for the practice.</p>','2022-07-21 17:09:05','2022-07-21 17:09:05'),(291,109,'Occupational health and safety considerations','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The radiotherapy central shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Be subject to annual inspection by the local regulatory body and adhere to the basic safety standards as set by the regulatory body.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disclose labeling laws for identification and classification of radiation by types of hazards, including radiation labels and safety data sheets.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish a system for identification and surveillance of exposure: estimating the number of workers who come into contact with substances and are employed in occupations with increased carcinogenic risk, and reducing to minimum the number of workers exposed, the duration of exposure and the degree of exposure, and establishing an appropriate system of records.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ensure medical surveillance applies to all healthcare workers in the radiotherapy unit and includes assessment and documentation of symptom complaints, physical findings &amp; laboratory values</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide personal protective equipment for workers and decontamination facilities in the workplace.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish/develop guidelines and recommendations for proper use and handling of radio-active substances and training packages for healthcare workers.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a system of monitoring services at the workplace and assess occupational exposures.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Empower workers by providing them with access to information about their exposures and risks.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have programs to monitor employee performance, mental health, work-life balance and put in place debriefing programs.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 17:09:05','2022-07-21 17:09:05'),(292,109,'Waste Management','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dispose radioactive waste produced in the process of the diagnosis and treatment of cancer in accordance to international and relevant local guidelines.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have written policies and SOPs for hazardous waste describing requirements for the segregation, packaging, labeling, collection, transportation and storage of waste within the facility.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide waste disposal amenities and commodities.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Conduct regular capacity building on waste disposal for all healthcare providers including support staff.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide appropriate PPEs for handling hazardous waste.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Minimize the risk of contaminating the local water supply and/or soil with radio-active waste. Hazardous materials shall never be discarded into waste water (sink or toilet) or into a landfill.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 17:09:05','2022-07-21 17:09:05'),(293,109,'Emergency Medical Care','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have facilities and human resources to handle oncologic and palliative care emergencies.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Develop and display SOPs on emergency care.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ensure medical staffs are trained in BLS/ACLS.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stabilize the patient and expeditiously refer for emergency management where applicable.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Be well equipped with resuscitation commodities and equipment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 17:09:05','2022-07-21 17:09:05'),(294,109,'Adverse Events','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Document, discuss internally, put in place mitigation measures then report to the relevant regulatory body any adverse event that occurs as a result of cancer diagnosis or treatment.</p>','2022-07-21 17:09:05','2022-07-21 17:09:05'),(295,109,'Death of a patient','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Document all deaths occurring whilst patients are undergoing treatment appropriately.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Offer bereavement support to the family.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have periodic mortality meetings where cancer deaths are discussed by a multidisciplinary team.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 17:09:05','2022-07-21 17:09:05'),(296,110,'Human Resource','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The human resource requirements for the chemotherapy centre are as follows with core staff and supportive staff</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Human resource category</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Minimum Qualifica- tions</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Staff Establishment</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Anesthesiologists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MMed in Anesthesis</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p>(Licensed to practice by&nbsp; KMPDB)</p>\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management; in charge of ICU/HDU</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Biomedical engineering officers (medical engineers or technologist)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or bachelors in medical engineering and trained on maintenance of cancer equipment.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered by the Association of Medical Engineers of Kenya (AMEK) or relevant international body</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Installation, maintaining service contracts and equipment documentation and regular maintenance of cancer equipment at the&nbsp; facility</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer registrars</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Degree/diploma holder in Health Records &amp; information management (registered by AMRO-K or by an established HRIM Board)</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in cancer registration and notification by NCI-K or NCI-K approved provider.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Cancer data abstraction, notification/data entry and maintenance of cancer patients records and participation in cancer research.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Reception and registration, storage, filing and retrieval, clinic preparation, file tracing, report generation/sharing and editing files.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical counselors</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma/degree in psychological counseling.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice from relevant body</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Counseling of patients and their caregivers/ families on cancer; patient navigation; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinical Officer anesthetist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Higher Diploma in Anesthesia</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice by the Clinical Officers Council</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management in consultation with the&nbsp; anesthesiologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clinically qualified Medical Physicists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Bsc in physics with postgraduate training in medical physics or Msc Medical Physics with clinical training in radiotherapy physics</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Responsible for equipment selection, specifications, acceptance, delivery, design of installations and shielding requirements, com- missioning and management for radiotherapy, diagnostics and nuclear medicine; Treatment planning in collaboration with the radiation oncologist; safety assessment, establishment, measurement and supervision of QA for radiotherapy and nuclear medicine devices; radiation protection and safety; dose calibration and instrumentation; technical supervision of maintenance; research and innovation of new medical devices; teaching &ndash; radiation protection &amp; users of equipment.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Housekeeping staff</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Relevant training in housekeeping</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Training in safe handling of hazardous products</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Handling of waste and cleaning</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical Officers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MBCHB</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice by&nbsp; KMPDB - Training and certification in chemotherapy handling and administration</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Health education; screening activities; assess, prescribe, administer subsequent cancer treatment under supervision of an oncologist; participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical social worker</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or&nbsp; bachelors in social Sciences</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Assessment of socio-economic background of patients; Contact tracing; patient navigation; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Patient navigators</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>KCSE Certificate</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Training in customer service</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Training in basic life support for non-medical providers</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Receiving and guiding patients</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse anesthetist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Higher diploma in anesthesia</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed by NCK</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management in consultation with the&nbsp; anesthesiologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Oncology nurse&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MSc Nursing or equivalent focused in oncology Nursing or HND oncology nursing&nbsp;</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya (NCK)</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; providing nursing care to cancer patients; health education; screening activities; part of the MDT; comprehensive patient assessments; symptom management; treatment side effects management; patient navigation activities; clinical research in oncology; advocacy; mentorship and teaching; policy formulation and implementation; screening&nbsp; activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>General nurse</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or Degree in Nursing</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Certification in chemotherapy handling and administration (those working in chemotherapy units)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-Undergone an appropriate induction pro- gram in cancer management</p>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Trained in BLS/ACLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Providing nursing care to cancer patients in collaboration with other members of the MDT, in all areas of cancer treatment; health education; screening activities; participate in clinical research in oncology; screening&nbsp; activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nurse Manager</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>BSc Nursing with Specialized oncology nursing training,</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Registered with Nursing Council of Kenya.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Additional qualification in admin and MSc is an added advantage</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>&nbsp;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Head of Nursing oncology services; Coordination, Directing and organization of patient care activities in the unit; Resource management and Budgeting; Staffing activities; Quality management; Reporting participate in MDTs meetings; Participate in clinical research; policy formulation, implementation and&nbsp; monitoring</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Nutritionists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Diploma or degree in Nutrition</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>License to practice from Nutritionists &amp; Dieticians Council</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Provision of nutritional counseling and support to patients and their families/caregivers; re- search; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation Safety Officer (RSO)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Advanced degree in Medical Physics, Health Physics, radiation physics or equivalent</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Supervised training for 6 months</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Radiation Protection and Safety</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Psychologists (both adult and pediatric)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Degree in psychology.</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>License to practice from relevant body</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Counseling of patients and their caregivers/ families on cancer; patient navigation; research; member of MDT</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Quality Assurance Officer/ Safety health officer</p>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Quality assurance officers</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Radiation Safety Officers</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Patient Safety officer</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p>Occupational safe- ty &amp; health officer</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>A designated Quality Assurance Officer/ Safety health officer</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Liaise with all departments to ensure safety &amp; quality assurance is embedded in their processes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation oncologists/clinical oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MMED/Fellowship in radiation oncology/ Clinical oncology</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice as an oncologist by KMPDB</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; in charge of radiotherapy treatment; assessment, initiation, review of patients cancer treatment and patient follow up; treatment planning; chair MDTs meetings; participate in clinical research in oncology; participates in equipment procurement</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Paediatric Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>MMED Paediatrics with fellowship in paediatric oncology</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>Licensed to practice by&nbsp; KMPDB</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer centre/facility; cancer diagnosis; assessment, initiation, review of paediatric patients cancer treatment; chair MDTs meetings; participate in clinical research in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiation Therapists (RTT) /Therapy radiographers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>-Diploma or higher diploma in radiation therapy</p>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>\r\n				<p>-&nbsp; Trained in BLS</p>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Participate in treatment planning; administer radiotherapy&nbsp; treatment&nbsp; under&nbsp; supervision&nbsp; of the radio-oncologist; participate in research and MDT activities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Radiotherapy Services Manager</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>The officer in charge to hold at least a bachelor&rsquo;s degree in therapy radiography</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>To head and coordinate radiotherapy services in the centre</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>','2022-07-21 17:10:15','2022-07-21 17:10:15'),(297,111,'Equipment','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Equipment must have service contracts and appropriate measures for plans for preventive maintenance purposes and provide service stickers showing dates for last service and next service due dates. Elements that are important for the life of the equipment and for safety shall be addressed early in the planning stage and should be included in contractual forms, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Compliance with quality and safety standards</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Acceptance tests and conditions to correct deficiencies revealed during acceptance</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Warranty conditions</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Enforceable assurances on availability of maintenance support (technical and financial), manufacturer support, manuals and spare parts</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Training of all users and keep documentation of the same</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 17:14:13','2022-07-21 17:14:13'),(298,111,'Acceptance testing and commissioning','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Radiation sources need to be safely received, registered and stored; radiation measurement equipment tested and calibrated; shielding properties of special rooms measured; and the radiation sources tested and calibrated. All major equipment will require commissioning including tele therapy machines, imaging machines (simulators), brachytherapy units and TPSs. A record keeping system should also be in place. After commissioning has been completed, the specific tests needed for ongoing quality control and safety assurance will need to be carried out.</p>','2022-07-21 17:14:13','2022-07-21 17:14:13'),(299,111,'Commissioning requirements for Radiotherapy unit','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The process of Commissioning involves Pre-Commissioning and Trial run permission.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After completion of construction and installation, the applicant should approach the regulatory body for permission to carry out a trial run for commissioning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For this purpose, the applicant should submit the following to the regulatory body:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Acceptance Tests conducted on the following equipment;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation Protection Program (RPP).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Details regarding availability of qualified and trained manpower &ndash; operator(s), radio pharmacist(s)/radio-chemist(s) and a Board approved Radiological Safety Officer (RSO).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Personnel monitoring services for all radiation workers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Appropriate radiation measuring and monitoring Instruments</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Operational procedure manual</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safe handling tools and devices required for operation and maintenance of the medical cyclotron and auxiliary equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Security Plan</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Submit the Commissioning Test Report&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>After successful trial runs, the applicant becomes eligible for obtaining consent for trial operations.</p>','2022-07-21 17:14:13','2022-07-21 17:14:13'),(300,111,'Decommissioning Requirements','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When the medical cyclotron is no longer to be used, the permission for decommissioning shall be obtained from the Radiation Protection Board. The licensee should apply for the decommissioning license and supply the Authority with the following;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safety assessment survey report of the radiological and non-radiological hazards involved during decommissioning exercise.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Decommissioning Plan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation Protection considerations for the decommissioning workers.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Public radiation protection consideration at vicinity.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Qualified Radiation safety supervisor designated for the exercise.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation safety equipment to be used for decommissioning.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radioactive waste management, transport and disposal plan for the decommissioning.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Site radiation decontamination and final radiation survey.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>The licensee shall submit a report on the completion of decommissioning, which includes among others; safe disposal of sources and personnel exposures received during decommissioning.</p>','2022-07-21 17:14:13','2022-07-21 17:14:13'),(301,111,'List of Equipment','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>External Beam Radiation Therapy.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Electronic Portal Imaging Device (EPID) photo imaging device for verification</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>High dose Rate (HDR) brachytherapy machine (afterloader)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>CT/Conventional treatment planning simulator complete with accessories</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dosimetry quality assurance equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Radiation Safety monitoring devices and radiation safety checklists and reporting.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>ICT infrastructure and support</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Treatment planning system</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Standardized rulers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Two-way video cameras, with audio capability</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Appropriate shielding requirements of radiation sources</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>3-D water scan phantom</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Range of radiation dosimeters for measuring radiation doses</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Immobilization devices</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mould room equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provision for anaesthesia space and recovery if facility is to offer pediatric radiation therapy</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 17:14:13','2022-07-21 17:14:13'),(302,112,'Physical Infrastructure','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The following section outlines the infrastructural considerations for different units. The Radiotherapy cancer centre shall ensure the physical infrastructure meets the following requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>A standard bunker for Linac</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Brachytherapy suite with a theatre</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>CT simulator room/conventional simulator room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Control room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Physics room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mould room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Administration area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Capacity for electricity, water, power backup, space</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safety considerations &ndash; fire</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disability friendly infrastructure in all areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Maintenance considerations</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Treatment planning room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Recovery area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waiting area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient Reception area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Triage area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nursing station</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Consultation room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Procedure room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Emergency room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nutrition and counselling room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate staff and patient changing rooms</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate male and female toilets for staff and patients</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Sluice room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Registry</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hand wash area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Storage area&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Conference room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Staff room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Laundry</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Holding area in case of a death</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Special considerations:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>For a radiotherapy with in-patient services, separate adult from pediatric unit.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>For pediatric services, dedicated child-friendly rooms should be provided.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 17:15:16','2022-07-21 17:15:16'),(303,113,'Service Norms','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The National Guidelines for Cancer Management shall form the basis for clinical management at the facility.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The centre or unit must have NCI-K approved protocols for diagnosis and treatment of all malignancies they manage founded on sound scientific principles and evidence-based medicine which must be accessible to the prescribers, pharmacists and nurses at the centre at all times.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The protocols must be updated as appropriate and be readily available for inspection when needed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The centre or unit shall also commit to quality improvement, supporting cancer research and improving the training and mentoring of health care e. The centre or unit shall have infrastructure in place to be able to carry out cancer registration and reporting to the National Cancer Registry and KHIS.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 18:21:20','2022-07-22 05:11:29'),(304,113,'Service Delivery Considerations','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Every cancer centre shall:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Formulate and prominently display a service charter that details the roles and responsibilities of both the patient and the centre.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide integrated and multidisciplinary care&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Prioritize coordination and planning for professionals to help facilitate access to care at other levels of care, including awareness creation, screening/early detection, case management and appropriate downward referrals.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a reasonable time frame &ndash; definitive/tissue diagnosis should be done preferably within 2 weeks and the initiation of appropriate treatment within a month of diagnosis.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The recommended time frame between diagnosis and Surgery should be at least 120 days.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Follow evidence-based protocols and guidelines.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have informed consent obtained prior to all procedures including treatments. In case of a minor, a parent/guardian shall give consent. The information prior to consenting shall be provided in a manner easily understandable by the patient. The rights of the child should be prioritized.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish clear navigation systems to enable patients&rsquo; access to services.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Design patient-tracking systems for patient follow-up throughout the continuum of care.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Develop standard operating procedures for every service being provided</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 18:21:20','2022-07-22 05:11:29'),(305,113,'Clinical Considerations','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide cancer management that is holistic and patient-centred for best care outcomes.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Before initiation of treatment, clearly define and communicate the goals of care to the patient in accordance with a patient care plan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide the patient the right to detailed information on his/her condition, treatment options including clinical trials, side effects, expected outcome and prognosis.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow the patient the right to seek a second or additional opinion before consenting to initiation of treatment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all aspects of carefully documented, stored and easily retrievable.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Allow access of patients to their records as well as laboratory samples when needed&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Comprehensively document patient history</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 18:21:20','2022-07-22 05:11:29'),(306,113,'Multi-disciplinary Tumor Boards','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Definition; the multidisciplinary expert team that should manage cancer patients in a consultative approach</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;The cancer centre shall:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish multidisciplinary teams (MDTs)/tumor boards which shall guide and direct cancer management&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have MDTs meet regularly and have participation from all relevant disciplines depending on the cancer case and the level of care&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have all complex cases discussed by a multidisciplinary team&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have an MDT coordinator who will organize for meetings, keep records of discussions and provide reports on cancer patient management&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Utilize technology to convene virtual MDT discussions with proper documentation</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>It consists of different experts including &ndash; medical oncologist, radiation/clinical oncologist, surgeon, pathologist, palliative physician and specialists, oncology pharmacist, oncology nurse, radiologist, interventional radiologist, haematologist, medical physicist, radiation therapist/therapy radiographer, medical laboratory technologists specialized in different laboratory disciplines.</p>','2022-07-21 18:21:20','2022-07-22 05:11:29'),(307,113,'Diagnostic Imaging','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(i) Incorporate clinical findings in conducting diagnostic imaging modalities&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(ii) Consider image-guided diagnostics where applicable</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(iii) Use a standard protocol for conducting imaging procedures</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(iv) Use internationally and locally recognized standards and guidelines for the safe installation, operation and use of imaging equipment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(v) Use a standard imaging diagnostic reporting protocol&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(vi) Outsource/provide access to an accredited imaging diagnostic facility</p>','2022-07-21 18:21:20','2022-07-22 05:11:29'),(308,113,'Nursing Considerations','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:-</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Provide oncology and palliative nursing care for the entire continuum of care(Prevention, Awareness, screening, early detection, diagnosis, treatment, survivorship and end of life care, bereavement).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Support the coordinating role of oncology and palliative care nurses in the&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>care team and community linkage for cancer patients</p>','2022-07-21 18:21:20','2022-07-22 05:11:29'),(309,113,'Surgical Considerations','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:-</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have Surgical site marking protocol implemented (standard site identification process, patient involved in marking, and marking done by the one doing procedure.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a Safe surgery checklist (evidence of use for verifying correct site, correct procedure, correct patient; availability of informed consent; and equipment needed are on hand, correct, and functional) See checklist&nbsp;<a href=\"about:blank\">Resources\\Safe surgery checklist.pdf</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide Evidence that facility has an active process of monitoring safe surgical checklist compliance.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ensure the organization uses a &ldquo;time-out&rdquo; procedure just before starting a surgical procedure.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Facilitate patients to access surgical diagnosis and treatment for solid malignancies through a multidisciplinary team approach.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Where tissue is obtained for histological examination, have the surgeon observe the SOP for histology specimen handling, storage and transport.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have surgical treatment offered conforming to internationally recognized, evidence-based surgical-oncological practices</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 18:21:20','2022-07-22 05:11:29'),(310,113,'Palliative Care and Survivorship Considerations','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Provide palliative care from the point of cancer diagnosis and at all times throughout the course of illness.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Integrate palliative care with other health services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Prioritize and provide effective relief of pain and other distressing symptoms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Provide timely rehabilitative and supportive services.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Facilitate formation of patient support groups.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Establish survivorship programs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Adhere to the National Palliative Care Policy and the National Palliative Care Guideline</p>','2022-07-21 18:21:20','2022-07-22 05:11:29'),(311,113,'Equipment Considerations','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Have all the facilities and equipment registered and licensed for safe and effective conduct of its services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have access to a qualified biomedical engineer, who is ultimately responsible for ensuring that all equipment are in proper working condition and that the necessary safety devices are fitted and in working order.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Maintain service contracts and schedules of service with the contracted service providers to ensure regular servicing as per the manufacturer&rsquo;s instructions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Ensure equipment compliance with relevant regulations according to the appropriate governing regulatory body.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Ensure safe disposal of obsolete or unserviceable equipment as guided by the relevant regulatory body.&nbsp;</p>','2022-07-21 18:21:20','2022-07-22 05:11:29'),(312,113,'Referral Considerations','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Develop patient referral SOPs which conform to the national referral guidelines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Properly document referrals to and away from the facility.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Promote upward, downward and horizontal referral where appropriate.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Facilitate referrals for specialized services that are unavailable at the centre to facilities that are accessible and are accredited by the relevant regulatory body.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Assess patients for fitness to travel and provide necessary supportive mechanisms (ambulance, nurse, oxygen supply) before referral.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Provide proper patient counseling on cancer, tests to be done, costs implications and expected treatment before referral.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Refer a patient to the right specialist for further management if a service outside oncology services is required</p>','2022-07-21 18:21:20','2022-07-22 05:11:29'),(313,113,'Quality Assurance','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Establish a Quality Assurance Programme (QAP) that is adequately supervised and provides reports to NCI Kenya as required.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Have risk assessment measures in place with objectives and systematic monitoring and evaluation so as to identify problems and system failures and guide the necessary action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Have regular morbidity and mortality meetings to identify specific clinical performance indicators.</p>','2022-07-21 18:21:20','2022-07-22 05:11:29'),(314,113,'Infection Prevention and Control','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Oncology patients are at increased infection risk due to immunosuppression and frequent exposure to healthcare settings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a hospital&rsquo;s infection prevention and control program must be in accordance with the WHO Practical Guidelines for Infection Control.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have hand-washing facilities for staff readily available. Hand sanitizers should be provided at every work station.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide a designated sluicing area for linen generated in the Surgical area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have isolation rooms and practice barrier nursing by ensuring PPEs are available and easily accessible.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide decontamination and sterilization areas. (The decontaminant, sodium hypochlorite 5%)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 18:21:20','2022-07-22 05:11:29'),(315,113,'Occupational health and safety','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Implement the Occupational, Health &amp; Safety (OSH) Act in the workplace.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide safety and health training at least once every 3 years.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Be subject to annual inspection by the local regulatory body and adhere to the basic safety standards as set by the regulatory body.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disclose labeling laws for identification and classification of chemicals by types of hazards, including medication labels and safety data sheets.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have a system for incidents monitoring and management at the workplace.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have programs to monitor and support employee performance, mental health, work-life balance and put in place debriefing programs.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 18:21:20','2022-07-22 05:11:29'),(316,113,'Waste Management','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide waste segregation and disposal amenities.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Conduct regular capacity building on waste disposal for all healthcare providers including support staff.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Provide appropriate PPEs for handling clinical waste</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 18:21:20','2022-07-22 05:11:29'),(317,113,'Emergency Medical Care','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Have facilities and human resources to handle Surgical Oncology emergencies.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ensure medical staffs are trained in BLS/ACLS.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stabilize the patient and expeditiously refer for emergency management where applicable.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Be well equipped with resuscitation commodities and equipment.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 18:21:20','2022-07-22 05:11:29'),(318,113,'Adverse Events','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Any adverse event that occurs as a result of the surgery must be documented, discussed internally and reported to the relevant regulatory bodies such as the Pharmacy and Poisons Board, relevant regulatory body and the NCI-K.</p>','2022-07-21 18:21:20','2022-07-22 05:11:29'),(319,113,'Death of a Patient','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Document all deaths occurring whilst patients are undergoing treatment appropriately.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Offer bereavement support to the family.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Have periodic mortality meetings where cancer deaths are discussed by a multidisciplinary team</p>','2022-07-21 18:21:20','2022-07-22 05:11:29'),(320,114,'Surgical Unit Physical Infrastructure','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cancer centre shall ensure the physical infrastructure meets the following requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patient flow</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Capacity for electricity, water, power backup, space</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Safety considerations &ndash; fire</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separation of adult from pediatric management areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Disability infrastructure in all areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Maintenance considerations</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 18:27:07','2022-07-22 05:15:41'),(321,114,'All departments and units','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For centres operating within the precincts of a hospital, it can utilize similar facilities within the hospital. For stand-alone centres, these services must be provided for:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Appropriate space for the following administrative services:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Administration</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Finance</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Transport</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iv. Supply chain management</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;v. Laundry</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;vi. Healthcare waste management, including hazardous drug waste, a Lockable holding area, proper segregation and disposal, MOUs with disposal companies</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;vii. Conference room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ix. Reception area</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Utilities</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate patient and staff changing rooms</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Separate staff and patients rest rooms</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Staff room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 18:27:07','2022-07-22 05:15:41'),(322,114,'Health records and information - Registration area','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>i.&nbsp;Office space</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Filing room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Use of NACARE system for reporting is required using secure internet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Other supportive services</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Provision for day care services where applicable</p>','2022-07-21 18:27:07','2022-07-22 05:15:41'),(323,114,'Cancer registry office','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Office space</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Filing room</p>','2022-07-21 18:27:07','2022-07-22 05:15:41'),(324,114,'Surgical Oncology Unit','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Patient registration and reception area</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Waiting area for patients and caregivers</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Consultation room&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Triage/observation room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Counseling room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Procedure room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Pharmacy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>h. Operating theatre capable of handling minor and major surgical procedures with a Patient receiving room and a patient recovery room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>i. Nutrition</p>\r\n\r\n<p>j. Palliative care</p>\r\n\r\n<p>k. Medical Laboratory Unit</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Support from;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Diagnostic radiology unit</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pathology unit</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Blood banking</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Critical care unit</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Rehabilitation centres&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Endoscopy services</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Morgue services</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 18:27:07','2022-07-22 05:15:41'),(325,114,'Inpatient oncology wards','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Separate female, male, adolescents, geriatric and pediatric wards&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Side room facilities for ward reviews of post-operative wounds, minor procedures, and emergency resuscitation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Isolation rooms for patients with infectious conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Waste management facilities</p>','2022-07-21 18:27:07','2022-07-22 05:15:41'),(326,114,'Palliative care and Survivorship Unit','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Patient registration and reception area</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Waiting area for patients/caregivers</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Counseling room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Procedure room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. Consultation room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Community room large enough to accommodate support groups</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. Support services</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Pharmacy</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Nutrition</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Chaplaincy&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iv. Counseling&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;v. Rehabilitative unit</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. Pediatrics play area</p>\r\n\r\n<p>g. Nutrition counseling rooms</p>','2022-07-21 18:27:07','2022-07-22 05:15:41'),(327,114,'Design and construction requirements','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The design of any surgery department revolves around environmental control, traffic control, and the desire to prevent surgical site infection (SSI).&nbsp;<a href=\"about:blank\">Resources\\Surgical Operating Theatres Standards.docx</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Consult the Services of a registered Architectural and structural Engineering firms, with expertise in construction of health care facilities, for the design and construction.</p>','2022-07-21 18:27:07','2022-07-22 05:15:41'),(328,115,'Surgical Unit Equipment','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Equipment must have service contracts and appropriate measures for plans for preventive maintenance purposes and provide service stickers showing dates for last service and next service due dates.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Elements that are important for the life of the equipment and for safety shall be addressed early in the planning stage and should be included in contractual forms, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Compliance with quality and safety standards</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Acceptance tests and conditions to correct deficiencies revealed during acceptance</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Warranty conditions</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Enforceable assurances on availability of maintenance support</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;(technical and financial), manufacturer support, manuals and spare parts</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Training of all users and keep documentation of the same</p>','2022-07-21 18:31:58','2022-07-22 05:16:37'),(329,115,'Acceptance, testing and commissioning','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Commissioning is done by the manufacturer or his representative, Biomedical Engineer and the Surgeon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A record keeping system should also be in place. After commissioning has been completed, the specific tests needed for ongoing quality control and safety assurance will need to be carried out.</p>','2022-07-21 18:31:58','2022-07-22 05:16:37'),(330,115,'Equipment Donation','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The donations should be guided by the principles developed by the WHO.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There should be effective communication between the donor, the recipient authority and, whenever possible, the end-user, before, during and after the donation.</p>','2022-07-21 18:31:58','2022-07-22 05:16:37'),(331,115,'Surgical Oncology Unit Equipment','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Fully equipped major and minor theatres with standard anaesthetic, surgical and interventional equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Receiving area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pre-operative room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Post-operative room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Scrubbing room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Changing room</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waiting area</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Fully equipped endoscopy suite</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 18:31:58','2022-07-22 05:16:37'),(332,115,'In-patient Surgical wards','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Wards</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. Beds</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;ii. Wheelchairs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iii. Trolleys</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;iv. Consumable and reusable equipment for IV and medication equipment</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Phlebotomy equipment</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bedside Cabinets</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurses&rsquo; station with cabinets/shelves</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>BP Monitors</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Thermometers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Weighing scale</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Heightometer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Crash cart</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Waste segregation bins</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medicine Cabinets&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Consumables cabinets</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>','2022-07-21 18:31:58','2022-07-22 05:16:37'),(333,115,'Decommissioning requirements','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Safety assessment survey report of the hazards involved during decommissioning exercise. Have a Decommissioning Plan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Have a hazardous waste management, transport and disposal plan for the decommissioning.</p>','2022-07-21 18:31:58','2022-07-22 05:16:37'),(334,116,'Human Resource','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Anesthesiologists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Biomedical engineer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical Lab personnel&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Cancer Registrar</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical Officer anesthetist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurse anesthetist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Gynaecology Oncologist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Housekeeping staff</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Interventional radiologists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical Officers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical social worker</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurse &ndash; General with theatre experience</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nutritionist</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Medical/ hemato-onco, Pediatric, Radiation Oncologists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Surgeons</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Q/A</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>IPC</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Clinical Counsellors</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Physiotherapists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pharmacists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nurse-palliative care</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Occupational therapists</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2022-07-21 18:35:37','2022-07-22 05:17:31'),(335,116,'Core Human Resource','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Human resource category&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Minimum Qualifications&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Roles and Responsibilities (in addition to relevant job description and scope of professional practice)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Anesthesiologists</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMed in Anesthesia&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Review patients for surgery; pain management;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>in charge of ICU/HDU</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Medical oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>- MMED and a fellowship in medical oncology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>as an oncologist by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>centre/facility; assessment, initiation, review of&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>patients cancer treatment; chair MDTs meetings;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>participate in clinical research in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Pediatric Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MMED Paediatrics&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>with fellowship in paediatric oncology</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>centre/facility; cancer diagnosis; assessment,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>initiation, review of paediatric patients cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>treatment; chair MDTs meetings; participate in&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>clinical research in oncology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Gynaecology&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Oncologist</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>MMED Obs/Gyne with&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>a fellowship in Gynae&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Oncology.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>- Licensed to practice&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>as a Gynae oncologist&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>by KMPDB</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>May be the designated head of the cancer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>centre/facility; assessment, initiation, surgical&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>management and review of gynaecological&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>cancer patients; p